Palmetto State Armory (PSA) is an American firearms company founded in 2008 by Jamin McCallum, based in Columbia, South Carolina. Initially starting as an online retailer selling magazines and ammunition, PSA quickly expanded into manufacturing firearms and firearm components. The company operates multiple retail locations across South Carolina, Georgia, and North Carolina.

PSA specializes in a variety of firearms, particularly AR-15 and AK-47 style rifles. Their product offerings include complete firearms, firearm build kits, high-capacity magazines, and various components and accessories. The company is committed to making firearms accessible to law-abiding Americans at competitive prices. PSA targets a diverse customer base of firearm enthusiasts and hobbyists, focusing on quality and affordability. As part of the JJE Capital family of brands, PSA also sells products from sister companies and other manufacturers through both online and physical stores.

Short Description:
Weatherby, Inc. is an American firearms manufacturer established in 1945 by Roy Weatherby. The company is headquartered in Sheridan, Wyoming, after relocating from Paso Robles, California, in 2018. Weatherby is recognized for its development of high-powered magnum cartridges and precision rifles, including the renowned .257, .270, .300, .340, and .460 Weatherby Magnum cartridges, which are designed for effective and humane hunting.

The company’s flagship product is the Mark V bolt action rifle, known for its strength and precision, featuring nine locking lugs and a short bolt lift to handle high pressures. Weatherby also offers the Vanguard series, which provides a more affordable option based on the Howa 1500 bolt action. Their product line includes proprietary ammunition tailored for big game hunting, as well as custom and production firearms. Weatherby serves a global market of hunters and shooting sports enthusiasts, emphasizing quality craftsmanship and ballistic innovation.

Short Description:
REM Surface Engineering is a leader in surface engineering, focusing on advanced metal finishing technologies. Founded in 1965 by Bob and Florence Michaud, the company initially specialized in metal cleaning and plating products for various industries, including silverware and aircraft engines. Over the years, REM developed the patented Isotropic Superfinish Process (ISF®), which utilizes non-abrasive automated mass finishing to achieve superior surface finishes.

The core offerings of REM include the ISF® technology and its advanced variant, the Extreme ISF® Process. These processes enhance surface roughness, remove near-surface defects, and improve the performance of metal components. They are particularly effective for post-processing in metal additive manufacturing. REM serves a diverse clientele, including high-technology and defense sectors, and collaborates with organizations like NASA and the Department of Defense. The company provides its finishing technologies as outsourced services and as installations for in-house use, catering to both high-volume production and specialty projects.

Short Description:
2nd Amendment Wholesale is a firearms wholesale distribution company that serves Federal Firearm Licensed (FFL) retailers across the United States. As a 100% wholesale distributor, it supplies firearms, ammunition, and related accessories exclusively to gun shops and sporting goods retailers, without selling to the general public.

The company emphasizes fast shipping, excellent customer service, and competitive pricing, offering a broad selection of leading firearm brands. To help smaller dealers compete with larger distributors, 2nd Amendment Wholesale has developed an innovative system called Allocation Points™, which ensures fair access to new products. They also provide technology integrations, such as a partnership with Celerant, allowing dealers to access their product catalog directly from point-of-sale systems. This integration aids in maintaining ATF compliance and streamlining inventory management.

Additionally, 2nd Amendment Wholesale utilizes advanced e-commerce and warehouse management solutions to enhance order management and dealer interactions. Their dealer portal enables authorized retailers to place wholesale or dropship orders with custom pricing, supporting seamless business operations and growth for both the distributor and its dealers.

Short Description:
Alro Steel is a prominent distributor of metals, industrial supplies, and engineering plastics, founded in 1948 in Jackson, Michigan, by brothers Al and Robert Glick. The company began during a steel shortage from World War II, connecting businesses in need of steel with those that had excess supply. Today, Alro operates over 80 locations across 16 states, serving more than 25,000 manufacturing customers with next-day delivery services.

Alro offers a wide range of products, including various metals and performance plastics, along with industrial supplies to support manufacturing needs. The company provides processing services such as cut-to-size options for metals and plastics, available both online and at retail outlets. Alro's online store allows customers to purchase materials 24/7, and its retail outlets offer prime materials and remnants at discounted prices, along with expert advice and on-the-spot cutting services. Alro Steel is dedicated to customer service and teamwork, fostering a culture of respect and support for both customers and employees.

Short Description:
AMUT is an Italian company founded in 1958, headquartered in Novara, Italy. It specializes in the design, manufacture, and supply of extrusion and recycling technologies for thermoplastic materials. With over 50 years of experience, AMUT has established itself as a global leader in its field, known for its innovative solutions and strong customer service, supported by a skilled engineering team and a dedicated R&D department.

The company produces a wide range of extrusion lines for various plastic products, including cast film, sheets, tubing, and profiles. AMUT also designs and builds advanced recycling plants for sorting and washing plastics, covering the entire circular treatment process. Its product offerings include custom-engineered machinery for both extrusion and recycling, ensuring tailored solutions for its clients in the plastics manufacturing and recycling industries worldwide.

Bizzflo is a comprehensive small business software system that will help you manage your business even more efficiently.  The Bizzflo platform enables small or medium sized businesses to conduct all of their transactions online in a cloud based platform.

Central Plastics is a family-owned custom plastics manufacturer based in McPherson, Kansas, with a history that dates back to 1968. The company specializes in custom plastic extrusions, producing a variety of profiles such as channels, tubes, and custom shapes using materials like PVC, ABS, and polycarbonate. With over 170 employees and a 250,000 square foot facility, Central Plastics operates 24/5, focusing on high-quality production and customer satisfaction.

In addition to extrusion, Central Plastics provides complementary services including cutting, drilling, punching, and custom packaging. The company also has a facility in Northern California that offers custom plastic injection molding and thermoforming packaging solutions, certified to ISO 13485:2016 and AS 9100 Rev D standards. Central Plastics serves a wide range of industries, including construction, automotive, medical, aerospace, and electronics, showcasing its versatility and commitment to quality and sustainability. As a minority- and woman-owned business, Central Plastics emphasizes diversity and inclusion in the manufacturing sector.

Short Description:
Darn Tough Vermont® is a family-owned sock manufacturer based in Northfield, Vermont. Founded in 2004 by Ric Cabot, the company operates under the Cabot Hosiery Mills, which has a history dating back to 1978. Darn Tough is known for its high-quality performance socks made from fine gauge Merino wool blended with nylon and Lycra®/Spandex. These socks are designed for moisture-wicking, flexibility, and long-lasting comfort.

The company offers a variety of socks for activities such as hiking, running, skiing, hunting, and military use. Darn Tough stands out with its unconditional lifetime guarantee, promising to replace any socks that develop holes at no cost to the customer. EBizCharge is a payment processing company founded in 2004, dedicated to providing integrated merchant processing solutions for businesses. The company addresses inefficiencies in credit card acceptance and accounting systems with its flagship software, EBizCharge, which allows businesses to accept credit card payments directly within their accounting software.

EOTECH is an American company that designs, manufactures, and markets professional-grade electro-optic products, focusing on holographic weapon sights, night vision, and thermal imaging systems. Founded in 1995 as a subsidiary of the Environmental Research Institute of Michigan, EOTECH has been delivering high-performance optics since its first product launch in 1996. The company is known for its innovative holographic technology, which enhances speed, accuracy, and reliability for small arms optics.

EOTECH's product lineup includes Holographic Weapon Sights (HWS), which are widely used by military, law enforcement, and civilian shooters for their rapid target acquisition and durability. The company also offers night vision and thermal imaging devices, as well as magnifiers and precision scopes, including the Vudu line. EOTECH emphasizes domestic manufacturing, producing its holographic sights in Ann Arbor, Michigan, and ensuring high-quality standards across its product range. The company serves a diverse customer base, including U.S. military forces, law enforcement agencies, and recreational shooters.

Blockchain is a rapidly-advancing field that offers many exciting developments, with more applications and use cases appearing every day. However, this innovation often comes with a ‘move fast and break things' approach to software development that doesn't sit well when dealing with millions or even billions of dollars of users' financial value.

Ergo draws on ten years of blockchain development, complementing tried and tested principles with the best peer-reviewed academic research into cryptography, consensus models and digital currencies. We start with solid blockchain basics and implement new and powerful cryptography natively. Our team has a solid background in core development with cryptocurrencies and blockchain frameworks including Nxt, Scorex and Waves, and our lean approach means we can prioritise new features and requirements quickly.

GunBroker.com is a prominent online auction marketplace that specializes in firearms, ammunition, and shooting-related accessories. Founded in 1999 by Steven F. Urvan, the platform emerged in response to eBay's restrictions on gun sales and has since become one of the largest venues for buying and selling firearms and related gear.

The company provides a secure and transparent platform for users to auction or purchase a variety of products, including firearms, hunting gear, air guns, archery equipment, and knives. GunBroker.com facilitates transactions between buyers and sellers, emphasizing responsible gun ownership and adherence to applicable laws. In 2021, it was acquired by AMMO, Inc., and has approximately 6 million registered users. The leadership team includes CEO Jared Smith and Chairman Fred Wagenhals.

GunBroker.com has a diverse customer base, including firearm enthusiasts, hunters, collectors, and shooting sports participants. The company has also engaged in sponsorships, notably in NASCAR and with USA Shooting for the Olympics, showcasing its commitment to the shooting sports community.

HighCom Armor is a U.S.-based company that designs, develops, manufactures, and distributes advanced ballistic-resistant body armor and personal protective equipment. HighCom Armor is recognized for its commitment to quality, being the first to receive the BA 9000 certification for body armor manufacturing and maintaining ISO 9001:2015 certification. Short Description:
HOMMEL ETAMIC is a global manufacturer and system supplier specializing in industrial metrology solutions. The company provides a wide range of standard and custom measurement and testing systems that utilize tactile, pneumatic, and optical technologies. These systems are designed to measure surface roughness, contour, shape, and dimensional features of workpieces throughout the production cycle.

Their solutions cater to various precision manufacturing industries, including automotive, aerospace, and medical technology. HOMMEL ETAMIC's systems support inline, offline, spot checks, and 100% inspection of manufactured parts, delivering fast and accurate measurement data to enhance productivity. The company offers digital gages, measuring tools, optical inspection equipment, and quality services, including consulting and training.

Founded from the merger of Hommelwerke and Etamic, HOMMEL ETAMIC has over 140 years of expertise in precision production measurement technology. Headquartered in Villingen-Schwenningen, Germany, the company has subsidiaries in France, the USA, and India, along with a global network of distributors. As part of the Jenoptik Group, HOMMEL ETAMIC continues to innovate in industrial metrology, focusing on precise process control and seamless system integration.

Silencer Shop, founded in 2010 by Dave Matheny in Austin, Texas, is the largest distributor of firearm suppressors in the United States. The company aims to simplify the complex process of legally purchasing suppressors, which are regulated under the National Firearm Act. By leveraging technology, Silencer Shop has made silencer ownership faster and more accessible, embodying the slogan “Silencer Ownership Simplified.”

The company operates a nationwide network of kiosks that allow customers to complete trust-based suppressor purchases, streamlining the process and reducing wait times for approval from months to just a few weeks. Silencer Shop also provides electronic ATF form processing, ensuring accurate submission of required paperwork, and offers extensive customer support to help clients navigate legal requirements. Additionally, the company actively advocates for suppressor rights through partnerships and funding for legislative efforts. Silencer Shop serves a diverse customer base, including hunters, sport shooters, and firearm enthusiasts, with a wide range of suppressor brands and models available.

Their product lineup includes CO2 laser machines capable of engraving and cutting various materials such as wood, plastic, and metal, as well as fiber laser systems designed for marking bare metals and engineered plastics. Epilog Laser serves a diverse customer base, including sign shops, schools, and industrial facilities, all seeking to improve production efficiency and creative capabilities through advanced laser technology. The company is committed to quality, with machines designed and assembled in the USA.

IPG Photonics Corporation is a global leader in the manufacturing and supply of high-performance fiber lasers, amplifiers, and laser systems. Founded in 1990 and based in Marlborough, Massachusetts, the company has pioneered optical fiber-based lasers, which are widely used in various industrial, medical, and advanced technology applications. With over 4,700 employees and operations in more than 30 countries, IPG has grown significantly since its early days.

The company offers a diverse range of products centered on fiber laser technology, including high-power industrial fiber lasers for cutting, welding, and marking, as well as integrated laser systems for specific applications like additive manufacturing. IPG also provides optical fiber amplifiers and advanced laser platforms. Their services include technical support and application laboratories to help customers optimize laser performance. IPG's technology is utilized across multiple industries, including telecommunications, automotive, aerospace, and medical device manufacturing, emphasizing energy efficiency and sustainable practices.

OSH Cut, founded in 2018 by brothers Jacom and Caleb Chamberlain, specializes in on-demand metal fabrication, focusing on precision sheet metal and plate manufacturing. The company aims to streamline the custom metal fabrication process using modern technology and an innovative online quoting platform. This platform allows customers to upload drawings or 3D models, select materials and quantities, and receive instant pricing along with manufacturability feedback.

The services offered by OSH Cut include laser cutting, metal bending, deburring and graining, metal tapping, and powder coating. They support 3D model uploads and optimize material usage through nesting techniques. The company stocks over 500 variations of sheet metal and plate, accommodating various alloys such as steel, stainless steel, aluminum, and more. OSH Cut serves a diverse customer base, from individuals to businesses, providing rapid turnaround times for prototypes and short-run production. Headquartered in Spanish Fork, Utah, OSH Cut operates Monday through Friday and offers customer support via phone and email.

Short Description:
Advanced Technology International (ATI) is a nonprofit organization dedicated to fostering research and development (R&D) collaborations that address urgent national challenges. With over 25 years of experience, ATI connects government agencies with innovators from industry, academia, and non-traditional contractors to accelerate technological progress. The organization is a leader in managing Other Transaction Agreements (OTAs), which facilitate flexible partnerships and enhance collaboration among diverse stakeholders.

ATI's core mission focuses on coordinating innovative research initiatives, particularly those impacting national security across sectors like aviation, armaments, biomedical, and shipbuilding. The organization manages various programs, including the National Shipbuilding Research Program and the DoD Ordnance Technology Consortium, aimed at reducing costs and enhancing capabilities for the U.S. Navy and defense sectors. Additionally, ATI offers the collaborATIon™ app, a mobile platform that provides access to collaboration information and networking opportunities, further supporting its goal of uniting the best R&D teams to tackle the nation’s greatest challenges.
Subsidiary of: ATI Foundation | Advanced Technology International Foundation (ati-foundation.org)

Short Description:
Aimpoint Inc. is a subsidiary of Aimpoint AB, a Swedish company known for pioneering red dot sight technology since 1975. The company was founded by inventor Arne Ekstrand and entrepreneur Gunnar Sandberg, who aimed to enhance accuracy for hunters, sport shooters, and military users. Aimpoint is recognized as the originator of electronic red dot reflex sighting technology, focusing on innovation, quality, and reliability.

Aimpoint specializes in designing and manufacturing high-tech red dot sights and related optical products. Their offerings include compact and durable sights suitable for various applications, such as hunting, sport shooting, law enforcement, and military use. Notable products include the Aimpoint 3000 series and the Comp™ M sights, which are used by the U.S. military as the M68 Close Combat Optic. Aimpoint sights are known for their speed, accuracy, and ability to withstand harsh conditions.

The company serves a diverse customer base, including hunters, sport shooters, law enforcement agencies, and military forces worldwide. Aimpoint has gained significant recognition in the military sector, particularly during the Gulf War, and continues to deliver high-quality optical solutions globally.

Short Description:
AK SAVUNMA was founded in Ankara on August 1st, 2017 to carry on its bussines in the small arms ammunition industry with the slogan "Hundred Percent Local, Hundred Percent National". AK SAVUNMA started its foundation activity on a total area of 12.500 square meters including an indoor area of 7.600 square meters in Ankara, Elmadag, Turkey.

AK SAVUNMA aims to provide continuous improvement and development by taking into account customer requirements and by applying quality standards carefully. AK SAVUNMA firstly started to manufacture 9mm, 5.56mm, 7.62mm Brass Cups for Brass Cases and FMJ Bullets.

AK SAVUNMA obtained Establishment License, Facility Security Clearance Certificate (NATO / National), and Manufacturing Permit Certificate which is given by The Ministry of Defence. Armasight is a US-based company that specializes in advanced night vision and thermal imaging technologies. Founded in 2011 by Dmitry Rocklin, the company quickly gained recognition for introducing the first commercially available dedicated thermal weapon sight. Armasight provides high-quality optical solutions for military personnel, law enforcement, first responders, and civilian consumers.

The product lineup includes high-performance night vision devices such as goggles, monoculars, and scopes, as well as thermal imaging systems like weapon sights and handheld scopes. Additionally, Armasight offers optical accessories to enhance the functionality of its core products. The company is committed to delivering unparalleled quality and customer service, ensuring users are equipped for challenging environments. 

Armasight has a rich heritage in infrared technology, with roots tracing back to military innovations from World War II. After being acquired by FLIR Systems in 2016 and later by Ecentria in 2020, Armasight continues to innovate and serve a diverse customer base with its advanced optical solutions.

ArmorLube, LLC is a leader in high-performance, ultra-hard coating solutions, redefining durability and reliability across the world's most demanding industries. Since our founding in 2013, we have been committed to revolutionizing surface performance with advanced Diamond-Like Carbon (DLC) coating technology that consistently outperforms traditional methods.

Our mission is simple: to deliver unmatched hardness, wear resistance, and long-term reliability — without the complications associated with liquid-based lubricants. By combining innovation with precision engineering, we enable our customers to tackle their toughest challenges with total confidence.

At the heart of our success is our patented Hollow Cathode process and cutting-edge 3D DLC coating technology. This permanent dry lubrication solution significantly enhances both performance and longevity, empowering components to thrive in extreme environments where failure is not an option.

We take pride in setting new industry standards, ensuring every product meets the highest benchmarks of quality. Our coatings serve a wide range of applications, providing critical advantages in medical, automotive, aerospace, energy, and defense-related sectors.

With an unwavering focus on excellence and innovation, ArmorLube is more than a coating provider — we are a trusted partner in performance, helping organizations around the globe achieve new levels of efficiency, reliability, and success.

Short Description:
Hartsfield-Jackson Atlanta International Airport is a major global aviation hub located in Atlanta, Georgia. Established in 1925, it has become one of the busiest airports in the world, handling over 110 million passengers annually and approximately 56,000 metric tons of mail and cargo each month. The airport features a complex terminal system with multiple concourses designed to facilitate efficient passenger transfers and support a wide range of airlines, with Delta Air Lines as a dominant carrier.

The airport offers extensive passenger services, including dining, retail, lounges, and business services across its terminals. It also provides cargo handling facilities, ground transportation options, and specialized services such as air traffic control and customs for international travelers. Hartsfield-Jackson serves a diverse clientele, including domestic and international airline passengers, cargo carriers, and local businesses, making it a vital transportation hub for the southeastern United States and a gateway to global destinations.

Atlantic Signal is North America's largest custom tactical communications designer, manufacturer, and supplier, based in Topeka, Kansas. The company offers a diverse range of tactical communication products, including custom headsets, push-to-talk devices, and accessories. Notable innovations include the world's first four-way adjustable tactical bone conduction headset, submersible amphibious assault headsets, and wireless push-to-talk systems. B.E. Meyers & Co., Inc. is a mid-sized defense contractor based in Redmond, Washington, founded in 1974. The company specializes in designing, manufacturing, and integrating advanced optoelectronic and photonics systems for defense and law enforcement applications.

For over 55 years, Berry's Bullets has been producing superior bullets for shooters everywhere. Established in 1961 by Ray Berry, Berry's is still family owned and operated today. With the capability of our state of the art CNC shop, we also produce the innovative VersaCradle® gun vise & accessories. Decades of experience in the shooting industry make Berry's Bullets & Reloading Accessories the superior choice for your shooting and reloading needs.

Short Description:
Seit über 150 Jahren fertigen wir die berühmten Messer mit dem weltweit bekannten Baumzeichen in der Klingenstadt Solingen von Hand. Seit unserer Gründung im Jahr 1869 hat kein Messer unsere Manufaktur ohne dieses Qualitätssiegel verlassen. Die lange Historie der Böker Manufaktur ist geprägt von ereignisreichen Zeiten. Eines ist aber immer gleichgeblieben: Unsere Leidenschaft und Begeisterung für außergewöhnliche Messer.

Die Böker Messer-Manufaktur hat sich so zu einem weltweiten Innovationsführer und zum größten Hersteller von Sportmessern, Einsatzmessern und Sammlermessern in Europa entwickelt.

Heute blicken wir auf eine mittlerweile 150-jährige Firmengeschichte zurück, in der die Böker Manufaktur kontinuierlich und ohne Pause, mit dem Ohr am Markt, für Innovationen in der Messerbranche sorgt. Mit neuen Ideen, aber auch mit der Wahrung unserer traditionellen Werte und dem nachhaltigen Umgang mit unserer Umwelt steht unser Sortiment heute für höchste Qualität und für eine beispiellose Vielfalt.

Broco, Inc. and Rankin Industries are world leaders in the development and manufacture of high-performance products for underwater cutting and welding, military and tactical breaching and rescue, industrial cutting and hardfacing, and automated welding systems.

Our processes for manufacturing Rankin hardfacing and Protective Metal Alloys products are ISO 9001:2008 certified.

For more information about all the products we offer visit www.broco-rankin.com or email us at sales@brocoinc.com.

Strengthening the Arsenal

Detroit once earned the name the Arsenal of Democracy for the role our fellow engineers and workers played in the war effort. The Detroit Gun Works Imperative

Our heart is riot gear. We have perfected the design of crowd control equipment and manufacture some of the world's leading riot shields, riot helmets and riot suits. EDI-USA also manufactures ballistic and tactical gear for law enforcement & military.

Manufacturing amazing products trusted by thousands of men and women around the world, EDI does business differently.

What We Value

Tradition:
Initially founded in Pennsylvania, USA to manufacture anti-riot suits for local police, EDI-USA has grown to manufacture over 3,700 law enforcement & tactical products. EDI's staff works daily to create, design, and produce tactical gear to help law enforcement personnel succeed.

Streamlined Export:
International customers comprise of more than 50% of our business. Our international presence stretches long and wide from shipping to our neighbors in Canada and Mexico, all the way across the world to South America and Asia. Wherever you are, we will make sure you get what you need.

Quality to the Max:
In an industry where people's lives depend on the items we provide, EDI-USA takes quality very seriously. We have set ourselves apart with our strict EDI-USA Quality -Pro Program, which ensures quality from the inside-out. On a regular basis, we send our products to laboratories for independent testing, as well as maintain ISO 9001:2015 certification.

To learn more, visit us at ExecDefense.com.

Elbit Systems of America is a U.S.-based aerospace and defense technology company located in Fort Worth, Texas. With over 3,300 employees across 16 locations, it is a subsidiary of Elbit Systems Ltd from Israel. The company specializes in advanced solutions that enhance situational awareness, survivability, and lethality for military and defense customers, particularly the U.S. Army.

The company offers a wide range of services and products in sectors such as defense, commercial aviation, homeland security, medical instrumentation, and law enforcement. Key offerings include airborne systems, electro-optics, precision targeting systems, night vision, tactical communications, and training and simulation. Elbit Systems of America also develops medical devices and provides support services, along with modernization for ground combat systems and helmet-mounted displays for military aircraft.

With a strong commitment to integrity, innovation, and customer partnership, Elbit Systems of America emphasizes sustainability and community engagement in its operations. The company is dedicated to serving those on the front lines, including soldiers, first responders, and medical professionals.

Short Description:
ELEY HAWK LIMITED is a British company that specializes in manufacturing premium shotgun cartridges. Founded in 1828 by the Eley brothers in London, it is recognized as the oldest shotgun cartridge manufacturer in the UK. The company is headquartered in Sutton Coldfield, West Midlands, and has been operating under its current name since 1986.

Eley Hawk produces a diverse range of shotgun cartridges suitable for game shooting and clay shooting. Their offerings include competition cartridges, custom loads, game cartridges, special loads, and non-toxic options. The company operates a modern manufacturing facility in Birmingham, where it combines nearly 200 years of expertise with advanced technology to ensure high quality and consistency in its products. Eley Hawk is known for its commitment to innovation and sustainability, making it a trusted choice for shooters worldwide.

Short Description:
Evidence IQ is a global forensic identification and evaluation company that specializes in advanced forensic technology solutions for law enforcement agencies at various levels, including local, county, state, and federal. The company aims to partner with these agencies to provide timely intelligence that helps reduce gun crimes in communities.

The flagship product, Ballistics IQ™, is an automated ballistics imaging triage solution designed for the immediate scanning and analysis of firearms evidence, particularly fired cartridge cases. This system uses proprietary software to identify the number of firearms involved in a crime and determines the best candidates for entry into the National Integrated Ballistic Information Network (NIBIN). It also features the Automated Potential Link (APL) search, which connects current incidents with previously scanned cartridge cases, offering actionable intelligence that enhances investigative efforts.

Evidence IQ's services focus on delivering rapid crime gun intelligence, streamlining evidence submission, and supporting law enforcement initiatives. The team comprises experts from agencies like the ATF and FBI, ensuring a strong commitment to reducing gun crime and improving community safety.

Franchi is an Italian firearms manufacturer with a history that dates back to 1868. Originally a family business in Brescia, Italy, Franchi has built a strong reputation for innovation and craftsmanship in shotguns and rifles. The company combines patented technologies with traditional manufacturing techniques to create high-quality firearms.

Franchi specializes in shotguns that feature advanced elements such as the TSA recoil pad for reduced recoil, the Relia Trigger for improved accuracy, and the Evolved ERGON-X stock for enhanced comfort. Their shotguns utilize the Inertia Driven System, which contributes to their performance and reliability. 

As part of the Beretta Group, Franchi continues to thrive in the firearms market, catering to hunters, sport shooters, and firearm enthusiasts who appreciate Italian design and innovation.

Short Description:
The State of Georgia is the official government entity of Georgia, operating under a republican form of government as defined by the Georgia State Constitution. It consists of three branches: legislative, executive, and judicial. The legislative branch, known as the Georgia General Assembly, creates state laws and policies through its bicameral structure, which includes the Senate and the House of Representatives.

The executive branch is led by the Governor, who oversees law enforcement, state budget management, and various agencies responsible for public services such as education, health, and transportation. The judicial branch interprets laws and administers justice through a system of courts, including the Supreme Court of Georgia and several trial courts. The State of Georgia provides essential public services to its residents, businesses, and local governments, ensuring a well-functioning governance system.

Short Description:
GLOCK GmbH is an Austrian firearms manufacturer established in 1963 by engineer Gaston Glock, with its headquarters in Deutsch-Wagram, Austria. The company initially produced consumer goods but shifted its focus in the 1970s to military products. In the early 1980s, GLOCK made a significant impact on the handgun market with the introduction of the Glock 17, the first polymer-framed, striker-fired semi-automatic pistol, designed for reliability and safety.

GLOCK's main product line features polymer-framed pistols equipped with the SAFE ACTION® System, which includes three internal safeties to prevent accidental discharge. Known for their lightweight design and high-capacity magazines, GLOCK pistols have gained popularity among military, law enforcement, and civilian users worldwide, with over 20 million units produced. In addition to pistols, GLOCK also manufactures field knives, entrenching tools, horse-related equipment, and apparel, showcasing a diverse product range. The company serves a broad customer base, emphasizing safety, reliability, and simplicity in its firearm designs.

Crye Precision LLC is based in Brooklyn, New York, and specializes in designing and manufacturing high-performance equipment and apparel for the United States Armed Forces and other defense customers. Founded in 1999 by Caleb Crye and Gregg Thompson, the company is recognized for producing Berry Amendment-compliant gear, ensuring that all products are made in the USA from American materials.

The product range includes combat uniforms, body armor, load carriage systems, and specialized protective solutions aimed at enhancing the performance and comfort of military personnel. A key innovation from Crye Precision is the MultiCam camouflage pattern, developed in collaboration with the U.S. Army Soldier Systems Center in 2002. This versatile pattern has been widely adopted by U.S. special forces and military units.

Crye Precision focuses on collaboration with end users to improve gear functionality and reliability. The company is committed to quality and smart design, catering to the needs of those who require top-tier tactical and combat equipment.

Short Description:
Springfield Armory is a historic American firearms manufacturer established in 1777 by General George Washington. Originally a government arsenal in Springfield, Massachusetts, it produced small arms for the military until its closure in 1968. The company is known for pioneering mass production techniques and interchangeable parts, influencing American manufacturing.

Today, Springfield Armory operates as a private, family-owned business, focusing on high-quality handguns and rifles for civilian, law enforcement, and military customers. Their product lineup includes popular models like the XD series, Hellcat micro-compact pistols, and 1911-style handguns, along with rifles designed for sport shooting and personal defense. The company emphasizes quality, innovation, and American heritage in its offerings, catering to firearm enthusiasts and competitive shooters.

Short Description:
The SAW-MAG™ offers for the first time a reliable and efficient AR-15 Drum Magazine. The SAW-Mag 150 round magazine for the AR15 pattern .223/5.56mm rifle and all weapons accepting AR-15 / AR15 / M16 magazines using the STANAG 4179 standard.

Designed to fit NATO standard (STANAG-4179) rifles, the SAW-MAG™ quickly converts a rifleman with a standard M4 into automatic support personnel. The flexibility of such force multiplication makes the SAW-MAG™ the most dominant accessory for the M4/M16/M27/HK416 family of weapons.

The SAW-MAG™ is a hybrid design externally constructed of thick walled long glass polymer and steel. This allows the magazine to have the durability to survive real world conditions. The hardened steel USGI tower allows it to fit into any weapon that accepts the 30 round standard magazine. All parts are from production tooling for precision and economics.

The SAW-MAG™ was designed to have the lowest operating drag due to friction. The ammunition is contained individually inside the drums on sprockets, each cartridge gets its own separate space, the ammunition is picked off the sprockets when they spin, not a typical high friction convergence found on cheaper designs. This is why our system does not require graphite lubrication to work. Instead of funneling the ammunition, the SAW-MAG™ uses a proprietary design that allows the ammunition to always be in a singular stream which results in a very low friction operation.

Caliber-5.56mm/.223
 Weight 4.9 lbs empty
 8.0 lbs loaded
 The Molle Carry Bag adds 0.8 lbs
 (SAW-MAG™ loaded+ HK416 =16lbs (M249 Unloaded 17lbs)
 Capacity-150 Rounds
 Color-Black only
 Body Material- Hi-impact Glass Nylon
 Tower-Heat Treated Steel to USGI specs
 Dimensions- 13.5″L x 3.25″W x 6.5″H

ASH Industries is committed to exceptional customer service and operational excellence. They work closely with clients across various industries, including automotive, medical, industrial, and consumer goods, to develop tailored solutions that meet specific project needs. Their focus on innovation and quality ensures reliable products and services for a diverse customer base.

Aspetto, based in Fredericksburg, Virginia, was founded in 2008 and specializes in designing, manufacturing, and distributing advanced ballistic clothing and tactical equipment. It is recognized as the first U.S. manufacturer of bullet-resistant clothing, merging fashion with protective technology for both civilian and government markets.

The company offers a range of products, including custom-tailored suits with integrated armor, bullet-resistant T-shirts, and tactical gear such as vests and helmets. Additionally, Aspetto provides cybersecurity training services to enhance defense against cyber threats.

Aspetto serves a variety of U.S. federal agencies, including the U.S. Air Force and Homeland Security, and has secured significant contracts for specialized tactical gear. The company has experienced substantial growth, with revenues projected to exceed $25 million, driven by its innovative approach to blending fashion with tactical design.

Initially, Bravo Concealment utilized CNC machining and CAD design to enhance production efficiency. Bravo Store Systems is a software company based in Las Vegas, Nevada, specializing in an all-in-one point of sale (POS) and business management platform for specialty retailers. Their solutions cater to pawnshops, gun stores, shooting ranges, buy/sell stores, and secondhand retailers. With over 1,500 customers and more than a decade of experience, Bravo aims to provide a seamless omnichannel retail experience through integrated systems.

The company's product suite features comprehensive POS software that includes real-time inventory tracking, barcode scanning, and purchase order management. Bravo also offers customer relationship management (CRM) tools for building customer profiles and running marketing campaigns. Additionally, their platform includes employee management capabilities, such as scheduling and payroll integration. A standout feature is their AI-powered pricing and valuation engine, which provides accurate item assessments and pricing recommendations based on real transaction data.

Bravo's platform supports various functionalities, including digital 4473 solutions for firearms retailers, eCommerce integrations, and robust reporting tools. The software is designed for scalability, ensuring that businesses can grow while maintaining high performance and customer support.

Short Description:
We currently make the Brella®, the highest waterproof performing rain jacket (20,000mm) in the industry in Realtree Edge camo at for $99, plus a microfleece Edge camo at 12,000mm.  No one can offer that performance at that MSRP.  The Brella is covered by 2 utility patents and a design patent.   We have a unique, unisex product and want to spread our value to the outdoor markets.

The Brella is a hybrid between a poncho and a rain coat and combines the best functions of each.  Being unisex and one size fits most, it is ideal for men, women and teens, covers a backpack, bow or rifle, guarantees non-restrictive upper body motion, is loose fitting and the hood retracts for better vision.  The Brella is used standalone when warm but in cooler climes it is the final layer over what you already wear.  We don't compete with any apparel partners you may have as we don't replace them, we complement them.  We can add 2 – 6+ extra hours of rain protection to a hunter in a tree stand, that's a great $99 investment.

Bridgford Foods Corporation is an American food company founded in 1932 by Hugh H. Bridgford in San Diego, California. Originally a retail meat market, the company has grown into a diversified food manufacturer and distributor, now headquartered in Dallas, Texas, with five production facilities across the U.S. These facilities focus on various product lines, supporting both retail and foodservice customers.

The company specializes in frozen bread dough and bakery products, meat snacks, and frozen foods. Bridgford pioneered the manufacture of frozen bread dough in 1962, and its product offerings include buttermilk biscuits, beef jerky, and shelf-stable sandwiches. Bridgford serves a wide range of customers, including supermarkets and foodservice providers, and has established significant contracts with institutions like the U.S. Military. With a commitment to quality and operational efficiency, Bridgford Foods continues to expand its product lines and maintain its legacy of innovation.

Burris Company, Inc. is an American manufacturer based in Greeley, Colorado, specializing in high-quality optical sighting systems for firearms and archery. Founded in 1971 by Don Burris, the company has a strong legacy of innovation and reliability in the optics industry, holding ISO 9001:2000 certification to ensure high product standards.

Burris offers a diverse range of products, including riflescopes, red-dot and reflex sights, archery optics, and mounting accessories. Burris focuses on delivering practical and durable optical solutions for hunters, tactical shooters, and archers, emphasizing functional improvements to meet real-world shooting challenges. Short Description:
Composite Fabrics of America (CFA) is a composite fabric weaving company based in Taylorsville, NC.    We weave Carbon Fiber and hybrid dry fabrics.   We are a wholly owned subsidiary of Schneider Mills.  Schneider is a 90 year old weaving company (also based in Taylorsville) with experts in every field of the weaving industry on staff.  Schneider currently operates over 500 looms producing fabrics for everything from military parachutes and uniforms to casual clothing.  The Schneider facility in Taylorsville has long been regarded by the textile industry as one of the most state of the art facilities in the country.  CFA has the luxury of tapping into this experience and talent bank in order to manufacture some of the highest quality Carbon Fiber and hybrid fabrics available on the market today. 
  
CFA is very much a custom weave house.   Whether our clients need a special weave style or a custom construction we can handle it.   We have the ability to weave everything from composite tapes as narrow as 3 inches to fabric as wide as 80 inches all with kevlar lenos to ensure fabric stability.   We pride ourselves on weaving first quality tapes and fabrics 100% of the time.   If it isn't first quality it doesn't leave our facility.

Short Description:
CORDURA® Advanced Fabrics, a brand owned by INVISTA, specializes in high-performance synthetic fiber-based fabrics primarily made from nylon 6,6 multi-filament fiber. Established in 1967, the brand is known for its durability, abrasion resistance, and tear strength, making it suitable for demanding applications like military gear, workwear, outdoor apparel, luggage, and backpacks.

The fabric portfolio includes various products such as classic CORDURA® fabrics, CORDURA® Truelock™, CORDURA® NYCO, CORDURA® Naturalle, and CORDURA Combat Wool™. These fabrics are engineered for long-lasting performance and sustainability, featuring innovations like solution-dyed fibers that minimize water, energy, and CO2 usage. CORDURA® serves a diverse customer base, including outdoor brands, military manufacturers, and fashion companies, with notable partnerships including Jansport®, Eastpak®, Carhartt®, Nike™, and the U.S. military. The company collaborates with textile partners worldwide to develop innovative fabric solutions tailored to various industry needs.

Short Description:
DFNDR Armor manufactures and sells advanced lightweight body armor to the military, law enforcement agencies and civilians who want proven lightweight armor. With a combination of trade secrets and patented armor technology, we innovate the lightest weight armor with the least trauma to the body in the industry.

After two decades of extensive next-generation body armor technology R&D and after producing hundreds of thousands of body armor units for the U.S. Military with our previous armor company; DFNDR Armor is now working exclusively with Honeywell as they have the highest grade fiber composites available for ballistic integration. We are leveraging one of the strongest synthetic fiber-based composite ever created, an Ultra High Molecular Weight Polyethylene (UHMWPE).

In May of 2016, the U.S. Army awarded our company an exclusive R&D contract to continue the advancement of lightweight armor development and lower traumas to the body for increased survivability for our soldiers. 

We currently manufacture and sell Level IIIA, III, III+ and Level IV armor systems; with numerous applications available for ballistic protection including body armor, vehicle, aircraft and marine craft. 

Our body armor products can be purchased at www.dfndr.com 

For unique and customized solutions please contact us at america@dfndrarmor.com

Short Description:
Dillon Precision Products, Inc. is a prominent American manufacturer of firearm ammunition reloading equipment, established in 1977 by Mike Dillon. Based in Scottsdale, Arizona, the company is recognized as the world's largest producer of reloading machines, known for its innovative progressive reloading technology that enhances output and efficiency.

The product lineup includes advanced reloading machines suitable for both handgun and rifle calibers, catering to hobbyists and professionals alike. Notable models include the RL550, XL750, Super 1050, RL1100, and CP2000, each designed to meet various reloading needs. Dillon Precision also provides a wide array of accessories and components, such as bullet feeders, reloading dies, and case gauges, creating a comprehensive reloading ecosystem.

Short Description:
Nihon Falcom Corporation is a prominent Japanese video game developer based in Tachikawa, Tokyo. Founded in March 1981 by Masayuki Katō, the company has played a significant role in shaping the action role-playing game (RPG) and Japanese RPG genres over its four-decade history. Falcom is recognized as one of the oldest active game studios in Japan and is often compared to major developers like Square Enix for its contributions to RPG development.

Falcom is best known for its iconic game series, including the *Ys series*, celebrated for its fast-paced combat, and *The Legend of Heroes series*, renowned for its deep storytelling. Other notable franchises include the *Dragon Slayer* and *Brandish* series. The company has pioneered innovations in game design, such as unique combat mechanics and the incorporation of vocals in game music. With a strong reputation among Japanese gamers, Falcom is increasingly gaining international recognition, particularly in Western markets, as interest in JRPGs continues to grow.

FTS Technologies is a global leader in flame surface treatment technologies that enhance adhesion properties on plastics, metals, and composite materials. With over 65 years of expertise, the company has developed advanced technologies such as the ATmaP® (Accelerated Thermo-molecular adhesion Process) and Cirqual™ burners, which are specifically designed for surface treatment applications.

Short Description:
Mesa Tactical's innovative, rugged and reliable tactical equipment is the choice for law enforcement, military  and the public to meet real world duty and personal protection requirements.

Mesa Tactical® was formed in 2003 to design and produce high quality tactical accessories for shotguns. The company's first products were cast aluminum telescoping stock adapters for Remington and Mossberg shotguns that allowed the installation of AR-15 stocks and grips on these platforms. 

From the beginning, Mesa Tactical's overriding design philosophy was to produce the most functional and robust accessories possible, even if it meant they would cost more. The company's primary focus was on law enforcement markets.

In early 2005, Mesa Tactical introduced its all-aluminum SureShell® on-gun shotshell carriers. Within a few years, the SureShell line became a favorite of law enforcement armorers across the country, who appreciated its thoughtful design and material toughness. By the beginning of 2013, Mesa Tactical had shipped over 50,000 SureShell shell carriers.

Another departure was in late 2010, when Mesa Tactical began shipping its first injection molded part, the Urbino® tactical stock for the Benelli M4. Urbino stocks have since been introduced for a variety of Remington and Benelli platforms. 

Mesa Tactical's largest customers include both the Los Angeles Police Department and Sheriff's Office; Orange County Sheriff's Departments in both California and Florida; FBI and Department of Homeland Security. Looking forward, Mesa Tactical will continue to develop innovative, robust accessories for tactical shotguns, and will soon introduce products for carbines and other rifle platforms.

Mesa Tactical's products include stocks, forends, shotshell carriers, scope mounts and Picatinny rails. For more information on the company's line of professional-grade products, contact 1775 Kuenzli St, Reno, NV, 89502 • Tel: 714-545-3332 • or visit www.mesatactical.com

ADS, Inc. (Atlantic Diving Supply) is a Virginia Beach-based company founded in 1997 by Luke Hillier. Initially created to support the military diving community, it has grown into a leading contractor for the U.S. Department of Defense (DoD) and a key provider of equipment and support solutions for the U.S. Armed Forces and various government entities.

The company specializes in logistics and supply chain solutions, offering a wide array of products including aerospace equipment, military clothing, C5ISR products, and medical supplies. ASKION Biobanking is a German company based in Gera, Thuringia, specializing in biobanking and cryogenic storage solutions within the medical devices and equipment industry. The company employs between 50 and 99 people and generates estimated revenues of $1 million to $5 million.

Short Description:
The American Translators Association (ATA) is the largest professional association for translators and interpreters in the United States, founded in 1959. With over 10,000 members from more than 100 countries, ATA is a not-for-profit organization that promotes the translation and interpreting professions. It is governed by an elected Board of Directors and relies on volunteer participation from its members.

ATA's mission includes advancing the profession, establishing standards of competence and ethics, and providing professional development opportunities. The association offers a certification program recognized as a key industry standard, along with workshops, conferences, and webinars to enhance members' skills. ATA also publishes *The ATA Chronicle*, a journal that covers industry news and trends, and maintains a directory of qualified professionals to connect clients with translators and interpreters. Through partnerships with international organizations, ATA works to promote the translation and interpreting fields on a global scale.

Short Description:
Established in 2004 in Konya, Turkey, BARAK ARMS has become one of the country's leading firearms manufacturers. With its experience and knowledge gained in all areas of the arms industry since the 1970s, the company was among the first shotgun manufacturers in Turkey. BARAK ARMS is committed to producing weapons that fully comply with TSE, ATF, SAAMI, and CIP standards.

BARAK ARMS gained international recognition after producing Turkey's first 12-gauge mag-fed shotgun, commonly known as the BR99. This success led the company to develop 20-caliber and .410 caliber versions of the same model, making important contributions to the defense and weapons industry in Turkey.

BARAK ARMS is dedicated to exceeding expectations in the global market and is committed to presenting innovative firsts to the sector by investing heavily in R&D activities. The company carries out all production processes, including barrel and receiver production and assembly, in its own 2000 square meter factory. BARAK ARMS uses 7075 aluminum for the receiver, lower, and upper, and 4140 steel for barrel production. Additionally, BARAK ARMS has a FACILITY SECURITY CLEARANCE CERTIFICATE issued by the Turkish Ministry of Defense.

BARAK ARMS has successfully passed various rigorous tests in America, Canada, England, and many European countries, proving its commitment to quality.

Born Primitive is a veteran-owned fitness and tactical apparel company founded in 2014 by Bear Handlon and Mallory Riley. The brand focuses on high-performance clothing designed for athletes of all sizes and skill levels, emphasizing support during physical and mental challenges. The company offers a wide range of products, including workout apparel and tactical clothing. Their fitness gear is tailored for intense physical activity, while the tactical line is rigorously tested for durability and functionality in demanding environments. Key offerings include performance workout gear for men and women, base layer tops, and tactical pants, all crafted to meet the needs of fitness enthusiasts and tactical professionals.

Born Primitive has built a strong community of athletes, military personnel, and individuals who resonate with its disciplined and patriotic lifestyle. Based in Virginia Beach, Virginia, the company has grown significantly, achieving approximately $18.4 million in revenue and employing around 95 people. The founders' experiences have played a crucial role in shaping the brand's identity and success.

Short Description:
Buderus Edelstahl GmbH is a prominent German manufacturer of high-quality special steels, established in 1731 by Johann Wilhelm Buderus I. Based in Wetzlar, Germany, the company specializes in producing a variety of steel products, including tool steel, engineering steel, open-die and closed-die forgings, as well as hot-rolled and cold-rolled strips. Buderus Edelstahl manages the entire production process, ensuring high quality across various dimensions.

With a workforce of around 1,130 employees, including over 50 apprentices, Buderus Edelstahl produces approximately 300,000 tons of crude steel annually. The company generated sales of about EUR 362 million in the fiscal year 2023/24, with more than 50% of its sales coming from exports. Its products primarily serve industries such as light vehicles, mechanical engineering, truck manufacturing, and wind energy. Buderus Edelstahl is recognized for its commitment to innovation and quality, continuously improving its production processes and supply chain efficiency. In 2024, the company was acquired by Mutares to enhance its capabilities and support future growth.

Byrna Technologies Inc. is a technology company based in Andover, Massachusetts, focused on designing, developing, and manufacturing less-lethal personal security devices and munitions. The company serves a diverse customer base, including civilians, law enforcement, military, corrections, private security professionals, and private investigators. Byrna aims to provide a safe and effective alternative to traditional firearms, allowing users to protect themselves and others without using deadly force.

The product lineup features shoulder-fired launchers, handheld personal security devices, self-defense pistols like the Byrna SD and Byrna SD XL, and rifles such as the Mission 4. Byrna also offers non-lethal ammunition, self-defense aerosol sprays branded as Byrna Bad Guy Repellent, and various accessories including holsters and personal safety alarms. Byrna's products are marketed under several brand names and are available through e-commerce platforms, dealers, and distributors in multiple regions, including the United States and South Africa. 

With over 20 years in the industry, Byrna Technologies is recognized for its commitment to customer service and product quality, holding an A+ rating from the Better Business Bureau.

Short Description:
Colt's Manufacturing Company LLC is a historic American firearms manufacturer founded in 1855 by Samuel Colt. The company is known for pioneering the revolver, which allowed multiple rounds to be fired without reloading, significantly influencing firearm technology and warfare. Headquartered in Hartford, Connecticut, Colt is a subsidiary of the Colt CZ Group and has played a key role in the development of firearms, particularly revolvers and military rifles.

Colt's product lineup includes iconic firearms such as the Colt Walker, Colt Single Action Army, and Colt Python revolvers. The company is also recognized for the Colt M1911 semi-automatic pistol, a long-serving handgun for military and law enforcement. Additionally, Colt produces a variety of military rifles, including the M16 and M4 carbine, as well as shotguns and machine guns. Colt serves a diverse customer base, including military, law enforcement, and civilian markets, and has a legacy of innovation and resilience in the firearms industry.

Holosun is a private company founded in 2013 and headquartered in City of Industry, California. It specializes in designing and manufacturing small arms accessories, particularly optics and tactical equipment for shooting, hunting, law enforcement, and military applications. The company is known for its innovative and affordable firearm optics, including red dot sights, holographic sights, thermal sights, and tactical lights.

A key feature of Holosun's products is their "shake awake" technology, which activates the optic when it detects movement and powers it down after inactivity, enhancing battery life. Many of their optics also utilize solar-powered systems to extend battery life further. Holosun emphasizes long battery life, reticle customization, and the latest advancements in laser and LED technology, making their products appealing to a wide range of users, from civilian shooters to military personnel. 

With manufacturing primarily in China and a corporate structure that connects the U.S. and Canada, Holosun aims to provide duty-ready equipment at competitive prices, positioning itself as a cost-effective alternative in the optics market.

Short Description:
Faxon Firearms is an American firearms manufacturer established in 2012, building on a family legacy that began in 1978 with machining and deep hole drilling. The company specializes in producing high-quality firearm components and complete firearms, utilizing decades of expertise in precision drilling to manufacture barrels and other parts in-house.

The product lineup includes proprietary rifle barrels, such as the "gunner" and "pencil" profiles, designed for AR-style firearms. Faxon also offers a range of rifles, including AR-15, AR-9, AR-10, .22LR, and the new X7 bolt-action rifles. Their FX-19 pistol line is compatible with Glock standards, showcasing their commitment to innovation. The ARAK21, their initial firearm, is a convertible rifle platform that reflects their advanced machining capabilities.

Faxon Firearms caters to firearm enthusiasts, custom builders, and professionals who seek durable and high-performance products. Their reputation for quality and precision extends internationally, appealing to customers who value American craftsmanship in tactical and sporting firearms.

Aguila Ammunition, founded in 1961 and based in Cuernavaca, Mexico, is a leading manufacturer of rimfire, centerfire, and shotshell ammunition. The company is known for its commitment to precision and reliability, using premium raw materials to produce high-quality ammunition for various markets, including self-defense, recreational shooting, hunting, law enforcement, and military applications. Notable innovations include the Minishell, which enhances shotgun capacity and reduces recoil.

TXAT LLC serves as the exclusive master distributor for Aguila Ammunition in North America and other international markets. Established in 2011, TXAT specializes in distributing high-quality brands and offers services such as strategic marketing, operational planning, and logistics. They are fully licensed to supply ammunition, firearms, and tactical gear to government, military, and law enforcement sectors, ensuring efficient delivery and strong market presence for Aguila products. Together, Aguila and TXAT provide a comprehensive solution from manufacturing to global distribution, focusing on quality and customer service.

Short Description:
Allied Machine & Engineering is a family-owned company based in Dover, Ohio, established in 1941. The company specializes in designing and manufacturing advanced holemaking and finishing cutting tool systems. They provide precision tooling solutions aimed at achieving the lowest cost per hole for various metal-cutting applications, including drilling, reaming, threading, and boring.

Their extensive product range features drilling and reaming tools, boring tools, threadmaking tools, burnishing tools, toolholders, and specialty tools made from materials like polycrystalline diamond, carbide, and high-speed steel. Allied Machine serves a variety of industries, such as aerospace, automotive, renewable energy, and medical, focusing on addressing complex metal-cutting challenges with innovative and efficient solutions.

The company emphasizes customer support through precision engineering and interactive digital tools, helping clients optimize their tooling solutions and manufacturing processes. Leadership remains within the founding Stokey family, with a commitment to growth and innovation in the industry.

Short Description:
Atlas Fibre is a prominent North American manufacturer and supplier of thermoset composite laminate materials and precision machining services for advanced plastics. With manufacturing facilities in the United States and India, the company produces over 5 million pounds of thermoset composites annually, supported by a large inventory valued at over $12 million in their 120,000-square-foot warehouse in Northbrook, Illinois.

The product range includes NEMA-grade thermoset composite laminates, such as XX and XXX paper-based phenolic grades, known for their durability, electrical insulation, and mechanical strength. Atlas Fibre also offers precision machining services with a fleet of over 65 CNC milling and turning machines, allowing for the fabrication of complex components tailored to customer specifications. The company serves various industries, including aerospace and automotive, and is committed to quality, holding certifications like AS9100D and ISO 9001:2015, as well as being ITAR registered for defense-related applications.

Short Description:
Aviation Specialties Unlimited (ASU) is a leader in aviation night vision technology, established in 1995 by former AH-64 Apache pilot Mike Atwood in Boise, Idaho. The company specializes in high-quality night vision goggles (NVGs), training programs, and custom aircraft modifications for both rotor-wing and fixed-wing aircraft. ASU was a pioneer in FAA-approved NVG use for first responders and law enforcement, achieving Part 135 operational approval in 1999.

ASU offers a range of services, including authorized sales of NVGs from leading brands, specialized NVG training for safe operation, and custom modifications for aircraft that comply with various aviation authorities. The company also provides inspection, service, and repair for night vision goggles with quick turnaround times. ASU serves a diverse clientele, including emergency medical services, military, law enforcement agencies, and various government organizations. With a strong federal contracting history and ongoing global expansion, ASU is committed to innovation and safety in night vision aviation technology.

BGH Edelstahlwerke GmbH is a German steel manufacturing company with over 550 years of experience. It specializes in producing stainless steels, tool steels, nickel, and special alloys. The company utilizes a fully integrated production process, handling everything from melting to finished products like wire, rod, and open-die forgings, with sizes ranging from less than one-tenth of a millimeter to over one meter.

The product portfolio includes high-quality stainless steels and nickel alloys used across various industries, including sustainable energy, mobility, medical technology, environmental technology, and shipbuilding. BGH provides medical stainless steels and alloys for surgical instruments, dental tools, and binding wire, as well as austenitic special steels with approvals for forgings in shipbuilding. With a workforce of 201 to 500 employees and estimated revenue between $11 million and $271.6 million, BGH Edelstahlwerke GmbH plays a significant role in the steel manufacturing sector, focusing on quality and innovation to meet global customer needs.

Short Description:
Blaser Swisslube is a family-owned Swiss company established in 1936 and based in Hasle-Rüegsau, Switzerland. It has grown from a regional business into a global leader in the development and manufacturing of high-quality lubricants, particularly cutting and grinding fluids for the metalworking industry. The company employs around 600 people worldwide, with a significant presence in about 60 countries across Europe, America, and Asia.

The core offerings of Blaser Swisslube include specialized metalworking fluids, known as "liquid tools," designed to enhance machining processes. These products aim to improve quality, reliability, cost-effectiveness, and productivity. The company also provides extensive support through its team of sales engineers and machining specialists, ensuring customers can maximize the potential of their machine tools. With a diverse clientele of over 100,000 customers, Blaser Swisslube serves various sectors, including industrial, construction, and transport applications. The company is committed to innovation and customer collaboration, supported by its dedicated Technology Center for research and development.

CamelBak Products, LLC is an outdoor equipment company based in Petaluma, California, founded in 1989 by Michael Eidson. The company is known for pioneering the hydration pack category, creating hands-free hydration solutions inspired by Eidson’s experience as an emergency medical technician during a long-distance bike race.

CamelBak's core offerings include hydration packs, which are backpack-style carriers with built-in water reservoirs, hoses, and bite valves, as well as taste-free, leak-resistant water bottles. The product line has expanded to include protective gear and other outdoor equipment. CamelBak serves a diverse customer base, including mountain bikers, hikers, and military and law enforcement personnel, providing specialized hydration solutions for tactical use. The company has a strong presence in the military sector, with government contracts accounting for a significant portion of its sales.

CamelBak focuses on delivering reliable and innovative hydration products that enhance performance and convenience for active users, making it a leading brand in hydration solutions for outdoor recreation and tactical applications.

The company is known for its innovative and high-quality knives designed for everyday carry, professional use, tactical applications, and outdoor activities. CRKT collaborates with renowned knife designers, allowing it to offer a diverse range of cutting tools that blend creativity, functionality, and affordability.

Connecticut Spring & Stamping (CSS) is a precision manufacturer based in Farmington, Connecticut, with over 80 years of experience. Founded in 1939, the company specializes in metal springs, progressive stampings, fineblanked stampings, machined components, and assemblies. CSS offers a diverse product portfolio, featuring compression, extension, torsion, flat springs, and wire forms made from materials like stainless steel, titanium, and copper alloys. Gerdau is a prominent multinational steel company founded in 1901 in Porto Alegre, Brazil. It has evolved from a small nail manufacturing business into the largest producer of long steel in the Americas and a key player in the global steel market, producing around 13 million tons of steel annually as of 2023. The company operates mini mills, integrated mills, and direct reduced iron plants, with a significant focus on sustainability, as approximately 71% of its steel production comes from recycled scrap.

Gerdau specializes in long steel products, including rebar, wire rods, structural steel, and special steel. Its flagship product, GG 50 rebar, is well-regarded in Brazil. The company serves various industries such as construction, automotive, machinery, and manufacturing. With a strong presence in Brazil and North America, Gerdau has expanded internationally through acquisitions and partnerships in several countries, catering to a diverse customer base that includes construction companies and industrial manufacturers.

Hawke Optics is a family-run company based in Woodbridge, Suffolk, United Kingdom, with over 40 years of experience in the sports optics industry. The company operates in more than 60 countries, including offices in the United States and Canada, and has been expanding its global presence since entering the U.S. market in 2007.

Hawke Optics specializes in designing and manufacturing a variety of precision optical products for outdoor sports and hunting. Their product range includes riflescopes, binoculars, spotting scopes, rangefinders, red dot scopes, lasers, LED lights, and various accessories. Known for their durability and precision, Hawke's products are tailored to meet the needs of hunters and sport shooters, supported by a No Fault Lifetime Warranty that highlights their commitment to customer satisfaction.

Heckler & Koch USA is the American division of the renowned German firearms manufacturer, Heckler & Koch GmbH, which was founded in 1949. The company has a strong heritage in precision engineering and firearms innovation, evolving into a global leader in military and law enforcement small arms. With manufacturing facilities in Columbus, Georgia; Newington, New Hampshire; and Ashburn, Virginia, Heckler & Koch USA is dedicated to serving the U.S. market with high-quality, precision-engineered firearms.

The company offers a diverse range of firearms, including assault rifles like the G3 and HK33, submachine guns such as the iconic MP5, and machine guns like the HK21. Additionally, Heckler & Koch USA produces pistols, sniper rifles, and other specialized weapons tailored for military and law enforcement needs. The company primarily serves military forces, law enforcement agencies, security professionals, and, to a limited extent, the civilian market, focusing on precision manufacturing, innovation, and reliability.

Hero's Pride is a family-owned manufacturer that specializes in duty gear, patches, and uniform accessories for law enforcement, public safety, and military personnel. Established in 1981, the company has grown significantly and is recognized as one of the fastest-growing brands in law enforcement gear. They offer three main lines of duty gear—AIRTEK®, Ballistic, and Tactical—designed to be ultra-lightweight and focused on comfort and health for first responders.

In addition to duty gear, Hero's Pride is known for its custom patches and emblems, which feature sharp lettering, clean stitching, and vibrant colors. The company provides free artwork assistance and quick quotes, ensuring high-quality products that reflect the pride and dedication of first responders. Hero's Pride distributes its products through a nationwide network of authorized dealers and online retailers, emphasizing exceptional service and support.

Recently acquired by World Emblem, Hero's Pride combines its legacy craftsmanship with advanced technology, enhancing its capabilities and ensuring high-performance, durable products delivered efficiently. The company remains dedicated to serving law enforcement and first responders with innovative solutions and a strong family-oriented culture.

Hesco is a leading manufacturer of the HESCO MIL Defensive Barrier, a wire-mesh gabion system designed for quick deployment in military, security, and environmental applications. Founded in 1989 by Jimi Heselden, the company created the "Concertainer," a collapsible, earth-filled barrier system used globally for flood control and military fortifications.

Hesco specializes in engineering and manufacturing earth-filled defensive barriers and related protective systems. Their products include modular barriers for blast protection, environmental and security barriers for border security and flood protection, and ballistic resistant armor plates. The company also offers technical support and training for the proper deployment of their systems. With multiple factories worldwide, including a Centre of Excellence in Poland, Hesco ensures a reliable supply of its innovative solutions to protect critical assets in various sectors, including military operations and disaster relief.

Hogue Inc. is an American company based in Henderson, Nevada, founded in 1968 by former LAPD officer Guy Hogue. Initially focused on crafting custom handgun grips, the company has expanded its offerings to include a wide range of firearm accessories, knives, and related products.

Hogue's core products feature high-quality handgun grips made from rubber and wood, designed for comfort and control across at least 16 different handgun brands. They also produce ergonomically designed rifle stocks, holsters, and AR components. In 2010, Hogue introduced a line of knives that showcase their expertise in ergonomics and precision manufacturing. These knives are known for their innovative features and are issued to all branches of the U.S. Military, as well as being manufactured for major firearm brands like Heckler & Koch and SIG Sauer.

As a family-owned business, Hogue Inc. emphasizes American manufacturing quality and craftsmanship. Their products are widely used by law enforcement, military personnel, competitive shooters, and firearm enthusiasts, reflecting a commitment to superior performance and design.

Short Description:
40 years. Three generations. These are numbers we don't stand behind casually. Together, they begin to paint a picture, one that—when broken down to brass tacks—is simply comprised of hard work day in and day out. But in the early spring of 2018, we zoomed out and began to realize that the Index brand simply didn't ladder up to our core values. While they served us well for decades, our customers expect us to stay ahead of the curling wave of industry trends, and we needed an updated, modern brand and website to communicate just that.
  From the aerospace to medical device industries and even all the way down to the textile industry, we've impacted supply chains. At the end of the day, though, we share one major attribute with our customers: We are the working class. Our histories and legacies are deeply woven together into a blue collar narrative. Even though our customers span an incredibly wide range of industries, we're proud to have fostered personal relationships with many of them—a significant number of them have been steadily built for 40 years. We use these relationships as our guiding light at every turn in our decision making process from the top down, and so it was only natural that it took a front seat during the brand refresh conversation and is now fully reflected in our name.
  This brand strategy serves as a 10k' view of what we do. Simple, straightforward, no minced words is both who we are and what we do. Our business is driven by our customers, and not what any gut feeling says is right or wrong. That's it, that's all.
