IWI US, Inc. is the American branch of Israel Weapon Industries (IWI), a well-established firearms manufacturer with a history dating back to 1933. The company specializes in designing, producing, and distributing advanced small arms systems tailored for the demanding conditions faced by the Israel Defense Forces (IDF). IWI US offers a diverse range of military-grade and civilian firearms, including iconic models like the UZI®, TAVOR®, and GALIL ACE®. These products are known for their reliability and combat effectiveness.

As part of the SK Group, IWI US maintains a strong commitment to quality, with its firearms manufactured to meet military standards and ISO certifications. The company has successfully entered the civilian market, catering to shooting sports enthusiasts and hunters. IWI US collaborates closely with the IDF for ongoing research and development, ensuring its firearms evolve to meet contemporary security challenges. The brand is recognized for its innovation and has gained a solid reputation among military, law enforcement, and civilian customers in the U.S. and beyond.

Katadyn Group is a Swiss-based company that specializes in self-sufficient nutrition and drinking water supply solutions. With over 90 years of experience, the company operates under the principle of "Sustaining life no matter where." It provides safe and sustainable hydration and nutrition products for various sectors, including outdoor, marine, tactical, emergency preparedness, humanitarian, and commercial.

Headquartered in Kemptthal, Switzerland, Katadyn Group employs around 200 people across its subsidiaries in Europe, Asia, and the United States. The company is recognized as a global leader in portable water treatment and nutrition solutions, bolstered by its acquisition of specialized brands like Trek’n Eat, AlpineAire Foods, and Optimus. Its product offerings include reliable water treatment systems, healthy meal options, and high-quality cooking equipment, all designed to meet the needs of outdoor enthusiasts, military personnel, and organizations focused on emergency preparedness.

Short Description:
KelTec is an American firearms manufacturer based in Cocoa, Florida, founded in 1991 by George Kellgren. Initially a precision CNC parts supplier, the company began producing its own firearms in 1995, starting with semi-automatic pistols. KelTec is known for its innovative designs that prioritize reliability, affordability, and compactness.

The company's first firearm, the P-11, was the first polymer-framed 9mm pistol designed for concealed carry. Other notable products include the P-32 pocket pistol and the PF9 micro-compact 9mm pistol. KelTec also produces rifles and shotguns, such as the SUB-2000 folding carbine and the KSG bullpup shotgun, both recognized for their unique features and functionality.

KelTec employs around 300 people and emphasizes innovation aligned with American values. The company serves a diverse customer base, including concealed carry permit holders, law enforcement, and firearm enthusiasts who appreciate compact and reliable firearms.

Kimber Mfg., Inc. is an American firearms manufacturer that specializes in high-quality M1911 pistols, rifles, and revolvers. Founded in 1979 in Clackamas, Oregon, Kimber initially focused on producing accurate .22 caliber rimfire rifles and quickly built a reputation for precision craftsmanship. Over the years, the company expanded its offerings to include specialized 1911 pistols, bolt-action rifles, and a selection of revolvers.

Kimber is particularly renowned for its line of 1911-style pistols, which are favored by competitive shooters, law enforcement, and military personnel for their blend of traditional craftsmanship and modern engineering. The company also produces bolt-action rifles known for their accuracy and classic styling, along with a variety of revolvers. Kimber's firearms are trusted by notable customers, including the USA Shooting Team and the U.S. Marines Special Operations Command, highlighting the brand's commitment to reliability and performance.

Nighthawk Custom is an American firearms manufacturer based in Berryville, Arkansas, established in 2004. The company specializes in high-end custom firearms, particularly the M1911 pistol platform, and also produces rifles, revolvers, shotguns, and tactical knives. Nighthawk Custom is recognized for its craftsmanship and quality, serving a diverse clientele that includes competition shooters, military personnel, law enforcement, and self-defense customers.

The philosophy of “One Gun, One Gunsmith” guides Nighthawk Custom, ensuring that each firearm is hand-built by a single craftsman who oversees the entire assembly process. This approach emphasizes accountability and pride in craftsmanship, with the gunsmith’s initials engraved inside each gun. Nighthawk offers a range of customizable 1911 models, including the Talon and Dominator series, allowing customers to tailor features to their preferences. The company also operates an in-house machine shop for quality control and precision in manufacturing. 

Nighthawk Custom has expanded its offerings to include custom shotguns and tactical knives, and it serves as the exclusive U.S. importer for Korth revolvers and Cosmi shotguns. The company continues to grow, investing in its facilities and workforce to meet the demands of its discerning customer base.

Serving industries such as automotive, aerospace, electronics, and medical technology, TRUMPF is dedicated to advancing manufacturing processes through innovation and digital connectivity.

3D Systems Corporation is a technology company founded in 1986 by Chuck Hull, the inventor of stereolithography, the first commercial 3D printing technology. Based in Rock Hill, South Carolina, the company is a leader in additive manufacturing solutions, serving a global market across various regions including the Americas, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and Asia-Pacific.

The company offers a wide range of 3D printers, including those for plastic, metal, dental, and jewelry applications, as well as print materials like metals and plastics. 3D Systems also provides on-demand manufacturing services, digital design tools, and software solutions through its subsidiary Oqton. Its products cater to diverse industries such as aerospace, automotive, healthcare, and consumer technology, supporting applications from prototyping to production.

With a history of innovation, 3D Systems has developed key technologies in 3D printing and emphasizes sustainability through initiatives like recycling programs. The company serves a variety of users, from professional manufacturers to educational institutions, offering solutions that enhance design and production workflows.

Accuracy International is a British firearms manufacturer established in 1980 by a group of international target shooters, including Olympic gold medalist Malcolm Cooper. Headquartered in Portsmouth, England, the company designs, develops, tests, and manufactures high-precision sniper rifles and related equipment, adhering to ISO 9001:2015 quality standards.

The company specializes in hand-built precision sniper rifles, anti-materiel rifles, and civilian competition rifles. Its products are recognized globally, with adoption by military and law enforcement agencies in over 70 countries. Notable rifle series include the L96A1, Arctic Warfare series, and L115A3. Accuracy International also offers accessories, ammunition, and user training services. The company has expanded its market reach and product range since being rescued from financial difficulties in 2005, and it has received accolades such as The Queen’s Award for Enterprise for International Trade in 2015.

Angel Armor is a U.S.-based company founded in 2013 by the Richardson brothers, located in Fort Collins, Colorado. The company specializes in advanced ballistic protection solutions for law enforcement, military personnel, and security professionals. As a family-run business, Angel Armor is dedicated to enhancing the safety and performance of first responders and federal agents through premium body armor, ballistic plates, and vehicle armor.

Their product offerings include ballistic plates and panels made from proprietary blends of materials like Kevlar, designed for modular attachments. The body armor features patented technologies such as the QuadCore® Belt System, which provides innovative weight distribution for improved comfort and maneuverability. Additionally, Angel Armor manufactures vehicle armor solutions that offer comprehensive protection for law enforcement and military vehicles.

Angel Armor's mission is to protect and preserve the lives of first responders and their families, driven by innovation and feedback from end-users. The company emphasizes quality by manufacturing its products domestically in the United States, ensuring reliable and high-quality protective gear for those who serve in dangerous roles.

Apex Mills is a specialty textile manufacturer based in the U.S., founded in 1943. Initially a reseller of bridal and apparel fabrics, the company has evolved into a leading producer of warp knit fabrics for industrial and technical applications. With manufacturing facilities in Woolwine, Virginia, and Graham, North Carolina, Apex Mills emphasizes American-made quality and efficient customer solutions.

The company specializes in custom-engineered warp knit textiles, collaborating closely with engineers and product designers to meet specific requirements across various industries, including aerospace, defense, medical, and military sectors. Apex Mills is known for its advanced textile solutions, such as multi-layer insulation fabrics used in NASA missions, and is committed to innovation in smart textiles that incorporate circuitry and sensors for diverse applications. Their facility in Graham operates 24/5 and focuses on sustainability and operational efficiency, implementing energy-saving projects to enhance productivity. Apex Mills serves notable clients, including the Department of Defense and NASA, reflecting its strong reputation for quality and reliability in the technical textile market.

ARCH is a contract manufacturing company based in Michigan, specializing in advanced precision machining and engineering. Founded in 2011, it serves the medical, aerospace and defense, energy, and high-tech industrial markets. By consolidating multiple precision manufacturers, ARCH aims to reduce manufacturing costs, optimize component performance, and mitigate supply chain risks.

The company offers a range of services, including design-for-manufacturability, prototyping, on-site application testing, program management, and customized manufacturing solutions. Aurora Material Solutions is a prominent manufacturer and supplier of advanced polymer and engineered PVC compounds. Established in 1997, the company specializes in custom flexible and rigid thermoplastic solutions. With six manufacturing sites across the United States and Canada, Aurora has become a key player in the polymer compounding industry, focusing on safety, quality, and automation in its state-of-the-art facilities.

The company offers a wide range of thermoplastic products, including flexible and rigid PVC compounds, thermoplastic olefins, elastomers, and low-smoke zero-halogen compounds for cable jacketing. Their branded product lines, such as AuroraClean™, AuroraFlex™, and AuroraGuard™, cater to various applications, from cleaning extrusion machinery to providing flame-retardant materials. Aurora Material Solutions serves diverse industries, including construction, automotive, and consumer goods, and is dedicated to delivering high-quality products and exceptional customer service. Team Wendy is a Cleveland-based company founded in 1997 by Dan T. Moore in memory of his daughter, Wendy Moore, who passed away from a traumatic brain injury. The company is dedicated to enhancing head protection through innovative design and reliable customer service, focusing on preventing TBIs for military personnel, law enforcement, search and rescue teams, and adventure sports enthusiasts.

The company launched its first product, a ski helmet with a proprietary Zorbium® foam liner, in 1998. Since then, Team Wendy has expanded its offerings to include advanced helmet liner systems like the Zorbium® Action Pad (ZAP™) and the EPIC® Combat Helmet Liner System. Their tactical bump helmet, the EXFIL® Carbon, features the CAM FIT™ Retention System for optimal fit and weight distribution. Team Wendy's products are widely used by the U.S. military and other tactical operators around the world, reflecting a strong commitment to quality and performance. The company is part of Avon Protection, enhancing its capabilities in protective systems for military and first responders.

B&T USA is a Florida-based manufacturer and designer of advanced firearms, suppressors, and tactical weapon systems. Operating under license from B&T AG Switzerland, the company has established itself as a leader in the design and manufacture of complete weapon systems for professional operators, including police, special forces, and elite military units worldwide.

The product lineup features the APC (Advanced Police Carbine) series, including PRO variants, the 9mm USW® (Universal Service Weapon), and USW conversion kits. These systems are designed for precision and reliability in demanding conditions. B&T USA also produces a range of firearm accessories, such as modular accessory mounts, tactical rail systems, optic mounts, handguards, handgrips, and buttstocks. The company emphasizes high-quality standards through Swiss precision manufacturing, now executed in the USA, and maintains a robust quality assurance program to ensure product performance and reliability. 

In addition to manufacturing, B&T USA supplies domestic law enforcement and military markets with products from other global brands and is involved in the import and export of small arms, ammunition, and related accessories.

Short Description:
Barrett Firearms Manufacturing, Inc. is a Tennessee-based company that specializes in designing and manufacturing large-caliber firearms and ammunition. Founded in 1982 by Ronnie G. Barrett, the company is known for pioneering the semi-automatic .50 BMG rifle, starting with the iconic Model 82. Barrett's rifles are recognized for their precision and military-grade quality, serving civilian sport shooters, law enforcement, and military clients in over 80 countries.

Headquartered in Murfreesboro, Tennessee, Barrett is a leader in large-caliber rifle design, with a product range that includes the M82A1, M107, MK22 rifles, and the .416 Barrett cartridge. The company is expanding its operations with a significant investment in a new 250,000-square-foot headquarters and technology campus in Rutherford County, which will enhance its manufacturing capabilities. Barrett's commitment to quality is reflected in its ISO 9001:2015 certification, ensuring high standards in firearm and ammunition design and manufacturing.

Benchmade Knife Company is a prominent American knife manufacturer established in 1979 by Les de Asis in California. Originally named Bali-Song, the company focused on creating high-quality butterfly knives. It later changed its name to Pacific Cutlery Corporation in the early 1980s and became Benchmade in 1988, reflecting its commitment to combining handmade craftsmanship with factory precision. Headquartered in Oregon City, Oregon, Benchmade operates a modern, LEED Gold certified facility that emphasizes quality control and advanced manufacturing technology.

The company offers a diverse range of knives, including butterfly knives, folding knives, fixed blades, and automatic options, catering to outdoor enthusiasts, hunters, military personnel, and everyday users. Benchmade is recognized for its patented Axis lock mechanism, enhancing safety and usability. The knives are crafted from premium materials and designed by skilled artisans, ensuring durability and precision. Benchmade's philosophy centers on producing finely crafted knives that balance artistry and efficiency, appealing to customers who value high-quality, reliable tools.

Beverly Knits Inc. is a family-owned textile manufacturing company based in Gastonia, North Carolina, founded in 1980. It has become one of the largest circular knitters in the United States, specializing in high-quality knit fabrics made primarily from polyester and other fibers. The company operates as a vertically integrated manufacturer through its various business units, including Beverly Knits, Altus Finishing, Creative Fabrics, Creative Ticking, and Hemingway Sewing Solutions.

Beverly Knits serves diverse markets such as performance wear, athletic footwear, intimate apparel, outdoor products, and medical applications. Their extensive manufacturing capabilities include 250 circular knitting machines and facilities covering over 450,000 square feet. The company offers a range of products, including greige goods, finished fabrics, and complete sewn garments, while emphasizing sustainability through the use of recycled materials. With a commitment to innovation and responsiveness, Beverly Knits is a trusted partner for various industries seeking high-performance textile solutions.

Bounce Imaging is a technology company based in Buffalo, New York, that focuses on developing low-cost, user-friendly 360-degree imaging and robotics systems. Founded in 2012 at the Harvard Innovation Laboratory and MIT, the company was inspired by the need for better tools during search and rescue operations, particularly after the 2010 Haiti earthquake.

The company's core product line includes tactical 360-degree camera systems designed to enhance situational awareness in hazardous or confined environments. These compact and rugged cameras allow first responders and military personnel to safely assess dangerous areas from a distance, reducing risks associated with entering unsafe spaces. Bounce Imaging's products are utilized by over 450 law enforcement agencies, first responders, and elite teams within the U.S. Department of Defense, emphasizing the importance of reliable imaging technology in emergency and tactical scenarios.

Browning is a historic American company founded in 1878 in Ogden, Utah, by brothers John Moses Browning and Matthew Sandefur Browning. Known for its innovative firearms design, Browning has a legacy rooted in the work of John Moses Browning, who holds 128 patents and is recognized as a significant firearms inventor. The company became a formal entity in 1927 and is now a subsidiary of FN Herstal.

Browning offers a wide range of products, including high-quality rifles, shotguns, and pistols, such as the A-Bolt and Hi-Power models. In addition to firearms, the company provides fishing gear, archery equipment, knives, gun safes, and outdoor apparel. Browning serves hunters, sport shooters, and outdoor enthusiasts, emphasizing precision and reliability in its offerings. The company’s influence extends through its licensed products, which have been manufactured by other major firearms brands, showcasing its strong presence in the industry.

Check-Mate Industries, Inc. is a manufacturer with over 40 years of experience, specializing in tool & die, metal stampings, and assemblies. Founded in 1972, the company serves various industries, including aerospace, automotive, firearms, cosmetics, medical, and military sectors. It is recognized for its high-precision tooling and assembly services, all managed in-house to ensure quality and efficiency.

The company operates a 65,000 sq. ft. facility that features one of the largest tool rooms in the region. This advanced setup allows Check-Mate Industries to handle complex projects with skilled craftsmanship. Their services include design, prototype development, manufacturing, and product testing, working with a wide range of metals, including exotic varieties. Notably, Check-Mate has a strong relationship with the firearms and military industries, having fulfilled numerous government contracts and produced millions of high-quality magazines. Their commitment to continuous improvement and cost-effective manufacturing techniques supports their reputation for reliability and precision.

Short Description:
Chiappa Firearms USA, Ltd. is the American branch of the Chiappa Group, an Italian firearms manufacturer founded in 1958. The company has grown from a small artisan workshop into a significant player in the firearms industry, known for its technical expertise and family-led management. Chiappa Firearms produces around 60,000 firearms annually, with its U.S. headquarters located in Dayton, Ohio.

The company specializes in a diverse range of firearms, including reproductions of classic and historical models, such as muzzle-loading guns and iconic Winchester rifles. It also offers original designs like the Chiappa Rhino revolver and .22 LR versions of the M1911 pistol. Chiappa Firearms emphasizes advanced manufacturing techniques, including CNC machining and various surface finishing methods, to ensure quality and durability. Additionally, the company provides comprehensive customer support, including warranty services and repairs, enhancing its service for North American customers.

Short Description:
Explore the saga that is the real West in our five, family-friendly museums: Draper Natural History Museum, Buffalo Bill Museum, Plains Indian Museum, Whitney Western Art Museum, and Cody Firearms Museum. Only the Buffalo Bill Center of the West—formerly the Buffalo Bill Historical Center—shares the epic stories of Yellowstone and the American West together in one place, for one price. That makes us uniquely qualified to tell the stories of the American West like no other museum can. With our galleries, exhibitions, programs, and kid-approved activities, your whole family is sure to exclaim, "I found my true West!"

The Center is located in the authentic western town of Cody, founded by our namesake, William F. "Buffalo Bill" Cody. We're also located in the heart of the Greater Yellowstone region—just outside Yellowstone National Park's East Gate. So we're surrounded by the majesty of the Rockies and are privy to the history and myths of the Old West, the vibrant life of the New West, and the living cultures of Plains Indian peoples.

Short Description:
Condor Non-Lethal Technologies is a Brazilian company founded in 1985, specializing in the development and manufacturing of advanced non-lethal technologies for defense and security applications. Recognized as a Strategic Defense Company by the Brazilian Government, Condor has become a global leader in the non-lethal weapons sector, offering over 160 products distributed in more than 80 countries.

The company operates from a large manufacturing facility in Nova Iguaçu, Rio de Janeiro, which includes 18 research laboratories focused on continuous product development. Condor's product range includes rubber bullets, tear gas grenades, impact grenades, stun guns, smoke grenades, and pyrotechnic signaling devices. These products support public security forces, armed forces, peacekeeping missions, and private security sectors worldwide. Condor also provides training services to ensure the effective use of its equipment.

With a commitment to quality and environmental responsibility, Condor holds certifications such as ISO 9001 and ISO 14001. The company dedicates a significant portion of its manufacturing site to preserving native forest and biodiversity, reflecting its focus on sustainability.

Daniel Defense, LLC is an American firearms manufacturer based in Black Creek, Georgia. Founded by Marty Daniel between 2000 and 2002, the company is family-owned and focuses on producing high-quality rifles, rifle accessories, and firearm components. Known for its commitment to innovation and craftsmanship, Daniel Defense operates a state-of-the-art manufacturing facility equipped with advanced technology to produce most parts in-house.

The company offers a diverse range of products, including AR-15 style rifles, handguards, uppers, suppressors, handguns, and pistol caliber carbines. Daniel Defense is recognized for its Integrally Suppressed Weapon System (ISR) and employs advanced manufacturing techniques like cold hammer forging and CNC machining. With a strong emphasis on American jobs and the Second Amendment, Daniel Defense serves military, law enforcement, and civilian customers, providing a lifetime product guarantee and direct-to-consumer sales options.

Decibullz is a Colorado-based company founded in 2012 by Kyle Kirkpatrick, an elite gymnastics coach and extreme athlete. The company specializes in designing, manufacturing, and distributing custom molded earplugs and earphones that fit each customer's ears perfectly. Headquartered in Fort Collins, Decibullz focuses on providing solutions for individuals engaged in vigorous physical activities, ensuring their audio devices stay securely in place.

The core innovation of Decibullz is its thermo-fit technology, which allows users to create a personalized fit by molding the earphones or earplugs directly to the shape of their ears. This process takes about five minutes and results in a comfortable, secure fit that can be remolded multiple times. The product line includes custom molded earphones, such as the Decibullz Contour, and custom molded earplugs with noise reduction ratings suitable for various applications. Decibullz targets athletes, extreme sports enthusiasts, musicians, and professionals who need reliable ear protection and audio solutions. The company emphasizes innovation, quality, and customer-centric design in its offerings.

Short Description:
About EMF:  The cowboy was king in 1956 and Early & Modern Firearms, Inc. (EMF) was founded to supply the demand for the guns seen in the movies and on television. At the time Colt had stopped production of single action revolvers and declined to resume production. EMF became a major distributor, and then manufacturer, of the Great Western , the first reproduction of the famous Colt Model 1873 SAA. When the strong dollar made it too costly to produce the model 1873 in the U.S., EMF turned to Europe as the European gun manufacturers began the replica firearms industry there. During the past 53 years. EMF has traveled the world to bring "The Best In Cowboy Guns" to first, American Cowboys, and then Cowboy Action Shooters. EMF's efforts have culminated in the introduction of the Great Western II, which is an authentic copy of the original 1873 Colt.

Our Mission: EMF's mission is to provide quality, authentic, but safe, firearms at the best prices. The keystone of EMF's "Cowboy Way" is to provide friendly, personal customer service and stand behind our products. The amazing growth of the sport of Cowboy Action Shooting has fueled the demand for the guns of the Old West. Boyd A. Davis, CEO/President of EMF is also known as General U.S. Grant. SASS #2. He is a Founding Father and the President of SASS.

Engis Corporation is a privately owned manufacturer based in Wheeling, Illinois, specializing in high-performance superabrasive finishing systems. Founded in 1938, the company initially focused on precision measuring equipment and industrial machinery before entering the abrasives market in the 1940s with its Hyprez Diamond Compounds. Engis has since expanded its product offerings to include diamond slurries, tools, and specialized machinery for lapping, grinding, honing, and polishing, achieving nanometer-level surface finishes.

With a global presence supported by subsidiaries in several countries and a network of agents and distributors, Engis serves a diverse customer base in industries such as aerospace, defense, automotive, electronics, and medical device manufacturing. The company emphasizes innovation and precision engineering, with teams of research scientists and engineers dedicated to developing customized solutions. Engis is committed to quality and customer-focused service, maintaining its reputation as a leader in superabrasive finishing technology.

Short Description:
FAIR, the national media watch group, has been offering well-documented criticism of media bias and censorship since 1986. We work to invigorate the First Amendment by advocating for greater diversity in the press and by scrutinizing media practices that marginalize public interest, minority and dissenting viewpoints. As an anti-censorship organization, we expose neglected news stories and defend working journalists when they are muzzled. As a progressive group, FAIR believes that structural reform is ultimately needed to break up the dominant media conglomerates, establish independent public broadcasting and promote strong non-profit sources of information.

Uniquely, FAIR works with both activists and journalists. We maintain a regular dialogue with reporters at news outlets across the country, providing constructive critiques when called for and applauding exceptional, hard-hitting journalism. We also encourage the public to contact media with their concerns, to become media activists rather than passive consumers of news.

FAIR publishes Extra!, the newsletter of media criticism, and produces the weekly radio program CounterSpin, the show that brings you the news behind the headlines. In addition, FAIR's thriving email list distributes articles and Action Alerts to our international network of over 50,000 activists. Sign up today!

For an in-depth explanation of FAIR's critique of the mainstream media, you should start with our overview, What's Wrong with the News? You might also check out the article What's FAIR?, by FAIR founder Jeff Cohen. See what journalists, activists and scholars have to say about FAIR.

Fairness & Accuracy In Reporting, Inc. (FAIR) is a registered 501(c)(3) non-profit organization. FAIR's federal tax-exempt I.D. number is 13-3392362. Donations to FAIR are tax-deductible.

Fiocchi of America is a U.S.-based ammunition manufacturer and a subsidiary of the historic Italian company Fiocchi Munizioni, founded in 1876. Established in 1983, the company operates a manufacturing facility in Ozark, Missouri, to meet the demand for high-quality ammunition in the U.S. market. Fiocchi produces a wide range of shotshell and centerfire ammunition, employing nearly 200 people and importing select components from its Italian parent company.

The company specializes in premium ammunition products for hunting, sport shooting, and law enforcement. Fiocchi is known for its quality craftsmanship and innovation, utilizing advanced production machinery to maintain high standards. With plans to expand manufacturing capacity, including a new facility near Little Rock, Arkansas, Fiocchi aims to enhance its handgun ammunition production and pursue vertical integration in the U.S. market. The company supports the shooting sports community and has a strong reputation for reliability and performance, contributing to successes in competitive shooting events.

Founded in 2002, Galvion specializes in designing and delivering advanced protective armor, head systems, and innovative power supply and management solutions for military and tactical applications. Galvion's product offerings include advanced ballistic helmets, such as the Batlskin® series and the Hellbender™ FE helmet, as well as power management systems like the MAX-8 Mission Adaptive Charging Stations™. They focus on integrated systems that enhance situational awareness and operational effectiveness. With a commitment to innovation and user-centered design, Galvion invests in research and development to create customized technologies. Their ISO-certified facilities ensure high-quality manufacturing and lifecycle support for their products, which are used by military and tactical customers worldwide, including the U.S. Marine Corps and the FBI.

Short Description:
Gorilla Mill is a Wisconsin-based manufacturer specializing in high-performance cutting tools, including carbide end mills, drills, and precision machining tools. Founded in 1974 and rebranded in 2005, the company is headquartered in Waukesha, WI, and has over 40 years of experience serving industries such as aerospace, automotive, medical, and general manufacturing.

Their product range features carbide end mills with innovative designs that enhance tool life and machining performance, as well as carbide drills, thread mills, chamfering tools, and high-speed steel cutting tools. Gorilla Mill's tools are versatile, suitable for machining various materials like aluminum, stainless steel, and inconel, which improves efficiency by reducing the need for frequent tool changes. The company also offers regrinding services to extend tool life.

Gorilla Mill is recognized for its commitment to innovation and quality, earning accolades such as the 2023 Future 50 award from BizTimes Media. They focus on lean manufacturing and continuous improvement, partnering with organizations like the Wisconsin Manufacturing Extension Partnership (WMEP) to enhance their operations.

Short Description:
The U.S. Government Publishing Office (GPO) is a federal agency established in 1860, serving as the official source for producing, preserving, and distributing authentic government publications and information. It operates under the legislative branch and has evolved from a print-only operation to an integrated publishing organization that embraces digital communication and publishing technologies.

Headquartered in Washington, D.C., the GPO produces a variety of official documents, including publications for Congress, the Supreme Court, and federal agencies, as well as U.S. passports. The agency is dedicated to ensuring that government information is secure, authentic, and accessible to the public, supporting transparency and informed citizenship. With a mission to "Keep America Informed," the GPO values commitment, customer service, innovation, diversity, integrity, and teamwork.

Short Description:
Greenleaf Corporation, founded in 1945 and based in Saegertown, Pennsylvania, specializes in developing and manufacturing industrial cutting tools and machine tool accessories. With over 80 years of experience, the company produces high-performance tungsten carbide and ceramic grade inserts, along with innovative toolholding systems for various metal-cutting applications.

Their product range includes carbide and ceramic inserts, boring tools, grooving tools, lathe tooling, milling cutters, toolholders, and specialized tooling for heavy machining tasks. Greenleaf also offers custom-designed ceramic and ceramic-composite materials tailored for specific machining needs. The company serves a diverse clientele across industries such as aerospace, automotive, and machine tool manufacturing, providing engineering services to meet complex customer requirements.

Greenleaf is committed to innovation and quality in cutting tool technology, emphasizing exceptional customer service and a supportive culture for its employees. The company continues to expand its global presence while maintaining a strong legacy of problem-solving and partnership with its customers.

Gunwerks is a precision firearms company based in Cody, Wyoming, founded in January 2006 by Aaron Davidson. The company specializes in long-range shooting and hunting, focusing on integrated, precision-engineered rifle systems. Gunwerks is recognized for its commitment to quality and innovation, developing proprietary rifle stocks and systems that enhance stability and accuracy for demanding hunters and shooters.

The core product line includes precision long-range rifles, such as the LR1000 and Long Range Rifle (LRR), designed for exceptional accuracy at extended distances. Gunwerks also offers a variety of accessories, including optics and ballistic calculation tools, to complement their rifles. Their G7 Ballistics program provides advanced ballistic calculators, improving the shooting experience.

In addition to products, Gunwerks runs the Long Range University, which offers hands-on training in long-range shooting and ethical hunting practices. The company emphasizes research and development, ensuring their products meet the needs of serious hunters and competitive shooters. Gunwerks blends adventure, education, and innovation, positioning itself as a leader in the precision firearms industry.

Formlabs is a prominent developer and manufacturer of 3D printing technology based in Somerville, Massachusetts. Founded in 2011 by three MIT Media Lab students, the company has made significant strides in making high-quality professional desktop 3D printing accessible. They are known for their pioneering work in stereolithography (SLA) and selective laser sintering (SLS) technologies.

The company offers a diverse range of 3D printers, including the Form series of SLA printers and the Fuse series of SLS printers. Formlabs also provides proprietary materials and software to enhance the printing process. With over 130,000 printers sold and a global presence, their technology is utilized across various industries, including medical research, automotive, and aerospace. Formlabs is dedicated to empowering users to bring their ideas to life through accessible 3D printing solutions, while also focusing on community initiatives related to education and equity.

With a strong global presence in over 60 countries and more than 170 Haas Factory Outlets, Haas Automation is recognized for its commitment to quality and innovation.

Haas Automation serves small to medium-sized manufacturing businesses across various industries, including aerospace, automotive, and medical device manufacturing. Short Description:
Beretta USA is the American division of Beretta Holding, the oldest active firearms manufacturer in the world, with roots dating back to 1526 in Italy. Established in 1977, Beretta USA is headquartered in Accokeek, Maryland, and has manufacturing facilities in Gallatin, Tennessee, along with a distribution center in Fredericksburg, Virginia.

The company specializes in high-quality semiautomatic pistols for military, law enforcement, and civilian markets. Its flagship product, the Beretta 92FS, has been the U.S. military's M9 sidearm since 1985. Beretta USA also offers firearms designed for sport shooting and personal defense. As part of the Beretta Defense Technologies alliance, the company collaborates with sister companies to provide integrated solutions for professional users. Additionally, Beretta USA supports its customers through programs like the American Defender Program, focusing on law enforcement and military needs. The company combines traditional craftsmanship with modern technology, maintaining a legacy of quality and precision that has lasted over 500 years.

5th Axis Inc. is a San Diego-based company founded in 2004 by mechanical engineers Steve Grangetto and Chris Taylor. The company specializes in advanced 5-axis machining and automated production solutions, serving high-demand industries such as aerospace, defense, medical devices, and electronics. It has evolved from a small job shop into a leader in precision manufacturing.

The company offers a range of services, including precision workholding solutions, contract manufacturing, turnkey solutions, and engineering support. Their precision workholding products, such as tombstones and RockLock™ bases, enhance machining accuracy. They provide high-volume production of precision parts while adhering to strict regulatory standards. Their turnkey solutions cover all aspects of manufacturing, from product development to logistics. 5th Axis is committed to making manufacturing smarter and more efficient, positioning itself as a partner to its clients.

Short Description:
Absolute Machine Tools, Inc. is a prominent importer and distributor of CNC machine tools in North America, established in 1988. The company specializes in advanced metalworking solutions for various machining applications, including production machining, mold and die machining, and high-speed machining. With over 35 years of experience, they provide a wide range of high-precision machine tools from reputable partners.

Their product lineup features heavy-duty machining and turning centers, vertical lathes, mill/turn centers, Swiss-type lathes, and wire EDM machines, among others. Absolute Machine Tools also emphasizes customer support through applications engineering, training, and preventive maintenance programs. They operate four full-service technical centers in Ohio, Michigan, and Illinois, offering hands-on support and engineering expertise.

The company primarily serves machine shops and manufacturing facilities looking to enhance their production processes. They collaborate with leading suppliers of tooling, automation, and software to deliver tailored turnkey solutions that meet specific production needs.

American Technologies Network, Corp. (ATN) is a U.S.-based manufacturer specializing in advanced electro-optic solutions, including night vision, thermal imaging, and digital day/night optics. Founded in 1995 in Silicon Valley and now headquartered in Doral, Florida, ATN has over 30 years of experience in delivering high-performance optical products for military, government, law enforcement, and outdoor enthusiasts.

ATN is known for its innovative digital smart optics featuring 4K resolution for both day and night use. Their product lineup includes night vision systems, thermal imaging solutions, smart HD optics with AI-driven features, and digital smart optics with ultra HD sensors. They also offer advanced drone and counter-UAS technology for defense applications, as well as user-friendly optics designed for hunters and outdoor enthusiasts. ATN is committed to U.S.-based manufacturing and continuous innovation, making it a trusted provider of advanced night vision and thermal imaging technologies.

Mercedes-AMG GmbH is a high-performance subsidiary of the Mercedes-Benz Group, focused on designing, engineering, and manufacturing exclusive vehicles based on Mercedes-Benz models. Founded in 1967 by former Mercedes engineers Hans Werner Aufrecht and Erhard Melcher, AMG has evolved from a small tuning workshop into a global business with around 750 employees and a diverse range of high-performance vehicles.

AMG specializes in performance-enhanced vehicles, offering specially tuned versions of Mercedes-Benz cars with upgraded engines, suspensions, and aerodynamic components. The company has a strong motorsport heritage, contributing to racing engine development and competing in various championships. Additionally, AMG provides customization options, allowing customers to personalize their vehicles with unique design elements and performance upgrades. As a wholly owned subsidiary since 2005, Mercedes-AMG is dedicated to producing complete high-performance vehicles under the Mercedes-AMG brand, catering to automotive enthusiasts and luxury car buyers worldwide.

APEX Ammunition is a Veteran-owned American company based in Mississippi, dedicated to delivering the ultimate turkey and waterfowl hunting experience. Arc'teryx Equipment is a Canadian company based in North Vancouver, British Columbia, founded in 1989. Originally named Rock Solid, it quickly gained a reputation for high-quality climbing gear and innovative design. The company rebranded to Arc'teryx in 1991, inspired by the Archaeopteryx fossil, symbolizing evolution and innovation.

Arc'teryx specializes in technical outdoor equipment and apparel for activities like climbing, hiking, and skiing. Their product range includes climbing gear, backpacks, and technical outerwear made with advanced materials such as GORE-TEX. The brand is known for its commitment to quality and functionality, employing techniques like thermo-lamination and articulated patterning to enhance performance. Over the years, Arc'teryx has expanded its offerings to cater to a global customer base, including outdoor enthusiasts and consumers interested in high-performance streetwear. The company has also broadened its manufacturing footprint internationally.

Armscor, officially known as Arms Corporation of the Philippines, is a private manufacturer of firearms and ammunition with a history dating back to 1905. Originally starting as a print shop, the company shifted its focus to firearms manufacturing in 1952 after being acquired by the Tuason family. Renamed Armscor in 1980, it has since expanded internationally, establishing facilities in the United States.

Armscor also manufactures firearms for other brands and emphasizes quality control, holding ISO 9001 certification and utilizing advanced manufacturing techniques. With a strong presence in the U.S. market, Armscor serves a wide customer base, including civilian shooters, law enforcement, and military clients.

Short Description:
The Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives (ATF) is a federal law enforcement agency under the U.S. Department of Justice. Established in 1972, its mission is to protect communities from violent crime and illegal activities related to alcohol, tobacco, firearms, explosives, and arson. The ATF investigates violations of federal laws and regulates the lawful commerce of firearms and explosives through licensing and enforcement.

The agency collaborates with federal, state, local, and international law enforcement partners, often participating in joint task forces. It operates a specialized fire research laboratory in Maryland to analyze arson cases and conducts training programs to enhance public safety. The ATF also provides regulatory guidance and investigative reports to law enforcement and industry partners, supporting efforts to prevent violent crime and illegal trafficking.

Datanomix is a software company based in Nashua, New Hampshire, focused on data automation solutions for manufacturing production optimization. DEWESoft USA is the American subsidiary of Dewesoft, a leader in high-end data acquisition (DAQ) systems and test measurement solutions. With a team of over 50 experts, it manages sales, support, training, and engineering activities across the United States, Canada, and minor U.S. territories. Dewesoft, founded in 2000 and headquartered in Slovenia, develops versatile and user-friendly DAQ hardware and software systems for various applications, including vehicle testing, power quality analysis, and structural dynamics.

Dewesoft USA also provides comprehensive customer support, training, and custom solutions tailored to user needs. Its diverse customer base includes prestigious organizations such as SpaceX, NASA, Tesla, and John Deere, spanning aerospace, automotive, and heavy machinery sectors. DEWESoft USA is committed to innovation and aims to be the first choice for mission-critical test and measurement equipment.

Dillon Aero, Inc. is an armament manufacturer based in Scottsdale, Arizona, specializing in rotary machine guns. The company is known for its advanced M134D and M134D-H Minigun models, which have been adopted by the U.S. military and allied forces since 1989. Dillon Aero has redesigned the classic M134 Minigun to enhance reliability, reduce weight, and modernize components, resulting in over 6,500 systems deployed in more than 50 countries.

In addition to rotary machine guns, Dillon Aero produces feeders, delinkers, and other components that improve weapon system performance. The company focuses on design, reliability, and customer service, catering primarily to military and government customers, including specialized units like the U.S. Army’s 160th Special Operations Aviation Regiment. Dillon Aero is part of the Dillon family of companies, which also includes Dillon Precision and Dillon Optics.

Short Description:
About Us:
Since 1989, FALCO® Holsters has been dedicated to crafting a comprehensive range of gun holsters and tactical equipment for everyday civilian and duty use. We combine the finest leather, Kydex & nylon with meticulously handcrafted artisanship and our commitment to continuous innovation. This ensures a custom fit for your firearm, keeping it secure and accessible precisely when you need it most.

Our Story:
FALCO began by producing high-quality leather gloves for the traditional art of falconry in 1989. As needs evolved, we leveraged our expertise in leather manufacturing to expand into gun holsters and hunting products. Thanks to your positive feedback, our custom holster division has become the cornerstone of our company. In 2001, we further broadened our offerings to include nylon holsters, Kydex, concealed carry bags, and tactical gear, reaching a wider audience and better serving the diverse needs of gun owners.

Why Choose FALCO:
Handcrafted Artisanship: Our products are handcrafted by skilled artisans, who ensure that each holster is made with precision and care.
Premium Materials: We use only the finest leather and materials, providing you with durable, high-quality holsters.
Smart Design: Our custom holsters are designed with your comfort, safety, and ease of use in mind.
Compatibility: Our holsters can be custom-crafted for over 3100 handguns & over 60 different lights/lasers.
Exceptional Quality: We maintain the highest standards in material selection and traditional manufacturing processes to deliver you the best products for securing your firearms.
Reasonable Prices: We offer quality holsters and EDC gear at different price levels, making quality products accessible to everyone.

Today, FALCO stands as one of Europe's premier holster and tactical gear producers, exporting our products worldwide. With nimble manufacturing capabilities and an extensive product range, we create custom-crafted solutions tailored to your specific needs.

Short Description:
The Haartz Corporation is a family-founded manufacturer and supplier specializing in automotive topping fabrics and interior trim materials. Established in 1897 and based in Acton, Massachusetts, it is recognized as the world's leading supplier of automotive topping fabrics. The company serves major automakers and the aftermarket globally.

Haartz offers a diverse range of products, including fabrics for convertible tops, vinyl roof covers, and interior trim components. Their materials include solution-dyed acrylic Stayfast fabrics, synthetic felts, foam layers, moldable skins, and artificial leather, all designed to meet high quality and aesthetic standards. The company operates a large manufacturing facility in Acton, producing hundreds of thousands of yards of fabric weekly, and has international operations in Germany, Portugal, China, Japan, and Mexico.

With a customer base that includes prestigious original equipment manufacturers like Audi, BMW, and Rolls-Royce, Haartz emphasizes innovation and quality in its product development. The company maintains a strong family-oriented culture and continues to explore new market opportunities while leading in automotive fabric manufacturing.

Short Description:
Mossy Oak is an American outdoor lifestyle brand founded in 1986 by Toxey Haas in West Point, Mississippi. The company specializes in outdoor clothing and equipment, particularly known for its innovative camouflage patterns that help hunters blend into natural environments. Mossy Oak has developed over 25 proprietary camouflage patterns, including Bottomland and Break-Up Country, which enhance concealment in various terrains.

Operating under Haas Outdoors, Inc., Mossy Oak has grown to a mid-sized company with around 140 employees. The brand emphasizes a connection to nature and wildlife, catering to hunters, outdoor enthusiasts, and landowners. Its offerings include camouflage apparel, licensed clothing products, tree nurseries for habitat management, dog training services for gun dogs, and a real estate agency focused on rural and recreational land sales. Mossy Oak is dedicated to fostering a community that values wildlife conservation and the outdoor lifestyle.

Short Description:
Fishbowl is a company that offers two distinct products catering to different professional needs. 

Fishbowl Inventory provides inventory management and manufacturing software designed to automate business operations. It integrates with popular accounting platforms like QuickBooks and Xero, helping businesses maintain accurate inventory control across multiple locations and sales channels. Key features include barcode scanning, reorder points, multi-location tracking, real-time inventory counts, and automated stock alerts. Fishbowl Inventory targets small to mid-sized businesses across various industries, emphasizing responsive support and customizable workflows.

The Fishbowl Professional Network is a mobile app that facilitates anonymous and verified communication among professionals within the same industry or company. Users can join groups based on their affiliations to share advice and discuss work-related topics while maintaining their anonymity. The app supports verified user profiles, anonymous posting, and direct messaging, fostering open dialogue in a remote work environment.

Short Description:
Founded in 1989, and 100-percent employee-owned, Alternative Manufacturing, Inc. provides a one-stop manufacturing solution to original equipment manufacturers across a diverse range of high tech industries throughout the Northeastern U.S. and Canada.

From printed circuit board and wire harness production to product assembly, packaging and distribution, our ISO 9001, ISO 13485 and AS9100 registered, and UL-certified operations supply contract electronic manufacturing solutions that are custom crafted for both Fortune 1000 and start-up companies, alike.

To better support the New England region, we developed a dual-facility strategy that includes a Prototyping and Technology Center located in Somerville, MA and a full service electronics manufacturing facility in Winthrop, Maine, one of New England's most competitively priced labor markets.

We Own Our Results

As a 100% employee-owned company, every employee is thinking, "if we help our customers grow, we grow." That is the power of employee ownership. Short Description:
Nuts to Ammo: Since 1988

James Dudley developed the concept of the Ammo-Up machines in 1988. His original machine was designed to pick up pecans and other types of nuts. He called his machine the Bag-A-Nut. He started Bag-A-Nut Inc. in 1990 and developed many types of units for a variety of objects.

In 2004 Caleb Dudley, grandson of James, became CEO of Bag-A-Nut LLC. Caleb re-designed the Bag-A-Nut machine for the shooting industry, launching the Ammo-Up line of products.

Over the years, through feedback from our customers, we continue to develop the Ammo-Up. We have developed our product to a standard of which we are very proud. We have a 98% customer satisfaction rate and once you try the Ammo-Up, you will see why. The dream carries on as the Ammo-Up continues to pick up year after year.

GSA Pricing Available.

Angstadt Arms is a firearms manufacturer located in Charlotte, North Carolina. The company specializes in compact, lightweight personal defense weapons (PDWs) and pistol-caliber AR-style firearms. With a heritage rooted in the Angstadt family's craftsmanship from the 18th and 19th centuries, Angstadt Arms combines traditional gunsmithing values with modern innovation to create reliable and refined firearms.

Their product lineup features Glock-magazine-fed AR9 pistols, 9mm rifles, and pistol-caliber carbines, along with various parts and accessories. Notable designs include the integrally suppressed UDP-9I, which operates quietly, and the SCW-9 submachine gun, which participated in the U.S. Army’s Sub Compact Weapons Trials. Angstadt Arms focuses on serving both civilian customers and professionals, including law enforcement and military personnel, by providing innovative and high-quality firearms and suppressors.

Short Description:
Armament Technology Incorporated (ATI) is a Canadian company based in Halifax, Nova Scotia. Founded in 1988, ATI specializes in designing, manufacturing, and distributing professional-grade optical weapon sighting systems and accessories for small arms. The company serves military, law enforcement, precision shooting, and hunting markets worldwide, providing mission-ready optics that adhere to strict international quality standards, including ISO certification.

ATI's product range features Optical Combat Weapon Sights, such as the ELCAN Specter® series, and Long Range Precision Rifle Scopes under the Tangent Theta® brand. They also offer Scope Protection Systems from the Tenebraex® brand, which includes flip-up scope covers and anti-reflection devices. The company is known for its rugged, high-performance optics, built and tested in Canada, and trusted by various defense and security forces globally. Additionally, ATI provides OEM mounting solutions and maintains a broad distribution network.

Short Description:
Armor Research Company's (ARC) is excited to restructure with a new holding company and expansion to product-centric operating subsidiaries. 

During 2022, the global marketplace has rapidly changed, with increased demand signals for personnel protection body armor and products designed for safe transfer of high value artifacts, currency and equipment. Following strategic acquisitions and national-level product demonstrations during 2021, and further confirmation of trademarks and product domain ownership, to include over 30 patents, ARC is poised to lead the marketplace with the right, patented products through direct sales, B2B partnerships and B2G relationships. 

ARC is now advancing the former Dragon Skin certified as exceeding design performance specifications by National Institute of Justice and United States Testing Laboratory, is the world's most technologically advanced, effective, flexible and light weight rifle defeating body armor, currently servicing military special operations, federal agencies, and all levels of local and state law enforcement. ARC, and its current subsidiaries, also provide body armor for handgun defeating and correctional institution markets, as well as high value transfer technology products to the gaming community, high-volume transaction retailers and high net worth individuals. Planned research and development will further advance patented products to assure ARC sustains its position as the industry leader in this market vertical. 

With a national sales force and evolving high-volume manufacturing and assembly capacity, ARC is establishing a bi-coastal and international presence to more efficiently serve both public and private sectors while optimizing supply-chains, test and evaluation, and materials development.  

For correspondence, sales and technical information, please email Ken Hall, CEO, khall@armorresearchco.com or Hampton Dowling, COO, at hampton@armorresearchco.com.

Short Description:
Asolo S.p.A is an Italian company established in 1975, known for its expertise in designing and producing high-quality technical outdoor footwear. The brand, named after the town of Asolo near Venice, specializes in mountaineering boots and leisure outdoor shoes. Asolo is recognized as a global leader in technical mountaineering footwear, offering a wide range of products that cater to both professional alpinists and casual outdoor enthusiasts.

The company has a strong heritage in shoemaking, particularly after the Zanatta family acquired it in 1998, bringing in their expertise and innovative spirit. Asolo has introduced several product innovations, including the first mountain boot made from a combination of leather and Cordura, as well as the first Gore-Tex lined mountain boot. Their proprietary technologies, such as the AFS System and Asoframe, enhance the fit, comfort, and performance of their footwear.

Headquartered in Nervesa della Battaglia, Italy, Asolo also operates a production facility in Sibiu, Romania. The company distributes its products in over 40 countries through subsidiaries and partnerships, supported by a robust e-commerce platform for a seamless global customer experience.

Short Description:
Bally Ribbon Mills (BRM), established in 1923 and based in Bally, Pennsylvania, specializes in the design and manufacture of engineered woven narrow fabrics, tapes, webbings, and specialty textiles. The company serves various industries, including aerospace, defense, medical, safety, automotive, and commercial sectors worldwide.

With a product portfolio featuring over 2,000 woven patterns, BRM utilizes advanced weaving technologies such as shuttle looms and Jacquard looms. Their offerings include woven tapes, webbings, and complex structural fabrics engineered for high performance, ensuring qualities like tensile strength and abrasion resistance. BRM provides a full range of services, from custom design and prototype development to weaving, dyeing, and finishing treatments.

BRM is committed to quality, holding multiple certifications like ISO 9001:2008 and AS 9100:2009. The company has a strong history of collaboration with notable clients, including the U.S. Military and NASA, contributing to significant projects like the heat shield for NASA’s Orion spacecraft. With nearly 300 certified personnel, BRM emphasizes innovation and technological advancement to meet the needs of its diverse clientele.

CERATIZIT is a global leader in the production of wear parts and cutting tools, with a history that dates back to 1931. Originally founded as CERAMETAL in Luxembourg, the company became CERATIZIT S.A. in 2002 after merging with Plansee Tizit. With around 8,000 employees and over 30 production sites worldwide, CERATIZIT is recognized for its expertise in hard materials, particularly tungsten carbide.

CERATIZIT is also known for its commitment to innovation, holding more than 1,000 patents and actively pursuing sustainability initiatives, including participation in projects promoting green hydrogen production. Headquartered in Mamer, Luxembourg, CERATIZIT maintains a strong global presence and holds several key quality and environmental certifications.

DripDrop Hydration, PBC is a Public Benefit Corporation based in Oakland, California, focused on providing a medically formulated oral rehydration solution (ORS) to effectively treat mild to moderate dehydration. Founded in 2008 by Dr. Eduardo Dolhun, the company aims to combat dehydration globally, with each purchase supporting life-saving donations and community aid programs.

The core product is a hydration powder mix that features a balanced blend of electrolytes, glucose, zinc, and vitamin C, designed to promote rapid fluid absorption. DripDrop's formula contains three times the sodium of traditional sports drinks while maintaining lower sugar levels, optimizing hydration. The convenient powder packets can be mixed with water and are suitable for various situations, including exercise, travel, and illness. The company offers a range of flavors made with natural colors, appealing to athletes, military personnel, and everyday consumers seeking effective hydration solutions. DripDrop is recognized for its growth and impact in the hydration market.

Short Description:
Ducks Unlimited is a nonprofit organization founded in 1937, focused on the conservation, restoration, and management of wetlands and habitats for North America's waterfowl. Headquartered in Memphis, Tennessee, it is recognized as the largest private waterfowl and wetlands conservation organization in the world. The organization was established during the Dust Bowl era to address the decline of waterfowl populations due to habitat loss.

Ducks Unlimited's mission is to ensure the sustainability of wetlands, benefiting both wildlife and people. The organization engages in wetlands conservation, habitat management, and collaborates with various stakeholders, including private landowners and government agencies. It has raised over $3.3 billion and conserved more than 12.4 million acres of habitat across the United States, Canada, and Mexico. Ducks Unlimited also offers membership programs, educational outreach, and fundraising events to involve the community in conservation efforts.

Short Description:
Ecoroll AG Werkzeugtechnik is a German company based in Celle, Lower Saxony, specializing in the development, manufacturing, and sales of tools and machines for mechanical surface treatment of metallic components. Founded in the mid-1990s, Ecoroll has over 30 years of industry experience and employs around 80 people. The company focuses on processes such as roller burnishing, deep rolling, skiving/roller burnishing, and mechanical hammer peening, which enhance surface quality and component strength without material removal.

Ecoroll designs customized tools and machines in collaboration with its customers. Their product range includes innovative tools like the HG tool series, which features hydrostatically mounted "ballpoint" tools that adapt to complex shapes. The company serves various industries, including machinery manufacturing, automotive, aerospace, power generation, and medical engineering, providing solutions that improve surface quality and durability of components. Ecoroll also has a subsidiary in Milford, Ohio, to cater to the North American market.

Their offerings include high-performance edge computers, miniaturized computers (NanoPCs), and high-performance computers (HPCs) suitable for harsh environments and mission-critical applications.

The company is committed to sustainability and the United Nations’ Sustainable Development Goals, using edge computing to enhance resource efficiency and reduce waste. Their products support various sectors, including industrial automation, intelligent transportation, energy management, healthcare, and public services, enabling automation, predictive maintenance, and improved operational efficiency.

Short Description:
Now, the world-famous Chinese brand Ganzo was founded over 20 years ago in the city of Yangjiang, Guangdong Province. Then it was a small group of specialists who were really passionate about the idea to produce quality and affordable price knives.

The company began to grow rapidly, almost immediately after the release on the national market, since its products are of high quality. Now, the company has reached the status of a large international company. The product range is increased by multi-tools and sharpeners that ensure professional maintenance of the tools. Ganzo knives, multi-tools and sharpeners are very popular far beyond the borders of their country: The United States, Germany, Italy, Spain, France, and about three dozen countries.

Multi-tools are also designed so as to make convenient use of each of the instruments in the kit. A set of functionalities in different models may differ in number as well as in purpose, but among a wide range of tools each customer can choose the one that will fit his needs.

The same positive feedback from customers is given to Ganzo sharpeners, the range of which includes models for home use and those who are hiking-orientated, for both professionals and beginners. But the distinguishing feature of each model is its high efficiency.

Ganzo company received more than a hundred patents developing its own manufacturing methods and functional details. Products that should be certified according to international standards must undergo this procedure and, therefore, meet all the stringent requirements to comply with standards. Moreover, the use of high-quality equipment and a thorough quality control system, allows Ganzo to achieve excellent results. These facts are confirmed by a stable increase of popularity of Ganzo sharpeners, knives and multi-tools.

Unwavering quality combined with cost affordable for a wide range of customers – are the features of Ganzo multi-tools, knives and sharpeners.

Gasbarre Products, Inc. is an American manufacturer specializing in powder compaction and thermal processing equipment. Founded in 1973 by George Gasbarre Sr. in Falls Creek, Pennsylvania, the company has over 50 years of experience and operates globally with more than 200 employees across seven locations. Gasbarre is recognized as a full-service supplier to the powder metallurgy, particulate materials, and thermal processing industries.

The company designs, manufactures, and services a wide range of equipment, including mechanical, hydraulic, and electric powder compaction presses, as well as various thermal processing systems like industrial furnaces. Gasbarre also offers precision tooling solutions, industrial automation systems, and contract manufacturing services. With a commitment to quality management and operational excellence, Gasbarre adheres to ISO standards and employs Total Quality Management methodologies to ensure customer satisfaction. The company serves a diverse global customer base, with 20% of its products exported internationally.

Short Description:
General Dynamics is a prominent American aerospace and defense company, founded in 1952 through the merger of the Electric Boat Company and Canadair. Headquartered in Falls Church, Virginia, the company has a rich history, notably in submarine development, including the launch of the USS Nautilus, the world’s first nuclear-powered submarine, in 1954.

The company primarily serves the U.S. government and allied military customers, focusing on advanced military technologies and systems. General Dynamics specializes in several areas, including the design and construction of nuclear-powered submarines and surface warships through its Electric Boat division. It also produces armored vehicles, such as the M1 Abrams tank, and offers business aviation solutions through Gulfstream Aerospace. Additionally, General Dynamics provides information technology services, including defense electronics and cybersecurity solutions, following strategic acquisitions. Overall, General Dynamics is a diversified defense contractor with a strong emphasis on government contracts and military support.

General Inspection LLC is a manufacturer based in Davisburg, Michigan, specializing in high-speed gauging, sorting, and 100% inspection systems. Founded in 1991, the company integrates advanced technologies such as laser, eddy current, vision, and acoustic methods to ensure product quality in size, shape, and structure. Their goal is to help manufacturers achieve zero defects through state-of-the-art inspection technology.

The company offers a range of automated inspection systems tailored for various industries, including ammunition, aerospace, and automotive. Notable products include the Gi-6v ammunition inspection system, which meets military standards, and the VisionLab system, a 3D non-contact gauging tool that enhances inspection efficiency. General Inspection LLC also provides the VisionDome system for high-speed inspection of roller bearings, along with other measuring equipment and automation solutions.

With a focus on continuous research and development, General Inspection LLC consistently introduces innovative technologies to support high-volume, precision manufacturing and maintain stringent quality standards.

Grizzly Industrial, Inc. is an American company founded in 1983, specializing in the retail, mail order, and internet sales of woodworking and metalworking machinery, power tools, hand tools, and related accessories. Short Description:
IDEX Corporation is a global industrial company based in Northbrook, Illinois, founded in 1988. It operates more than 50 subsidiary businesses and employs around 9,000 people across over 20 countries. The company is publicly traded on the New York Stock Exchange and is part of the S&P 500 index.

IDEX specializes in designing and manufacturing a wide range of specialty engineered products. Its operations are organized into three main segments: Fluid and Metering Technologies, Health and Science Technologies, and Fire and Safety and Diversified Products. The company produces industrial pumps, valves, flow measurement devices, hydraulic rescue tools, and equipment for medical diagnostics, among other products. IDEX serves various industries, including agriculture, pharmaceuticals, semiconductor fabrication, and emergency services, providing essential solutions for both commercial and governmental clients.

With a strong focus on innovation and operational excellence, IDEX has grown significantly since its inception, achieving over $3.1 billion in annual sales. The company promotes a culture of diversity and decentralized entrepreneurship, allowing its subsidiaries to operate with agility while leveraging the resources of the larger organization.

Intelligent Optical Systems, Inc. (IOS) is a research and development company based in Torrance, California, established in 2002. The company specializes in advanced optical technologies, focusing on the development of light sources, chemical sensors, and biomedical sensors using proprietary optical fibers. IOS has received international recognition for its innovations, including being named one of Time Magazine’s Best Inventions of 2007.

The company’s expertise encompasses various scientific fields, including physics, chemistry, and biochemistry. IOS provides a wide range of services, including research, development, testing, and evaluation in physical, chemical, biological, and remote sensing domains. Their product offerings include advanced light sources and sensors tailored for chemical and biomedical applications, designed to deliver high-performance sensing capabilities.

IOS serves a diverse clientele, including major corporations like General Motors and Honeywell, as well as U.S. government agencies such as NASA and the Department of Defense. The company combines multidisciplinary scientific knowledge with innovative product development to meet the needs of both commercial and government sectors globally.

Intermountain Health is a not-for-profit healthcare system based in Salt Lake City, Utah, serving the Intermountain West region, including states like Colorado, Idaho, Montana, Nevada, Utah, and Wyoming. Founded in 1975 with the donation of fifteen hospitals, it has expanded significantly through mergers and acquisitions, including a notable merger with SCL Health in 2022. The organization employs over 64,000 people and operates 33 hospitals and approximately 385 clinics.

The system provides a wide range of services, including acute care, specialty care, primary care, home healthcare, and health insurance through its SelectHealth plan. Intermountain Health also co-founded Civica Rx, a generic drug manufacturer aimed at addressing drug shortages and pricing issues. With a commitment to high-quality, cost-effective care, it serves millions of patients, including individuals, families, and institutions, across urban and rural communities. The organization focuses on community health and integrated care, aiming to inspire the future of health.

KA-BAR is recognized for its commitment to American craftsmanship and quality in all its products.

The company is committed to delivering high-quality solutions that meet the needs of military personnel and tactical operators.

Massif® is a U.S.-based manufacturer of advanced flame-resistant (FR) apparel, primarily serving military, first responders, and specialized government users. Founded in 1999 and headquartered in Ashland, Oregon, the company has expanded its reach from Search and Rescue and Wildland Firefighting to supplying all branches of the U.S. Armed Forces, including the Coast Guard and Army.

The company focuses on creating high-performance, comfortable, and durable FR gear that meets the demands of hazardous work environments. Massif collaborates with Antex Knitting Mills to develop unique FR fabrics and clothing designs suitable for various climates. Their product line includes flame-resistant clothing and outerwear that prioritize stretch, breathability, and moisture management. All products are Berry Amendment compliant, ensuring they are sourced and manufactured in the U.S., which supports quality control and domestic jobs.

Massif is committed to protecting those who serve, with apparel that exceeds military standards for durability and safety. They also engage with the community through initiatives like Big Voice™, which shares stories about their innovations and the people behind the brand.

Short Description:
Mectron Engineering Company, Inc., was founded in 1968 to design and manufacture quality control and handling systems utilizing eddy current and ultrasonic instrumentation.

Today, Mectron offers its own complete line of laser, eddy current, and thread inspection systems. Individual parts are scanned and measured as they pass through Mectron's high speed systems.
Products are inspected for dimensions, diameters, lengths, foreign material, thread defects, part damage, metalurgical defects, hardness, cracks, etc.

Mectron Engineering's product development team has been awarded several patents on laser and eddy current inspection systems. Recent developments have yielded a new state-of-the-art laser, which will bring part inspection to another level.

The Mectron name has been built on technology, customer service and inspection systems that provide capabilities for supplying zero defect products.

Short Description:
Metal Form Manufacturing Company was founded in 1967 to meet the needs of the HVAC industry. Today, Metal Form LLC is a premier manufacturer of a wide range of air control, sound control, and evaporative cooling products for commercial, industrial, and institutional applications. We specialize in designing and manufacturing solutions for custom applications and requirements. 

With more than 100 representative organizations in major cities throughout the United States, Canada, Mexico, and the Pacific Rim, our products are distributed worldwide from our 80,000 sq. ft., fully-automated manufacturing facility located in Phoenix, Arizona. Our products are marketed under the Commercial Acoustics, Dynasonics, Energy Saver, and Metal Form brands.

Our Commercial Acoustics product applications include industrial and HVAC noise control. Our team can assist with quality acoustical analysis, engineering, and products manufactured to standard or custom specifications. Commercial Acoustics helps you make sound decisions with quality acoustical analysis, engineering, and products.

Dynasonics offers a comprehensive line of noise control products, and we offer innovative tools that predict noise levels and simplify product selection. For over 35 years we have been dedicated to providing the commercial and industrial acoustic markets with excellence in both products and service.

Energy Saver manufactures state-of-the-art, microprocessor-controlled, low-maintenance evaporative cooling systems. Our products include water supply controllers, replacement evaporative media, and PreCooler systems.

Metal Form, a member of the Air Movement and Control Association (AMCA), offers a broad range of certified products. Our products are made-to-order and easily customized to meet specific project requirements and specifications.
