Short Description:
MKU is a prominent Indian defense and homeland security company based in Kanpur, Uttar Pradesh. Founded in 1985 by GK Gupta, the company initially produced fiber-reinforced plastic helmets for the Indian Army. Over the years, MKU has expanded its offerings to include a wide range of personal and platform protection solutions, such as ballistic helmets, body armor, ballistic shields, and optronics devices like night vision binoculars.

With a global reach, MKU serves over 230 military and security forces in more than 100 countries, including notable clients like the United Nations and NATO. The company has established manufacturing facilities in India, Germany, and the UAE, with plans for expansion into Brazil. MKU's commitment to quality is reflected in its certifications, including ISO 9001:2008 and AS 9100, ensuring that its products meet international standards. The company continues to innovate in protective technologies, safeguarding millions of soldiers and various defense platforms worldwide.

MMI Textiles is a family-owned supplier in the textile industry, established in 1997 by Amy Bircher. Originally a manufacturer’s representative for six Midwestern states, the company has expanded significantly, including the acquisition of NDW Textiles in 2007 and the opening of a manufacturing facility in Lenoir, North Carolina, in 2021.

The company offers a wide range of products such as fabrics, webbing, binding tape, hook & loop fasteners, hardware, and labels. Their manufacturing facility specializes in weaving military-specification webbing and elastic, primarily serving the military and tactical industries. MMI Textiles is ISO 9001-certified, ensuring high quality and expertise, and emphasizes customer service and integrity in its operations. The company also features tactical gear lines with well-known brands like CORDURA®, VELCRO®, and ITW Nexus products. With a focus on teamwork and customer satisfaction, MMI Textiles has grown to a 32-person operation and celebrated its 25th anniversary in 2022.

My Medic is a family-operated company based in Salt Lake City, Utah, that specializes in high-quality first aid kits, supplies, and training. Founded after a personal tragedy, the company aims to empower individuals to handle emergencies effectively by providing the necessary skills, knowledge, and equipment.

The company offers a variety of first aid kits tailored to different needs, including basic kits, premium kits with trauma supplies, and specialty kits for activities like off-roading and boating. Their largest kit, "The Medic," is designed for larger groups or workplaces. Each purchase includes free life-saving training, reinforcing their commitment to equipping customers with both supplies and the knowledge to use them. My Medic also features unique tools and modular packs that allow for customization based on specific activities or risks.

My Medic serves a diverse customer base, including families, outdoor enthusiasts, and workplaces, focusing on reliable first aid solutions for everyday safety and specialized environments. With around 80 employees, the company generates approximately $15.1 million in revenue, operating primarily in the retail sector.

NANUK is a Canadian company based in Terrebonne, Quebec, specializing in the design and manufacturing of ultra-durable protective hard cases and accessories. Founded in 1984, NANUK has evolved into a globally recognized brand known for its premium-quality protective gear. The company employs around 100 people and has an estimated revenue of $50 million. NANUK aims to expand its presence as a lifestyle brand, inspired by the strength and resilience of the polar bear.

The company offers a wide range of injection-molded plastic protective cases that are waterproof, dustproof, and MIL-SPEC certified. Their products feature lightweight NK-7 resin construction and include various models with special features like padlock holes, stackability, and automatic pressure relief valves. NANUK serves diverse industries, including medical, drone, photography, and scientific equipment, providing reliable protection for sensitive gear. With a strong focus on durability and design, NANUK is committed to delivering products that meet the needs of professionals and consumers alike.

Short Description:
The National Rifle Association (NRA) is a historic American organization founded in 1871 by Union veterans Col. William C. Church and Gen. George Wingate. Originally established to promote rifle shooting and improve marksmanship among soldiers, the NRA has evolved into a leading firearms education organization. It is headquartered in Fairfax, Virginia, and has a membership of approximately five million people.

The NRA offers training programs in firearm safety and marksmanship for all ages, with a strong focus on youth involvement through partnerships with organizations like 4-H and the Boy Scouts of America. It operates museums that highlight the history of firearms in American culture, including the NRA National Firearms Museum. The NRA Institute for Legislative Action advocates for Second Amendment rights and engages in lobbying efforts related to gun legislation. Overall, the NRA plays a significant role in firearms education, youth shooting sports, and political advocacy for gun rights in the United States.

Newcon Optik is a Canadian company based in Toronto, founded in 1992 by Michael Beker. It specializes in the design, research, development, and manufacture of high-quality electro-optical products. The company is recognized for its expertise in image-intensified night vision, thermal imaging systems, laser rangefinders, and tactical optics.

Initially catering to the consumer market, Newcon Optik quickly expanded its offerings to include advanced hand-held, head, helmet, and weapon-mounted electro-optics for military and law enforcement agencies globally. Its product range features night vision systems for low-light conditions, thermal imaging systems for detecting heat signatures, precision laser rangefinders, and tactical optics designed for professional applications.

Newcon Optik is committed to innovation and high ethical standards, providing mission-critical solutions to customers in over 70 countries. The company also offers custom design services to meet specific operational needs, reinforcing its reputation as a trusted name in the electro-optics industry.

Nightforce Optics is a premium manufacturer of high-quality riflescopes and spotting scopes, founded in 1992 by Ray Dennis. Originally a subsidiary of Lightforce Performance Lighting, the company shifted its focus to optics due to strong demand in the North American market. Headquartered in Orofino, Idaho, Nightforce products are hand-assembled, emphasizing ruggedness, reliability, and precision.

The company specializes in precision optics for long-range professionals, competitive shooters, hunters, and elite military units. Its product lineup includes various riflescopes designed for different applications, known for their durability and exceptional optical clarity. Nightforce has earned a strong reputation in both civilian and military markets, supplying sniper-grade riflescopes to the United States Armed Forces and being the nominated sniper optic provider for the Five Eyes countries. The company is dedicated to quality craftsmanship, ensuring that its optics meet the highest standards for performance and reliability.

Nokta Detectors exports its products to over 100 countries, establishing a robust international presence. The company has experienced strong financial growth, with significant increases in net sales revenue and profit margins in recent years. With around 250 employees, Nokta Muhendislik A.S. continues to expand its operations and technological capabilities.

Outdoor Cap Company is a prominent headwear manufacturer and supplier based in Bentonville, Arkansas. Founded in 1977 by Paul Mahan, the company has expanded significantly, employing over 400 people and operating three distribution centers in Arkansas, California, and Texas. It serves more than 14,000 customers across various sectors, including team sports, promotional products, hunting and fishing, and retail markets.

The company specializes in a diverse range of headwear products, including baseball caps, visors, bucket hats, beanies, and more. With a commitment to quality and innovation, the company has produced over 200 million hats, including licensed products for well-known brands. Outdoor Cap is recognized for its core values of integrity, teamwork, and respect, and it has received industry accolades for its strong market presence and reputation.

Short Description:
PAWS Workholding is an innovative leader in workholding solutions for OEM's and high volume Contract Manufacturers.  Through the use of multiple-part workholding and automation, our team delivers engineered solutions that produce unmatched efficiency gains and precision. 

We've been providing clamping and fixturing solutions to the manufacturing community since the early 1990's and have a wealth of experience in solving workholding challenges in production milling environments. Our staff of dedicated, knowledgeable engineers and designers can look at your workholding needs and develop a first class solution to help you achieve your manufacturing output goals.

Our team of Workholding Specialists use their combined knowledge along with some of the industry's leading CAD/CAM tools, such as MasterCAM and SolidWorks, to design and engineer the right workholding solution for you. We have a wealth of experience in I.D. collet gripping, O.D. gripping (5c and 3J), Vise-type clamping, V-block bridge clamping and 4th Axis applications, as well as many custom solutions.

As the originator of our patented Hydraulic Clamping System, we understand the importance of efficiency and productivity in a production milling environment. That is why we have developed a modular clamping system that allows for maximum density under the spindle, or Multiple Part Workholding, along with automated clamping to reduce load times and keep your spindle turning!

Understanding the "Multiple Part Workholding Advantage", we believe, is critical to maximizing your productivity and efficiency on your CNC Milling Center.

Pelican Products, Inc. is an American multinational company founded in 1976 in Torrance, California. It specializes in designing and manufacturing high-performance portable lighting systems, temperature-controlled packaging, and protective cases. The Pelican case, known for its durability and protective features, is the company's flagship product.

Originally a small mail-order business focused on dive market products, Pelican has expanded its offerings over the years. The company operates multiple manufacturing facilities in the U.S. and Europe, producing rugged cases and advanced lighting systems. Its products cater to a variety of industries, including military, law enforcement, fire safety, consumer entertainment, photography, medical, biotech, and industrial sectors. Pelican is committed to quality and innovation, ensuring reliable protection for valuable equipment and critical supplies.

Pilot Precision Products is a global manufacturer and supplier specializing in industrial broaches, cutting tools, and tools for milling, drilling, and turning operations. Founded in 2019 by Eric Hagopian, the company builds on a legacy from the duMont Company, which has been a pioneer in broaching tools since 1945. It is the parent company of well-known brands like duMont Minute Man and Hassay Savage, and serves as the exclusive U.S. distributor for Magafor and GMauvais USA products, as well as the master importer of Palbit carbide cutting tools from Portugal.

Headquartered in South Deerfield, Massachusetts, Pilot Precision Products serves various industries, including aerospace, automotive, defense, medical, and railway sectors. The company emphasizes craftsmanship and innovation, offering a range of products such as precision rotary broaching tools, high-performance round cutting tools, and micro drills. They focus on outstanding customer service and aim to build long-term relationships with clients and distributors. Additionally, Pilot Precision Products values employee well-being, providing training, flexible schedules, and benefits to foster a collaborative work environment.

Patriot Ordnance Factory (POF-USA) is a firearms manufacturer located in Phoenix, Arizona, established in 2002 by aerospace engineer Frank DeSomma. The company specializes in designing and producing high-quality AR-style rifles, pistols, upper and lower receivers, and various gun accessories. POF-USA is recognized for introducing gas-piston-operated AR-15 rifles to the commercial market, which enhances reliability and reduces carbon fouling compared to traditional systems.

The company's innovative Regulated Short-Stroke Gas Piston System improves performance by controlling bolt carrier speed and minimizing wear on components. POF-USA's product lineup includes popular models such as the P15, Revolution, Renegade, and Minuteman rifles. The company emphasizes domestic production, with all major components manufactured in-house or sourced from American suppliers. POF-USA has grown significantly from its origins in a garage to a large manufacturing facility, maintaining a strong commitment to quality and innovation in the firearms industry.

Short Description:
For three generations Prandi Axes has produced high quality forged and heat cast manual tools with PASSION.

Prandi Axes is specialised in the production of cutting implements, such as axes, hatchets, wedges and other woodcutting tools. Thanks to our passion, we are among the few companies in Europe who boast such a large array of forest splitting tools with over 150 models of axes and hatchets.

Each and every article was studied and produced upon request by our clients who, in constant search of high quality standards, aim to respect the habits and cultural TRADITION of the territory in which they work.

We select and work with high quality steel that is exclusively Made in Italy.
Thanks to our state of the art fleet of machines, all processes necessary for the production of the tools are completed internally: creation of moulds, hot forging, sandblasting, heat treating, grinding, sharpening, varnishing, assembly of handles, marking, labelling, and packaging.
Each production phase, whilst maintaining the standards and peculiarities of typical Italian artisan work, is examined according to the UNI EN ISO 9001:2008 standards.

Rocky Brands, Inc. is a publicly traded company based in Nelsonville, Ohio, that specializes in designing, manufacturing, and distributing premium footwear and apparel. Founded in 1932, the company has grown from a local shoe manufacturer into a leader in outdoor, work, western, and military footwear and apparel. Its well-known brands include Rocky®, Georgia Boot®, Durango®, Lehigh®, The Original Muck Boot Company®, XTRATUF®, and Ranger®.

Additionally, it provides outdoor and work apparel designed to complement its footwear lines. Short Description: The Ruck Sox brand was developed after one of our founders suffered from severe blisters during rucking, no matter what he tried. Our Army has been in business for nearly 250 years. Our rifles, uniforms, helmets, plate carriers, and technology has changed dramatically in that time. However, our socks have largely remained unchanged... but we're changing that. Our socks utilize the "miracle fiber", also known as Merino Wool, which moves moisture and thermoregulates body temperature in both hot and cold conditions. We're proudly a SOF Disabled Veteran Owned Company knitting all of our socks right here in North Carolina with 100% All-American yarns.

Short Description:
Sarsilmaz Silah Sanayi A.Ş. is a prominent Turkish small arms manufacturer with a history that dates back to 1880. Headquartered in Düzce, Turkey, it is the largest small arms producer in the country and one of the leading manufacturers in Europe. The company employs over 1,600 people and operates extensive manufacturing facilities, including a 66,000 square meter outdoor area.

Sarsilmaz produces a diverse range of firearms, including pistols, shotguns, submachine guns, assault rifles, and machine guns. It is recognized as the official pistol supplier to the Turkish National Police and Armed Forces. The company also develops advanced weapon systems, such as the autonomous armed robot SARBOT and 25mm land cannon systems. Sarsilmaz exports its products to over 78 countries, serving military and law enforcement agencies worldwide, with a dedicated distribution partner in the United States. Additionally, Sarsilmaz has expanded into the aviation components sector through its subsidiary TR Mekatronik.

Short Description:
Silvus Technologies is a prominent developer of advanced Multiple Input Multiple Output (MIMO) communication systems, focusing on tactical and mission-critical wireless connectivity solutions. Founded in 2004 and headquartered in Los Angeles, the company specializes in delivering high-fidelity video, voice, and data transmission in challenging environments, including severe multipath and Non-Line-of-Sight (NLOS) conditions.

The company's core product line, the StreamCaster family of MANET radios, provides reliable, high-speed data transmission for military, law enforcement, and broadcast teams. Silvus also engages in custom research and development projects, collaborating with organizations like DARPA and the Department of Defense to innovate in areas such as secure communications and interference-immune networking. Additionally, Silvus offers customer support, training, and firmware upgrades to enhance the operational effectiveness of its systems. With a team of PhD scientists and engineers, Silvus Technologies is dedicated to advancing MIMO wireless technology to meet the complex demands of modern communication needs.

SLNT® is a private company founded in 2009 that specializes in signal-blocking technology, primarily serving the retail sector. The company focuses on helping individuals reclaim their privacy by offering products designed to block unwanted digital tracking and electromagnetic interference. Their product range includes Faraday sleeves, bags, backpacks, and RFID wallets, all aimed at providing protection against tracking, hacking, and harmful EMF radiation.

Led by CEO Aaron Zar, SLNT® operates with a small team and has established a strong presence in a niche market. The company has gained the trust of over 200,000 users and has secured six military contracts, serving clients such as Google and the US Army. SLNT® emphasizes sustainability and innovation, particularly with their E3 Faraday Bags collection, which combines advanced shielding technology with eco-friendly materials. Their offerings are designed to enhance digital security, data privacy, and overall well-being in an increasingly connected world.

SMW Autoblok Group is a multinational company specializing in workholding technology for machine tools. Founded in 1942 in Turin, Italy, the group has grown through the merger of several prominent manufacturing entities, including Autoblok and SMW of Germany. With headquarters in multiple countries and production facilities in Italy, Germany, the USA, China, and India, the company employs over 500 people and generates significant revenue.

Their product offerings include power chucks, manual chucks, static chucks, special jaws, cylinders, mechatronic clamping devices, and magnetic clamping systems. SMW Autoblok also provides intelligent sensors, software, and automation solutions to enhance manufacturing processes. They serve various industries, including automotive, aerospace, and general manufacturing, focusing on building long-term partnerships with customers to ensure product performance and service.

The organization offers a daily newspaper and multimedia content that includes news, features, sports, and community stories tailored for U.S. service members and their families. TİSAŞ Trabzon Silah Sanayi A.Ş. is a Turkish firearms manufacturer founded in 1993, specializing in the design and production of pistols and infantry rifles. TİSAŞ is committed to high-quality standards and continuous research and development.

The company exports around 80-85% of its production to approximately 60 countries, promoting the "Made in Turkey" brand in the global defense sector.

Short Description:
Since 1866 Winchester has continually manufactured quality products designed to provide security to Americans and their families. In 1991 that mission was taken to a new frontier and Winchester Safes was born.

Reliability and integrity are essential to Winchester. It's how we built "the gun that won the west," and it's how we continue to build the best gun safes to protect it. We know what our home and gun safes mean to our consumers, and we never take that responsibility for granted. Winchester Safes are fabricated using state-of-the-art methods that refuse to sacrifice quality.

A Winchester Safe is built to protect a lot more than just firearms. We put everything we have into our products so you can feel secure with everything you lock inside. Winchester Safes offer proven security for your memories, protection for your possessions, and - most importantly - peace of mind for you and your family.

In 2012, Winchester Safes fulfilled its goal to once again manufacture our safes back in our hometown of Fort Worth, Texas. Since then, we've invested in some of the most highly automated and sophisticated manufacturing equipment available. Our American facilities use the latest technology in laser cutting, robotic-tended forming equipment and robotic welding. This equipment allows us to build safes with the finest fit, consistency and finish in the industry. It also enables us to produce and build safes faster than any of our competitors. A Winchester safe comes off our production line, ready to be shipped, every 2.2 minutes.

Short Description:
WSI SPORTS is a leading manufacturer of innovative sports apparel located in Eagan, MN. For over 25  years WSI Sports has produced high-quality, Made in USA apparel.

Unlike the mass-produced clothing manufactured overseas by our competitors, each WSI garment is designed, cut and sewn one-garment-at-a-time at our factory in Eagan, Minnesota. Through attention to detail and our just-in-time manufacturing process we can produce the highest quality sports apparel while controlling costs at the same time. This assures you that you are a buying a superior product at competitive prices.

We're proud that all our products are made in America and we are equally proud to have found a way for Americans to compete with low-cost off-shore resources. 

Customization is an added benefit to our one-at-a-time process. Our ability to customize our sports apparel just the way you like it. Whether you are an individual training for the next marathon or a professional franchise touring the country, we can create a separate line just for you. You want custom team colors, no problem, custom team logos, no problem -- just let us know and we can make it for you.

For the retailer, our process allows you to pick the style and sizes that will sell in your store. We don't force you to buy garments that you don't need that will end up on the clearance rack. By ordering only what you need your customer will be more satisfied and more likely to return to your store.

We also manufacture base layer and cold weather clothing and performance gear for men and women with our HEATR®, ProWikMax®, Arctic WikMax®, Microtech™, and HYPRTECH™ BAMBOO lines.  We have supplied major college and professional sports teams and athletes.  Our clothing and gear is used for those into:

Outdoors and hiking
Hunting and fishing
Skiing and snowboarding
Baseball
Football
Hockey
Cycling
Running
Adventure sports

Our TAC Gear series also is used for military and law enforcement.  Contact us today at (651) 994-9945.

Short Description:
Live Free Armory makes OEM parts for over 100+ well-known companies. For example, you have probably already seen many of our replacement slides, handgun barrels, and handgun compensators, but due to non-disclosure and confidentiality agreements, you don't know we made them.

Live Free Armory is an ISO9001:2015 and AS9100 compliant company where quality is Job Number One. If there are any lessons to be learned from its journey so far, it's this: if you want to be successful at manufacturing, run your operation as if everything you were manufacturing is for yourself or a loved one. Another thing Live Free Armory has learned, is that hiring the right people makes all the difference in the world. Every member of Live Free Armory is either a veteran, a former law enforcement officer, a competitive shooter, hunter, or avid firearms enthusiast. Everyone at Live Free Armory, regardless of background, is an avid supporter of the 2nd Amendment, and ultimately, an end user of the types of products we manufacturer.

Live Free Armory has a design and development component to its manufacturing, which can help companies design and develop their own products. Our design team can take an idea and develop it through to full production — our engineers design it and our experts test it. LFA recently expanded its engineering design team, has trained more programmers, and added more set-up specialists to meet the growing demand for our services. Success creates more success, and Live Free Armory has no intention of slowing down any time soon.

LYNRED is a B2B company based in Palaiseau, France, that specializes in designing and manufacturing infrared (IR) detectors for various applications, including military, space, and commercial sectors. As Europe's leading supplier of infrared detector technology, LYNRED produces both cooled and uncooled microbolometers that span the entire infrared spectrum, including SWIR, MWIR, LWIR, and VLWIR.

Formed in July 2019 from the merger of Sofradir and ULIS, LYNRED combines over 35 years of experience in infrared imaging sensor technology. The company employs around 1,000 people and invests more than 15% of its annual revenue in research and development, focusing on innovation and holding several hundred patents. LYNRED serves diverse markets such as defense, security, automotive, and smart buildings, providing advanced infrared imaging solutions for applications like space observation, thermal cameras, and industrial thermography.

The Norwegian-American Defense Industry Council (NADIC) is a non-profit trade association located in the Washington DC area. It focuses on enhancing collaboration between the Norwegian and American defense and homeland security sectors. NADIC promotes the Norwegian defense industrial base and helps Norwegian companies access the U.S. market while ensuring U.S. officials are informed about their unique capabilities.

NADIC's key activities include hosting the annual Norwegian-American Defense Conference, organizing national pavilions at U.S. trade shows, and conducting various networking events in partnership with Team Norway organizations. Through these efforts, NADIC plays a vital role in strengthening ties between the two countries' defense industries.

The company reported net sales of approximately $2.08 billion, reflecting its robust financial position and extensive patent portfolio.

Short Description:
Rolled Alloys is a specialty metals company based in Temperance, Michigan, founded in 1953. The company specializes in processing and supplying heat- and corrosion-resistant metal alloys for various industrial applications worldwide. It gained recognition for introducing the wrought RA330 alloy, which serves as a superior replacement for cast HT alloy in the commercial heat treat industry.

The company offers a wide range of high-performance alloys, including duplex stainless steels, titanium alloys, nickel alloys, and cobalt alloys. These materials are designed for demanding environments in industries such as chemical processing, aerospace, power generation, and heat treating. Rolled Alloys operates multiple locations across the U.S. and has divisions in Canada, Singapore, and China, with NeoNickel serving as its exclusive representative in Europe. The company emphasizes customer service, supported by a team of sales professionals and metallurgists, and maintains a large inventory with extensive processing capabilities for prompt shipment of standard and custom-cut parts.

Safeware, Inc. is a prominent company based in Lanham, Maryland, specializing in protective safety equipment and emergency response solutions since 1979. The company serves various sectors, including public preparedness, safety, government, education, healthcare, hospitality, and enterprise technology.

Safeware plays a crucial role in supporting first responders during significant national emergencies, such as the Oklahoma City Bombing, the 9/11 attacks, Hurricane Katrina, and the COVID-19 pandemic. With around 150 employees and annual revenues estimated between $10 million and $50 million, Safeware operates distribution and service centers across the United States. SilencerCo is a prominent American manufacturer based in West Valley City, Utah, specializing in firearm suppressors. Founded in 2008 by Jonathon Shults and Josh Waldron, the company aims to make firearms quieter and safer for shooters. It has grown to become the largest suppressor manufacturer in the United States, recognized for its innovation, quality, and durability.

The company designs and manufactures a diverse range of suppressors for handguns, rifles, and shotguns. Notable products include the Sparrow, Osprey, Salvo 12, and Maxim 9, along with various muzzle devices and firearm accessories. SilencerCo serves a wide customer base, including recreational shooters, hunters, and law enforcement, all of whom value hearing protection and noise reduction. The company is also committed to customer service, providing legal counsel to assist with the silencer approval process. SilencerCo is dedicated to craftsmanship and innovation, actively participating in advocacy efforts to advance suppressor legislation in the U.S.

Solar Atmospheres, Inc. is a prominent family-owned commercial heat treating company in the United States, established in 1983 by William R. Jones. With multiple plants across the country, including locations in Pennsylvania, California, South Carolina, Michigan, and Connecticut, the company has grown to become one of the largest independently owned heat treaters, operating over 90 vacuum furnaces.

The company specializes in vacuum heat treating and brazing services, providing high-quality thermal processing of metal parts. Their capabilities include annealing, stress relieving, age hardening, and handling large parts with vacuum furnace capacities up to 48 feet in length and 150,000 pounds in weight. Solar Atmospheres operates 24/7, ensuring responsive service and technical expertise. Their close relationship with affiliate Solar Manufacturing enhances their service quality and equipment innovation, as they continuously test and improve vacuum heat treating furnaces. The company serves various industries, including aerospace, defense, and medical device manufacturing, focusing on meeting specialized thermal processing needs.

Springboard encompasses several distinct entities operating in various sectors.

Spyderco is an American cutlery company founded in 1976 by Sal and Gail Glesser, based in Golden, Colorado. The company is recognized for its innovative approach to knife design, having introduced features that have become standard in the industry. Short Description:
Since our humble beginnings in the early 2000's as a ragtag group of cyclists wanting to host races better, Strike has grown into a global experiential marketing company, driving innovation, and making events easy for all.

We saw brands shift away from marketing in-person to virtual "social" spaces hyping the ability to connect and transact. Over the years we have all learned that these virtual connections are exactly as defined; almost or nearly a connection, but not as complete. The global pandemic especially highlighted humanity's need to connect face-to-face, and a surge in events as we recovered reaffirms that nothing substitutes for those meaningful connections in-person.

Strike seeks to streamline the grind for the Road Warriors that are out there staging event after event—passionately growing their brand through miles on the road, inclement weather, shoe string budgets, and emotional roller coasters. By refining details, improving materials, and providing unparalleled ease there will be no distractions from the meaningful connections you're trying to create with your customers, followers, athletes, partners, and fans.

Strike is more than the sum or parts of our products or services, it is style defined by substance: A unwavering reliability that you can trust from concept to design, from engineering to delivery, and from setup to take down. 

When beautifully curated events are easier to create, there's more time and energy to really connect and be remembered... Your audience is waiting.

UDC - Ultra Defense Corp is an American defense contractor based in Tampa, Florida, specializing in the manufacturing of small and medium caliber ammunition, weapons, and related military hardware. Founded in 2008, UDC operates three federally licensed facilities that design, test, and produce precision munitions and destructive devices for elite military and law enforcement customers worldwide.

The company is ISO 9001:2008 certified and registered with the U.S. Department of State and Department of Justice for the import, export, and manufacturing of defense articles. UDC employs between 51 and 200 staff, all U.S. nationals with expertise in government procurement and international defense contracts. Their offerings include a wide range of ammunition, specialized weapons, research and development for innovative military solutions, and military training services. UDC has been awarded numerous contracts exceeding $500 million, primarily serving the U.S. Army and Special Operations Command, and is recognized for its commitment to quality control and operational security.

The company started with a focus on moisture-wicking athletic wear designed to keep athletes cool and comfortable. The company offers a wide range of high-performance apparel, footwear, and accessories tailored for athletes across various sports. Under Armour is recognized for its innovative sportswear technology, including advanced cushioning systems in footwear. The brand has also expanded into digital fitness by acquiring fitness app companies, creating a large digital fitness community. UNIT Solutions is a California-based company that specializes in non-lethal firearms training systems. Their flagship product, the UNIT4 Training Rifle, is designed to replicate the look, feel, and recoil of a real AR platform while ensuring safety. This next-generation training rifle is classified as a non-firearm by the ATF, allowing for safe use in various environments without the need for an FFL license. It utilizes compressed air to launch projectiles, providing a realistic training experience without the hazards of traditional ammunition.

UNIT Solutions focuses on creating effective training opportunities for scenarios such as active shooter response and tactical training. Short Description:
VICTOR COMPANY

This year marks 15 years of innovation and precision at Victor Company, and I couldn't be more excited to share what's ahead. From the very beginning, our mission has been to engineer rock-solid products that give shooters the edge they need to perform at their best—and that commitment is stronger than ever.

Thank you for being part of this journey. Whether you've been with us since the start or are just discovering Victor Company, I'm proud to have you on board. Here's to 15 years—and to the next chapter of precision, innovation and excellence!

Heather Victor
President/Founder
Victor Company USA INC

VirTra, Inc. is a leading provider of judgmental use-of-force and firearms training simulators, established in 1993 and based in Chandler, Arizona. Originally founded as Ferris Productions, the company has transitioned from entertainment simulation to focus on advanced training technologies for law enforcement, military, educational, and commercial markets. VirTra is publicly traded on Nasdaq under the ticker symbol VTSI.

The company offers a variety of patented products, including the V-300 Simulator, which features a 300-degree immersive training environment, and the Threat-Fire™ Concussion Simulation System, which enhances training realism. Other offerings include the V-180 and V-100 Simulators, simulated recoil kits, and the V-Author software for custom scenario creation. VirTra also provides online training through its Virtual Interactive Coursework Training Academy (V-VICTA) and a subscription-based model called Subscription Training Equipment Partnership (STEP)™. Their services include custom content development and training support, ensuring effective use of their simulation systems.

Wilcox Industries designs, develops, and manufactures advanced tactical equipment for military, law enforcement, and first responders globally. Short Description:
ZEV Technologies, founded in 2006 by Alec Wolf in Oxnard, California, specializes in high-performance firearm components and custom firearms. Initially focused on aftermarket parts for Glock pistols, the company became known for pioneering drop-in replacement triggers that set a standard in competitive shooting. Over the years, ZEV expanded its offerings to include slides, barrels, frames, magazines, sights, and springs, all designed to enhance the performance and customization of Glock handguns.

In 2017, ZEV Technologies acquired Mega Arms, allowing the company to diversify into AR-15 rifle products. Today, ZEV provides award-winning pistols and rifles, along with a comprehensive range of premium upgrade parts. Their products are recognized for innovation and quality, appealing to competitive shooters, military personnel, law enforcement, and firearm enthusiasts. ZEV Technologies is committed to excellence and community engagement, contributing positively to its local area.

Short Description:
SUMMARY
Vector Optics has provided premium optics and innovative sighting systems for more than 15 years. 
We design, build and test our scopes & red dot sights for rifles and pistols to be used in all fields of applications for hunting, defense, sporting & competition.

BRAND EVOLUTION
The company originated under the name Sunclear but as time progressed Stephen wanted to change the name to something more product specific. Vector is defined as a quantity having direction as well as magnitude, especially as determining the position of one point in space relative to another. He was dwelling on this thought when an American partner suggested the name "Vector Optics". Stephen decided that name sounded more appropriate and thought it would be more widely recognized and remembered by optics consumers. Since that time Sunclear, was officially changed to the Vector Optics® and is still in use today.

PRODUCT ADVANTAGE
Why is Vector Optics the top brand for optics made in China? What is the difference between Vector Optics products and other optics made in China? 
Vector Optics delivers unmatched performance products with an unforgettable user experience at unbeatable prices. We build our products beyond your expectations. We provide precision aiming solutions and perfect shot over short, medium, and long range shooting.
Robust: Tremendously strong to withstand heavy recoil and just about everything else
Remarkable: Bright color, high resolution and virtually perfect image contrast
Reliable: Precision shots with every hunting, sporting and defense in any distance even at low light
Repeating: Accurate and positive adjustments allow fast & repeatable distance corrections

ACHIEVEMENT
Vector Optics has won many government contracts. Our products are implemented in various applications from recreational shooters to critical users such as: sporting marksman, avid hunters and tactical elites in arctic cold, desert heat and all in environments that can-and-will.

Short Description:
Worldpay is a prominent financial technology and payment processing company that delivers a wide array of payment services to merchants and financial institutions around the globe. With a processing capacity of approximately 40 billion transactions annually across 146 countries, it supports 135 currencies, positioning itself as one of the largest non-bank merchant acquirers in the world.

The company provides various payment processing solutions, including services for mail order, internet retailers, and point-of-sale transactions. Worldpay also offers multi-currency and multi-channel payment solutions, mobile card processing terminals, and alternative payment options for eCommerce merchants. Additionally, it provides loans to small businesses and operates technology platforms designed to handle high transaction volumes. Worldpay serves a diverse clientele, including multinational retailers, small businesses, and various vertical markets such as retail, restaurants, and financial institutions. Headquartered in Cincinnati, Ohio, with an international base in London, Worldpay employs around 8,500 people and operates in 25 countries.

Knight's Armament Company (KAC) is a leading American manufacturer based in Titusville, Florida, specializing in advanced small arms, weapon accessories, and suppressor technology. Founded in the late 1970s by C. Reed Knight, Jr., KAC focuses on meeting the unique needs of special operations and counter-terrorism communities. The company is recognized for its robust in-house processes in research, development, design, and manufacturing, which have established it as a key player in the defense industry.

KAC offers a range of products, including modular weapon systems like carbine rifles and machine guns, state-of-the-art suppressors, and advanced accessory rails. The company has pioneered innovations in firearm accessories, enhancing weapon modularity and effectiveness for military and law enforcement users. KAC's commitment to continuous improvement is reflected in its collaboration with U.S. and international special operations forces, ensuring that products are field-tested and refined based on real-world feedback. With ISO-9000 series quality certifications, KAC maintains a strong reputation for quality and innovation in defense manufacturing.

Koops Automation Systems is a full-service engineering and systems integration company based in Holland, Michigan. With over 30 years of experience, Koops specializes in designing, building, and integrating custom factory automation systems for various manufacturing industries. The company is employee-owned and is known for its strong engineering capabilities and exceptional customer support.

Koops offers a range of services, including project management, engineering consultation, 3D mechanical and electrical design, production line integration, and on-site training. They focus on IoT and Industry 4.0 solutions, providing clients with tools for remote monitoring and process optimization. Their automation technologies encompass robotic systems, conveyor integration, material handling, packaging, and more, tailored to meet the specific needs of manufacturers.

The company serves a diverse clientele, with a significant portion of its business in the automotive sector, as well as industries like life sciences, medical, and defense. Koops is committed to fostering long-term client relationships and ensuring seamless integration of their automation solutions.

Laguna Tools is a Texas-based manufacturer of woodworking and metalworking machinery, founded in 1983 by master woodworker Torben Helshoj. Originally established in Laguna Beach, California, the company has grown to offer a wide range of products, including heavy-duty band saws, table saws, sanders, lathes, CNC routers, CO2 lasers, and plasma cutters. With a commitment to innovation, Laguna Tools combines European design principles with American manufacturing standards.

Headquartered in Grand Prairie, Texas, Laguna Tools employs around 156 people and generates annual revenue of approximately $35.5 million. The company serves a diverse customer base, including hobbyist woodworkers, professional artisans, and industrial manufacturers. It focuses on providing high-quality, reliable machinery and engages in community outreach to enhance customer service. With a global supply chain, Laguna Tools designs its products in the U.S. while manufacturing primarily in Asia to ensure quality and cost-effectiveness.

Liberty Mountain is a leading wholesale distributor of technical outdoor products and climbing gear in the United States, operating since 1952. The company offers a vast selection of tens of thousands of products from over 1,000 brands, serving as a one-stop-shop for outdoor retail stores. They streamline inventory management by consolidating orders from various manufacturers into single shipments, which can be placed via phone, email, or online.

With major warehouses in Sandy, Utah, and Montoursville, Pennsylvania, Liberty Mountain ensures efficient logistics and timely delivery, providing 1-2 day ground shipping to most U.S. locations. Their extensive product range supports a variety of outdoor activities, including camping, hiking, rock climbing, and more. As the exclusive U.S. distributor for several prominent brands, Liberty Mountain enhances its product offerings and strengthens its market position. The company is also committed to the outdoor community, supporting organizations like the Climbing Wall Association and the American Alpine Club.

Short Description:
Marathon Watch Company Ltd. is a Canadian watch manufacturer with a history dating back to 1904. Originally founded as Weinsturm Watch, the company has evolved through various names before becoming Marathon Watch in 1939. It has a strong tradition of producing precision timepieces, particularly for military use, supplying watches to Allied Forces since 1941.

Marathon specializes in military-grade watches and timing instruments that combine durability with Swiss craftsmanship. Their products meet strict standards, including the United States Military Standard MIL-PRF-46374G, and are Swiss-made in La Chaux-de-Fonds. The company is the sole supplier of watches to the U.S. military, and their offerings include military watches designed for extreme conditions, stopwatches for specialized applications, and customized watches for military clients. Marathon serves a diverse clientele, including military organizations, government departments, collectors, and civilians who appreciate high-quality, reliable timepieces. The company remains family-run and committed to producing authentic military watches that uphold rigorous quality standards.

Short Description:
Meprolight is an Israeli electro-optics company established in 1990 and operates as part of the SK Group defense conglomerate. The company specializes in designing, manufacturing, and marketing advanced sighting systems and optical devices for military, law enforcement, and civilian markets globally. Meprolight is known for its durable and reliable optics, developed with input from the Israel Defense Forces, ensuring they meet practical battlefield requirements.

The product range includes tritium night sights for firearms, electro-optical systems like red dot sights, thermal sights, and night vision devices. Meprolight also provides specialized military optics used by elite units, as well as digital low-light handheld devices. The company adheres to strict quality control standards, maintaining defect rates below 1% and complying with international standards for quality and environmental sustainability.

Headquartered in Or Akiva, Israel, with a significant presence in Pennsylvania, USA, Meprolight serves a diverse customer base, including the Israel Defense Forces, global military and law enforcement agencies, and civilian markets, particularly in the United States. The company also supports retailers with customized plans to enhance commercial success.

Modig Machine Tool is a family-owned Swedish company founded in 1947 and based in Kalmar, Sweden. It specializes in developing, engineering, and manufacturing high-performance CNC machine tools and machining automation solutions. The company serves various industries, including aerospace, automotive, electric vehicles, space, energy, construction, and heavy equipment, focusing on enhancing productivity, precision, and cost-effectiveness.

Modig also offers comprehensive automation solutions, such as robotic machine loading and pallet systems, to improve operational efficiency. The company supports its customers with a robust international sales and service organization, ensuring optimal machine performance and customer satisfaction.

Their products are designed for elite users, including Special Forces, tactical law enforcement, and first responders across more than 60 countries. MOHOC combines advanced sport camera technology with insights from military professionals to create rugged and user-friendly equipment suitable for demanding environments.

The company specializes in fine mechanics and pyrotechnics, focusing on high-quality machinery for the industrial production of metallic and pyrotechnic elements. Nosler, Inc. is a family-owned American company based in Bend, Oregon, founded in 1948 by John A. Nosler. The company specializes in manufacturing high-quality ammunition, handloading components, and firearms, and is known for its innovative hunting bullet designs and precision manufacturing.

Nosler's product offerings include a range of high-performance hunting bullets such as the Partition, Ballistic Tip, Solid, E-Tip Lead-Free, and Varmageddon. The company is recognized as a leader in the design and manufacture of hunting bullets and ammunition, maintaining a strong reputation for innovation and performance in the shooting sports industry.

OTTO Engineering, Inc. is a U.S.-based manufacturer founded in 1961, located in Carpentersville, Illinois. The company specializes in designing and producing electro-mechanical control switches, grips, joysticks, and communications accessories. OTTO is recognized for its innovative products and strong manufacturing capabilities, which include injection molding, stamping, CNC machining, and 3D printing.

The company operates through two main divisions: OTTO Controls and OTTO Communications. OTTO Controls focuses on reliable switches and operator control solutions for demanding industries such as construction, military, and aerospace. OTTO Communications offers accessories for the two-way radio market, including headsets and tactical communications equipment. With a commitment to quality and community investment, OTTO manufactures all products domestically and holds multiple global accreditations, ensuring high standards in engineering and production.

Outdoor Channel is an American pay television network focused on outdoor lifestyle programming. Launched on April 1, 1994, it has become the largest outdoor TV network in the United States, reaching approximately 17 million households and available in over 50 countries. The channel features a variety of content, including hunting, fishing, shooting sports, off-road motorsports, adventure travel, and western lifestyle programming.

Originally founded in 1983 by the Gold Prospectors Association of America, Outdoor Channel has evolved to include a wide range of shows and events. Its programming includes hunting shows with experts, live fishing tournaments, shooting sports events, and environmental documentaries. The network is accessible through traditional cable, satellite TV, and various digital platforms, catering to outdoor enthusiasts, hunters, anglers, and adventure seekers. Under the ownership of Kroenke Sports Entertainment, Outdoor Channel continues to expand its reach and influence in outdoor media.

Short Description:
Das Unternehmen Schmidt & Bender wurde 1957 von Helmut Schmidt und Helmut Bender in Fellingshausen (Biebertal) gegründet. Was einst in einer Waschküche mit bescheidensten Mitteln begann entwickelte sich innerhalb weniger Jahre zu einem der weltweit führenden Hersteller von Präzisionszielfernrohren für Jagd, Sport, Polizei und Militär.

Wegweisend für den Erfolg dieses Unternehmens waren neben dem Erfindungsreichtum und einer gehörigen Portion Herzblut vor allem die Werte der Gründer. Höchste Präzision und Qualität war für den Feinmechaniker Helmut Schmidt und den Feinmechanikermeister Helmut Bender nicht nur Beruf sondern auch Berufung. Auch nach 65 Jahren ist Schmidt & Bender noch immer ein Familienunternehmen, das bald in dritter Generation die Werte und Traditionen der beiden Gründer erfolgreich weiterführt.

So meistern die Mitarbeiterinnen und Mitarbeiter von Schmidt & Bender ihre selbst gesetzte Herausforderung: die Ansprüche der Kunden nicht nur zu erfüllen, sondern zu übertreffen.

Sierra Bullets, LLC is an American manufacturer of high-precision bullets for firearms, established in 1947. Founded by three aircraft machinists in California, the company was created to meet the demand for quality bullets following World War II. Since 1990, Sierra has been based in Sedalia, Missouri, where it operates a state-of-the-art manufacturing facility, including an underground test range for accuracy testing.

The company produces a wide range of bullets for rifles and pistols, covering calibers from .204 to .500. Their product lineup includes well-known brands such as Sierra MatchKing, Sierra GameKing, and Sierra BlitzKing, recognized for their accuracy and quality. Sierra Bullets serves a diverse customer base, including hunters, sport shooting enthusiasts, law enforcement, and military professionals. The company is known for its commitment to precision and reliability, making it a trusted name in the firearms industry. In 2017, Sierra was acquired by Clarus Corporation, enhancing its position in bullet technology and innovation.

The State of Wyoming is the official government entity of Wyoming, overseeing its executive, legislative, and judicial branches. It administers state laws, policies, and public services to residents, operating under a traditional state government structure with a Governor, a bicameral Legislature, and a judicial system led by the Wyoming Supreme Court.

Wyoming provides a variety of public services through its branches and agencies. The Legislature enacts laws and manages the state budget, while the Governor and elected officials handle administration, public safety, and education. The judicial branch ensures justice through district courts and the Supreme Court. Additionally, the state supports local governments and manages public administration functions, including transparency initiatives and citizen services.

The primary beneficiaries of the State of Wyoming's services are its residents, businesses, local governments, and visitors. The government focuses on delivering essential public services and regulatory oversight to promote the welfare and development of the state's population and economy.

Swarovski Optik is an Austrian company founded in 1949 by Wilhelm Swarovski, specializing in high-precision optical instruments. As a division of the Swarovski group, it utilizes advanced glass production techniques originally developed for jewelry. The company is renowned for its premium long-range optical products, including binoculars, spotting scopes, rifle scopes, telescopes, range finders, and night sight devices.

Swarovski Optik is committed to innovation and quality, having pioneered several optical technologies. Its product lineup features models like the Habicht binoculars and the EL series, designed for outdoor enthusiasts, hunters, and nature lovers. The company has earned a global reputation for excellence in sport optics and holds a Royal Warrant as a supplier to the United Kingdom’s Queen Elizabeth II.

With a strong emphasis on environmental sustainability, Swarovski Optik integrates eco-friendly practices into its production processes and supports nature conservation initiatives. The company also invests in vocational training for precision optics, reflecting its dedication to craftsmanship and education.

Originally founded as Armson USA, the company transitioned to Trijicon and began producing night sights that utilize tritium illumination, which lasts up to 15 years without batteries. Their flagship product, the Advanced Combat Optical Gunsight (ACOG), was introduced in 1987 and has been widely adopted by the U.S. military, including the Marine Corps.

Trijicon offers a diverse range of optical products, including night sights for handguns, red dot optics like the MRO-C, and AccuPoint® riflescopes designed for hunters and sport shooters. Their products are known for their durability and precision, making them suitable for military, law enforcement, and civilian use. Trijicon is recognized for its innovative technology in firearm optics, providing reliable solutions for various shooting applications.

Short Description:
Wilson Tool International is a leading manufacturer of tooling systems for the sheet metal fabrication industry. Established in 1966 in St. Paul, Minnesota, the company has expanded to include over 900 employees and manufacturing facilities in multiple countries, including the United States, England, China, Brazil, Italy, and Canada.

The company specializes in designing and producing tooling solutions for punch presses, press brakes, and punch and die components. Their products enhance the performance of machinery used in bending, punching, and stamping applications across various sectors such as automotive, aerospace, military, agricultural equipment, HVAC, and food and beverage manufacturing. Wilson Tool is recognized for its innovative and customized solutions, holding 91 patents for technologies that improve fabrication processes.

Headquartered in White Bear Lake, Minnesota, Wilson Tool International features a large manufacturing space dedicated to research and development, engineering, and marketing. The company also has a global network of sales engineers and distributors, ensuring support for its diverse customer base around the world.

Short Description:
Walmart Inc. is a multinational retail corporation founded in 1962 by Sam Walton and headquartered in Bentonville, Arkansas. It is one of the largest and most profitable retailers globally and the largest private employer in the United States, with over one million employees. Walmart's mission is to help people save money and live better, which has guided its growth from a single store to thousands of locations worldwide.

The company operates various retail formats, including discount stores, supercenters that combine general merchandise with groceries, and membership-only warehouse clubs under the Sam's Club brand. Walmart offers a wide range of products, including groceries, apparel, electronics, and home goods, catering to a diverse customer base. Known for its "Every Day Low Prices" strategy, Walmart leverages high sales volume and efficient supply chain management to provide competitive pricing.

Walmart has embraced technology and innovation, investing in e-commerce and supply chain automation to enhance customer experience. Its business model focuses on inventory control and cost efficiencies, contributing to its sustained growth and market presence across five continents.

Short Description:
Hornady Manufacturing Company is a family-owned American manufacturer of ammunition and reloading products, established in 1949 by Joyce Hornady in Grand Island, Nebraska. The company began as a small garage operation and has grown to be the largest independently owned bullet maker in the industry. Hornady was founded to provide effective hunting ammunition, developing reliable and reloadable bullets, including the flagship .30-caliber 150-grain Spire Point.

Hornady offers a diverse range of products, including precision bullets, factory-loaded ammunition for rifles, pistols, and shotguns, as well as comprehensive reloading tools and components. Their custom ammunition lines and Frontier ammunition brand, which includes recycled cartridge cases, further showcase their commitment to innovation. Hornady's products are popular among hunters, sport shooters, competitive shooters, and reloaders who seek high-quality and accurate ammunition. The company continues to operate from its headquarters in Grand Island, Nebraska, upholding its dedication to quality and craftsmanship.

InVeris Training Solutions is a global leader in integrated live-fire and virtual weapons training systems. Based in Suwanee, Georgia, the company operates from a 235,000-square-foot facility and employs over 400 people across multiple countries, including the United States, Australia, Canada, and the United Kingdom. InVeris was formed through the combination of three legacy companies, bringing together decades of expertise in firearms training.

The company offers advanced live-fire training systems, including bullet traps and target retrieval systems, suitable for military, law enforcement, and commercial shooting ranges. InVeris also provides virtual and simulation training solutions, such as the VR-DT virtual reality system, which enhances decision-making and marksmanship skills through scenario-based training. Their integrated training solutions combine both live-fire and virtual technologies to improve performance under pressure, ensuring users can make informed and safe decisions in critical situations.

The company serves a diverse customer base, including large enterprises, and emphasizes compliance, security, and collaboration through dashboards and analytics for tracking contract data.

Kennametal, Inc. is a global manufacturer known for high-performance cutting tools and engineered components. Founded in 1938 in Latrobe, Pennsylvania, the company has its roots in the Vanadium Alloys Steel Company, established in 1910. Kennametal gained recognition for developing a tungsten-titanium carbide alloy, which significantly improved steel cutting capabilities.

The company offers a diverse range of products, including advanced cutting tools, wear-resistant materials, and engineered components. These products are designed to enhance machining precision, speed, and durability across various industries such as aerospace, defense, transportation, and energy. Kennametal emphasizes innovation in materials science and technical expertise to provide solutions that help customers improve productivity and competitiveness.

With a global presence in nearly 100 countries and a dedicated workforce of approximately 8,700 employees, Kennametal continues to address complex manufacturing challenges. Its legacy of innovation and commitment to customer-focused solutions has established Kennametal as a trusted partner in high-performance manufacturing for over 85 years.

KEYENCE has a significant global presence, with 16 international organizations and warehouses in multiple countries. Recognized for its commitment to innovation and quality, KEYENCE is a trusted partner in industrial automation worldwide.

Headquartered in Melbourne, Florida, it employs around 48,000 people and generates annual revenues of approximately $18-19 billion. The company operates in over 100 countries, delivering advanced technology solutions across air, land, sea, space, and cyber domains.

Lenco Armored Vehicles is a family-owned American company based in Pittsfield, Massachusetts, established in 1981. The company specializes in designing and manufacturing high-quality armored vehicles, expanding from a small facility to a nearly 200,000 square-foot manufacturing campus. Lenco is committed to innovation, quality, and customer-focused engineering.

The company’s product line includes tactical armored response and rescue vehicles, primarily the BEAR and BearCat models. The BEAR was initially designed for military use, while the BearCat is tailored for law enforcement and special operations teams. These vehicles are engineered to withstand high-caliber weapons and provide critical protection in hostile environments. Lenco serves a diverse range of customers, including police departments, military branches, and various U.S. government agencies, with over 6,000 vehicles produced and operational in more than 40 countries. Their focus on ergonomic design and precision manufacturing ensures that their vehicles meet the needs of national defense, counter-terrorism, and emergency response operations.

Magnum Photos is a prestigious photographic cooperative founded in 1947 by renowned photographers including Robert Capa and Henri Cartier-Bresson. It is recognized as one of the leading picture agencies, specializing in documentary and photojournalistic work that captures significant historical and cultural moments.

The cooperative's mission is to protect photographic authorship and provide photographers with the freedom to pursue their vision. Members retain full copyright of their images, ensuring creative control and ethical representation. Magnum supports a diverse roster of international photographers who cover a wide range of subjects, including war, politics, culture, and social issues. The agency maintains an extensive archive of iconic images and offers photographic prints, books, exhibitions, and licensing for editorial and commercial use.

Magnum Photos serves a global clientele, including media organizations, publishers, museums, galleries, and private collectors. Its commitment to authentic visual storytelling and artistic excellence makes it a sought-after source for impactful documentary photography.

Midwest Shooting Center is an indoor shooting range and retail center located in Cridersville, Ohio. Founded in 2016 and operating since 2019, it features modern facilities designed for both beginners and experienced shooters. The center emphasizes safety, education, and customer service, creating a welcoming environment for all firearms enthusiasts.

The company offers a variety of services, including a 24-lane indoor shooting range with advanced technology, firearms training for various skill levels, and a large retail department with a wide selection of firearms and accessories. Additional services include custom gunsmithing, firearm rentals, and exclusive membership programs that provide access to a members-only lounge. As the first indoor shooting range-retail franchise in the U.S., Midwest Shooting Center supports franchisees with a proven business model and comprehensive resources. The company has been recognized for its rapid growth, ranking on the 2024 Inc. 5000 list of America’s fastest-growing private companies.

Short Description:
Mistral Group is a consortium of independent companies focused on defense, law enforcement, public safety, and industrial markets. Key member Mistral Inc. has over 34 years of experience providing solutions to military and law enforcement agencies in North America. The company operates a secure production facility in Maryland, offering services that include research and development, manufacturing, assembly, integration, and testing. Mistral Inc. is a woman-owned small business certified to ISO 9001:2015 quality standards.

Mistral Inc. delivers advanced systems and products tailored to military and public safety needs. Their capabilities encompass complex manufacturing, in-house fabrication, and robust supply chain management. The company offers specialized products such as blast management systems, communication shelters, counter-UAV technologies, and C4ISR sensors. The broader Mistral Group also markets aerosol drug testing kits for law enforcement, enabling rapid detection of substances. Mistral Inc. serves a diverse client base, including federal, state, and local law enforcement agencies, as well as defense organizations across North America.

Short Description:
The San Diego County Sheriff's Office (SDSO) is a major law enforcement agency serving San Diego County, California, since 1850. It is the largest sheriff's office in the county and one of the largest in the United States, employing over 4,200 personnel with an annual budget exceeding $1.3 billion. The SDSO operates across more than 4,500 square miles, including a 60-mile international border.

The SDSO provides a wide range of law enforcement and public safety services, primarily to unincorporated areas of the county and through contracts with nine incorporated cities. Its organizational structure includes five main service bureaus: Law Enforcement Services, Detention Facility Services, Court Services, Human Resource Services, and Management Services. The office also manages multiple jails and detention centers, offers courtroom security, and has specialized units for air support, search and rescue, and tactical operations. The current Sheriff, Kelly Martinez, took office in 2023.

Nite Ize, Inc. is a product design and manufacturing company based in Boulder, Colorado, founded in 1989 by Rick Case. The company started with the Headband Mini Flashlight Holder and has since expanded to offer over 500 innovative products worldwide. Nite Ize focuses on creating practical solutions that organize life, protect gear, and provide lighting options, emphasizing quality and functionality.

Their product range includes lighting accessories, such as hands-free flashlight holders and LED technology, as well as versatile tools like the S-Biner double-sided carabiner. The company serves a diverse customer base, including outdoor enthusiasts and professionals, and sells its products through retail partners and directly to consumers.

Nite Ize is committed to integrity and customer satisfaction, backed by a "Worry Free Guarantee." Founder Rick Case continues to influence the company's culture of creativity and attention to detail, ensuring that their products enhance everyday life and outdoor adventures.

North American Rescue, LLC (NAR) is dedicated to reducing preventable deaths by providing high-quality medical products designed for challenging casualty care situations. Headquartered in Greer, South Carolina, NAR employs a team of experts, including former Special Operations medics and military medical officers, to develop innovative lifesaving solutions. Their products are based on Tactical Combat Casualty Care (TCCC) guidelines and evidence-based medicine.

NAR offers a wide range of medical products for tactical and emergency care, such as tourniquets, emergency trauma dressings, junctional treatment tools, and hypothermic treatment sacks. These products are designed to empower responders to act quickly in life-threatening emergencies, enhancing survivability in unpredictable environments. NAR serves a diverse customer base, including military forces, federal agencies, civilian law enforcement, and emergency medical services, with a commitment to American-made quality and innovation.

Short Description:
Nucor Corporation is a prominent American steel producer and recycler based in Charlotte, North Carolina. Founded in 1905, the company transitioned to steel production in the mid-1960s and adopted the Nucor name in 1972. It is recognized for pioneering electric arc furnace (EAF) mini-mill technology, which allows for efficient and cost-effective steel production through the recycling of scrap metal.

As the largest steel producer in the United States and the leading recycler in the Western Hemisphere, Nucor operates a network of mini-mills and regional plants. The company manufactures a diverse range of steel products, including bars, joists, girders, sheets, and other structural components used in construction, manufacturing, and infrastructure projects. Nucor serves various sectors, including construction, automotive, energy, and manufacturing, emphasizing operational efficiency and a teammate-focused culture that has contributed to its growth as a Fortune 500 enterprise.

Pioneer Metal Finishing is a leading metal finishing company based in Green Bay, Wisconsin, with over 75 years of experience. Founded in 1945, it operates nine manufacturing locations across the U.S. Midwest, West Coast, and Mexico, employing more than 1,000 people and managing over 1 million square feet of production space.

The company specializes in high-precision metal finishing services, including zinc and manganese phosphate coatings, aluminum anodizing, plating, coating, rubber-to-metal bonding, and parts washing and blasting. It serves a wide range of industries such as aerospace, automotive, medical, electronics, and defense, processing over 560 million parts annually. Pioneer is committed to quality, customer trust, and environmental responsibility, offering full process control and flexible delivery options. The company is privately owned by Aterian Investment Partners and has reported significant revenue, approximately $271.6 million. Its corporate culture emphasizes core values that focus on serving customers, employees, and the community.

Short Description:
Powertac is an American owned and operated company based in Greensboro North Carolina. We create premium tactical lights to withstand the toughest conditions of combat or law enforcement. We blended our American ingenuity, premium craftsmanship, and cutting-edge technology to create a rugged, battle-tested tool to trust your life with.

Our lights are used by law enforcement and first responder agencies all over the world including the Israeli Defense Force, Israeli National Police, branches of the Secret Service and FBI, as well as hundreds of local law enforcement agencies across the US. We overbuild our lights for durability and safety because we know every day police officers and soldiers are trusting their lives with our lights and we want to be able to go to sleep knowing we've done all we can to keep people safe.

We want our lights to be on the cutting edge of flashlight technology and be truly tactical tools which is why we listen to our customers and are constantly improving our products. As a vertically integrated company, we manage every aspect of the business from product design to distribution through our talented manufacturing, marketing, distribution and Research & Development teams. We proudly stand by our products with the best no-hassle lifetime warranty in the industry and friendly US based customer service.

We've combined the three elements of tactical lights (solid reliability, cutting edge technology, and simple tactical interface) to make what we believe are the best tactical lights on the market. With industry-leading tactical features, our lights are built to serve you in the toughest conditions when you need it most. Since 2006, our mission has been to provide nothing short of the ultimate lighting device.

Short Description:
Precision Resource, Inc. is a leader in precision metal manufacturing, specializing in fineblanking technology. Founded in 1947 and based in Shelton, Connecticut, the company operates over 100 fineblanking presses, the largest number worldwide, with production facilities in North America, Europe, and Asia.

The company excels in producing precise metal components with complex geometries through a single-step fineblanking process. This method allows for the creation of parts with small holes and clean edges from rolled stock of varying thicknesses. Precision Resource also offers value-added services, including advanced machining, grinding, assembly, and custom tooling design, providing comprehensive solutions for its clients.

Serving a wide range of industries such as automotive, electronics, and medical equipment, Precision Resource is committed to quality and service excellence, with all facilities certified to IATF 16949 standards. The company emphasizes sustainability through energy-efficient practices and continuous investment in research and development. With around 775 employees and annual revenues of approximately $289 million, Precision Resource combines experience with advanced technology to meet the needs of its global customer base.

Princeton Tec is a family-owned American manufacturer based in Pennsauken, New Jersey, specializing in personal lighting products since 1975. Founded by Bill Stephens, the company initially created the first automatic dive timer, the "Bottom Timer," which transformed how scuba divers track their underwater time. Over the years, Princeton Tec has shifted its focus to innovative lighting solutions, becoming a leader in durable, high-performance lights for various professional and recreational applications.

The company offers a wide range of personal lighting systems designed for outdoor enthusiasts, tactical users, industrial workers, and scuba professionals. Notable products include scuba lights, LED headlamps, and specialized lighting for activities such as hiking, camping, and cycling. Princeton Tec is committed to 100% American manufacturing, ensuring quality and supporting local employment while continuously innovating in lighting technology. With over 40 years of expertise, Princeton Tec remains dedicated to providing reliable and user-focused lighting products.

Short Description:
QuiqLite Inc. (Quick Light) is a progressive company founded by Brian Quittner, a 15 year California Law Enforcement veteran. QuiqLite was invented after recognizing the need for a hands-free concealed light source that could fit into a uniform shirt pocket for reading, writing and maneuvering in the dark.

Because of QuiqLite's unique design, ease of use and dependability, QuiqLite Inc. has become a known and trusted name in the world of public safety. Police Officers, Paramedics, Search & Rescue, Firefighters, Military and many others use and depend on QuiqLite Products to help make their jobs easier and safer while working in the dark!

Our products have been field tested in a variety of applications from casual contacts, tactical applications, search and rescue operations and a variety of challenging conditions where a hands-free light source is preferred.

Unlike other flashlights that impair your night vision by producing too much light, QuiqLite products are specifically designed to keep your night vision intact by providing just the right amount of light to get the job done!
