Short Description:
Raptor Workholding Products from TE-CO Manufacturing get out of your way so you can get the job done! Speed up your machining processes and avoid costly crashes by making all five sides of the workpiece accessible in a single set-up. Raptor's patented dovetail design and locating pin quickly lock parts in place with extreme accuracy and clamping force. And unlike other workholding products, the spring-loaded clamp can be tightened with a simple T-handle wrench. Quick and easy. 

The Raptor system is also modular, with a wide range of adapters, risers, fixtures, and zero-point options that speed setups and eliminate clamping headaches, even in tight quarters or when machining multiple parts per cycle. Whatever the brand or model of CNC machining center, Raptor has a configuration to make five-axis workholding fast, flexible, and accurate. And when accompanied by one of Raptor's Piranha brand modular coolant systems, you can rest assured that cutting fluid delivery will be equally accurate and secure. Goodbye, plastic lines. 

Raptor. Because it's all about time.

Short Description:
REGG Inspection specializes in designing and manufacturing high-precision inspection and sorting systems for the fastener industry, including screws, bolts, nuts, rivets, and threads. The company provides fully automatic, high-speed inspection machines that can process up to 20 parts per second, enhancing production efficiency through reliable quality control.

Their product lineup features the i600 Series for comprehensive inspection, the i300 Series for fast vision inspection, and the Cube system for first article inspection of single parts or small lots. REGG Inspection's systems are modular and can incorporate advanced technologies such as vision systems, dimensional laser checking, and eddy current crack detection. They focus on custom solutions, tailoring systems to meet specific customer needs and ensuring optimal inspection quality.

Headquartered in Wixom, Michigan, REGG Inspection is supported by a skilled technical team with extensive industry experience, offering expert assistance and ongoing support. The company also has a presence in Italy and collaborates with distributors in the U.S. to serve a global customer base.

Short Description:
REGO-FIX Group is a Swiss family-owned company established in 1950, known for its invention of the original ER collet system in 1973, which set a new standard in toolholding design. The company specializes in manufacturing premium toolholding systems that are recognized for their reliability, precision, and quality. All products are produced and rigorously tested at their ISO-certified facility in Tenniken, Switzerland.

The product range includes toolholding solutions such as ER collets and collet chucks, widely used in machining industries for securing cutting tools with high accuracy. REGO-FIX's innovations have influenced industry standards, with the ER collet chuck being standardized under DIN 6499 in 1993. Their systems cater to various sectors, including automotive, aerospace, medical, and gear manufacturing, where precision is essential.

With a strong global presence, REGO-FIX operates in North America through a subsidiary in Indiana, USA, providing expert service and support to customers in the region. The company emphasizes Swiss-made quality and upholds family values, focusing on social responsibility and ethical business practices.

REV Group, Inc. is a specialty vehicle manufacturer based in Brookfield, Wisconsin. Founded in 2010, the company operates 24 brands across 14 U.S. states and is publicly traded on the New York Stock Exchange under the ticker REVG. REV Group designs, manufactures, and distributes a wide range of specialty vehicles and related aftermarket parts and services, focusing on three main segments: Fire & Emergency, Commercial, and Recreation.

The company's product offerings include custom-engineered fire trucks, ambulances, commercial buses, and recreational vehicles. REV Group's fire apparatus is tailored for municipal fire departments, while its ambulances prioritize patient safety and ergonomic design. The company also produces various recreational vehicles, including motorhomes and luxury coaches. Additionally, REV Group provides aftermarket support, vehicle maintenance, and financial services, ensuring a comprehensive approach to serving its customers. With over 210,000 units in service, REV Group is committed to quality and safety, particularly for first responders.

Rollomatic Inc. is the North American subsidiary of Rollomatic SA, a Swiss company founded in 1989. It specializes in designing and manufacturing high-precision CNC machines for grinding cutting tools, cylindrical grinding, and laser machining of ultra-hard materials. The company has its roots in the Swiss watch industry and has evolved to produce advanced grinding machines that meet complex precision standards.

The company offers complete manufacturing solutions for precision tool and part grinding, including CNC grinding machines, cylindrical grinders, and fully automatic 6-axis grinding centers. Rollomatic emphasizes Swiss engineering craftsmanship and precision assembly, with manufacturing taking place at a modern production site in Switzerland. The company integrates sustainable practices, such as using photovoltaic panels for energy.

Rollomatic Inc. serves industries like automotive, aerospace, medical, electronics, and watchmaking, providing tailored solutions through a global network. Established in 1993 and headquartered in Mundelein, Illinois, it acts as the North American hub for distribution, customer service, and customization, ensuring optimal machine performance and longevity.

S&S Precision, LLC is a Virginia Beach-based company established in 2007, specializing in manufacturing and engineering solutions for military, federal government, and law enforcement customers. The company provides precision machining, design engineering, and fabrication services tailored to the needs of special forces and tactical operations.

Their offerings include precision machining of various materials, advanced CAD/CAM programming, and CNC equipment to produce high-quality machined parts. Additional capabilities include injection molding, thermoforming, cerakote coating, laser engraving, sewing, and hydro dipping, allowing for extensive product customization. The company develops OEM products designed for military and special operations, focusing on durability and performance.

S&S Precision serves a specialized clientele, including military branches, special forces units, and law enforcement agencies. With a dedicated workforce of fewer than 50 employees and annual revenues around $7.1 million, the company emphasizes high-quality, timely delivery of precision parts and assemblies that meet military specifications.

Savage Arms Inc. is a private firearms manufacturer founded in 1894 by Arthur Savage in Utica, New York, and is now headquartered in Westfield, Massachusetts. The company has a rich history of innovation, particularly known for the iconic Model 99 rifle, which has maintained its original design over the years. Savage Arms has established itself as a key player in the firearms industry, producing affordable and reliable firearms for hunters, sport shooters, law enforcement, and military personnel.

The product lineup includes a variety of sporting rifles, such as the Model 99 and various bolt-action models, as well as double-barrel shotguns and combination guns like the Model 24. The company also offers the "Striker" hunting handgun, ammunition, reloading tools, sights, and hunting knives. Additionally, Savage Arms develops environmentally safe firing range systems branded as SNAIL, utilized by police, military, and private shooting clubs around the world. The company sells its products through gun shops and sporting goods retailers, catering to a diverse global customer base.

The company focuses on producing high-quality, American-made AR-15 and AR-10 style rifles and parts. Short Description:
The U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service (USFWS) is a federal agency within the U.S. Department of the Interior, dedicated to the conservation and enhancement of fish, wildlife, plants, and their habitats. Established in 1940, it is the nation’s oldest conservation agency, with a mission to work collaboratively for the benefit of the American people. USFWS manages extensive natural resources, including the National Wildlife Refuge System, which spans 150 million acres, and oversees numerous fish hatcheries and ecological services.

USFWS fulfills its mission through various functions, such as enforcing wildlife laws, protecting endangered species, managing migratory bird populations, and restoring fisheries. The agency also engages the public through outdoor recreational activities and educational initiatives, promoting an understanding of natural resources. Its stakeholders include federal, state, tribal, and local governments, as well as private landowners and conservation organizations, all working together to support wildlife conservation efforts.

W. R. Case & Sons Cutlery Company is a historic American manufacturer of premium, hand-crafted knives, established in 1889 by the Case brothers. Short Description:
Columbia Southern University (CSU) is a private, for-profit online university founded in 1993 by Dr. Robert G. Mayes Sr. The university aims to change lives through education by providing affordable and flexible academic opportunities. CSU offers a wide range of programs, including 26 degree programs and 21 certificate programs, spanning fields such as environmental management, business administration, computer science, and health administration.

CSU emphasizes a flexible learning format with open enrollment and maximum transfer credit, catering to working adults and military personnel. The university is accredited by the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools Commission on Colleges (SACSCOC) and the Distance Education Accrediting Commission (DEAC). With over 22,000 students worldwide, CSU is recognized for its commitment to quality education and has received awards for outstanding course design and community engagement. The university also partners with Waldorf University to expand its online degree offerings.

Short Description:
YETI Holdings, Inc. is an outdoor consumer goods company based in Austin, Texas, founded in 2006 by brothers Roy and Ryan Seiders. The company was established to create durable, high-performance coolers that meet the needs of outdoor enthusiasts. YETI's mission is to design products that last for generations, allowing adventurers to enjoy the outdoors for longer periods.

Initially focused on virtually indestructible coolers, YETI has since expanded its product line to include stainless steel drinkware, bags, apparel, and outdoor living products. The company targets serious outdoor enthusiasts, such as hunters, fishers, and campers, who prioritize durability and performance in their gear. YETI is recognized for its high-quality offerings, including coolers known for their toughness and ice retention, as well as drinkware designed to keep beverages at the desired temperature. 

With a strong brand reputation and a loyal customer base, YETI has evolved its business model to include partnerships with major retailers and has experienced global expansion since its initial public offering in 2018.

Short Description:
LOWA Boots LLC is a premium outdoor footwear company founded in 1923 by Bavarian cobbler Lorenz Wagner in Jetzendorf, Germany. The name "LOWA" comes from the first two letters of Wagner's first and last names. Initially focused on heavy work brogues, the company quickly expanded into Alpine boots and ski boots, establishing a reputation for high-quality outdoor footwear.

LOWA operates four factories, including its main facility in Germany, which produces traditional trekking boots, and additional factories in Italy and Slovakia that focus on mountaineering boots and innovative polyurethane-injected products. The company offers a wide range of footwear, including trekking boots, mountaineering boots, lightweight hiking shoes, ski boots, and specialized Alpine footwear. LOWA is known for its commitment to quality and innovation, having pioneered manufacturing techniques like PU injection molding and developed influential products such as the "Air" ski boot and the Trekker hiking boot.

LOWA serves outdoor enthusiasts, hikers, mountaineers, and professionals who need reliable footwear for challenging environments. The company has a history of supplying military boots and collaborating with experienced climbers for expeditions.

Short Description:
Merit3D is a Utah-based company that specializes in additive manufacturing solutions, focusing on the rapid mass production of plastic parts through advanced resin 3D printing technology. The company aims to significantly reduce production lead times, enabling faster time-to-market for its customers. Merit3D's proprietary "protoduction" process ensures that prototypes are consistent with final mass-produced parts, eliminating discrepancies.

The company serves manufacturers and businesses that require plastic parts, particularly those facing supply chain disruptions or needing quick production without the delays of traditional methods. Merit3D has demonstrated its capabilities with large-scale orders, including a notable contract to deliver one million 3D printed parts to Adhesive Technology Corporation. By reshoring production to the U.S., Merit3D offers cost-effective, high-quality parts with fast turnaround times, positioning itself as a competitive alternative to traditional manufacturing.

MIRA Safety is a family-owned manufacturer and distributor based in Austin, Texas, specializing in personal protective equipment (PPE) for Chemical, Biological, Radiological, and Nuclear (CBRN) defense. Founded in 2018 by Roman Zrazhevskiy, the company focuses on providing reliable and innovative emergency-preparedness gear for both professional and civilian use.

Their product range includes gas masks, filters, hazmat suits, tactical gear, and powered air-purifying respirators (PAPR), designed to protect against CBRN threats. MIRA Safety's products are manufactured in the Czech Republic, Israel, and the United States, and cater to a diverse clientele, including military personnel, first responders, law enforcement, and civilians, as well as children and pets. The company emphasizes quality and innovation, with products recognized for meeting and exceeding industry standards. MIRA Safety operates primarily through e-commerce, shipping to over 175 countries, and supports its offerings with educational resources and customer service.

Short Description:
Mirion is a global leader in radiation safety, science, and medicine, headquartered in Atlanta, Georgia. The company employs around 2,800 people and operates in 12 countries. Mirion focuses on two main segments: the Mirion Technologies Group, which advances nuclear energy and industrial applications through radiation safety technologies, and the Mirion Medical Group, which enhances cancer care quality with medical solutions for radiation therapy and diagnostic imaging.

The company's product portfolio includes radiation detection instruments, nuclear measurement systems, digital integration solutions, and regulatory compliance tools. Mirion has expanded its capabilities through strategic acquisitions, enhancing its offerings in radiation safety and digital technologies. It serves a diverse range of customers, including nuclear power plants, defense organizations, medical institutions, and industrial companies. Mirion also partners with organizations like RAD-AID International to promote radiology and radiation safety education globally. The company has shown strong financial growth, reporting record revenues of $860.8 million for the full year 2024.

Nation's Best Sports (NBS) is a nationwide buying group for independently owned sporting goods retailers, established in 1956. Originally founded as the Southwest Buying Syndicate, NBS has grown to become a leading organization in North America, helping retailers leverage their purchasing power to access volume discounts directly from manufacturers.

NBS empowers its members by providing marketing support and service opportunities. The organization connects over 350 retail members, representing more than 1,200 storefronts, with a diverse portfolio of buying opportunities across various categories, including outdoor sports, athletic equipment, and apparel. NBS hosts exclusive buying Markets, where retailers can meet vendors to place orders at pre-negotiated prices, ensuring competitive purchasing. Additionally, NBS publishes a magazine that highlights the achievements of its members and partners in the sporting goods industry, reinforcing the strength of independent retail.

Short Description:
SECURAM has been dedicated to designing and manufacturing innovative security solutions since 1991.  Early in our history, we developed some of the first contactless access control door lock systems used in hotels and commercial buildings.  Always striving to improve our products, we integrated biometric fingerprint authentication into these lock systems. 

Adjacent security industries soon came to recognize the technological acumen of SECURAM and began requesting our development of security systems for other markets.  

The high security safe lock market had been struggling to deliver innovative technological solutions, so after numerous requests from this market, we began our development of a complete line of electronic locks for safes. Now 12 years later, we have introduced over 150 different high security safe lock products. These safe lock solutions are used all over the world in banks, ATMs, cash safes, personal and gun safes. Everywhere highly valuable items are stored, SECURAM  products are sure to be found. 

As the smart home movement started with the introduction of various IOT devices for the home, safe owners began looking for ways to connect their safes also. SECURAM  took on the challenge and developed a series of connected safe lock systems that could be managed and controlled from a smartphone app. 

As our expertise with smart technologies expanded, we came to recognize the necessity of improved security of the devices offered in the smart home segment. Thus, our team of talented engineers set out to integrate the high security protocols developed for the safe lock market into secure devices for smart homes. Today, we have a broad array of highly secure smart devices for the connected home. From biometric smart locks for your front door, to perimeter security sensors, and smart garage door controllers, SECURAM  ​can be trusted to keep guard over your family and home. 

Welcome to SECURAM Smart Home Security.

Short Description:
Our mission is to deliver the best products to enable all outdoor enthusiasts to enjoy the greatest comfort and performance in any cold weather activity.

Our Mantra:
To foster a culture where commitment to excellence in product innovation, quality and customer service permeates all we do. To deliver the best products to enable all outdoor enthusiasts to enjoy the highest level of comfort and performance in any cold weather activity.  The R&D process never ends for us and we continue to search out and use the very best materials and workmanship.

How it all started:
Seirus grew out of 2 guys intent on creating solutions to issues that limited the winter experience of the outdoor enthusiast. One looking to help preserve the boot/binding compatibility for more predictable release while skiing. Thus Cat Tracks were born, which also make for a more comfortable & secure walking experience on winter surfaces. And the other wanting to shield his chops during frequent forays into that sweet Utah powder. Viola, the Original Masque was born. While neither of these young outdoor entrepreneurs ever imagined one day these pocket sized, self-fashioned gems would actually put food on the table, they were ambitious & eager to take their new inventions to the market. 

Flash forward 3 decades and families of products are thriving and engineered to keep you warm like no one else. Now over 300 cold weather protection items and a burgeoning crop of sun protection products are the fruit of the combined imaginations of Seirus'​ development team, striving to bring both comfort and protection to al of us who love the snowy outdoors. Seirus has been the industry's major innovator & first to market for products to protect the head, hands & feet.

Short Description:
Maximum protection in a versatile and mobile design: SOB™ Defense Systems incorporate an optimal balance of protection, mobility, and versatility for real world operations. In an ideal world, an ops team would have impenetrable, mobile, weightless defense systems to protect them from every possible form of danger. In the real world, this level of protection is not practical. Think of being inside an underground nuclear bunker; it offers protection from almost anything, but severely limits operational flexibility! SOB™ Defense Systems provide the highest level of protection possible while allowing for mobility, agility, and overall versatility in a variety of circumstances.

SOB™ Defense Systems fill the gap between body armor and armored vehicles. Situations often arise where operators need the confidence and security of head-to-toe ballistic coverage; body armor can't provide that. Armored vehicles provide excellent coverage, but they cannot be taken through doorways, down hallways, or into elevators. SOB™ Defense Systems offer protection when and where it is needed so that the heroes return home safely after every operation.

Steiner eOptics is a U.S.-based company that designs and manufactures advanced electro-optical technology products for military, homeland security, law enforcement, and commercial users. Founded in 1979 and headquartered in Miami Township, Ohio, the company has established itself as a leader in laser aiming devices, night vision systems, and tactical illumination tools. Steiner eOptics proudly labels all its products as "Made in the USA."

Steiner eOptics focuses on enhancing situational awareness and improving accuracy and safety in challenging conditions. As a subsidiary of the German-based Steiner brand under Beretta Holding SpA, the company combines a legacy of quality and innovation with a commitment to meeting the needs of its customers.

Short Description: Arsenal Inc. is the exclusive licensed US manufacturer of premium semi-automatic sporting rifles, available with forged and CNC milled or stamped receivers. These rifles feature chrome-lined barrels and adhere to strict quality control standards in calibers 7.62x39mm, 5.56x45mm (.223 NATO), and 5.45x39.5mm. Founded in 1998, Arsenal Inc. initially manufactured products for the movie industry, government agencies, and the shooting public. Today, they continue to serve all three sectors. Arsenal Inc. has produced over 25 rifle and pistol versions, preserving old-world craftsmanship while incorporating modern technology. These rifles are available in both fully automatic for government contracts and semi-automatic for civilian use, all maintaining Arsenal's legendary quality. With fixed or folding butt stocks, their manufacturing process allows quick integration of new lines, offering economically priced stamped receivers alongside traditional forged and milled ones. Every Arsenal Inc. product comes with their guarantee, reflecting their commitment to well-made, superior-functioning rifles.

Short Description:
HTI Plastics is a custom injection molding company based in Lincoln, Nebraska, with over 26 years of experience in producing high-quality thermoplastic products. The company operates a modern facility exceeding 100,000 square feet, featuring advanced Krauss Maffei injection molding machines that allow for precision molding and efficient production cycles.

The company specializes in designing and manufacturing custom and proprietary injection molded plastic products for various industries, including medical devices, pharmaceuticals, animal health, sporting goods, food packaging, and firearms. Approximately half of their business is dedicated to pharmaceutical and medical products, which are produced under strict contamination control. HTI Plastics is FDA registered and holds ISO 13485 and ISO 9001 certifications, ensuring high standards of quality and regulatory compliance.

HTI Plastics provides a range of services, including product design assistance, material selection, prototyping, testing, and full lifecycle support. Their engineering expertise helps customers develop innovative products and optimize manufacturing processes, contributing to their reputation as a leading OEM and contract manufacturer in the injection molding sector.

Short Description:
Huğlu Av Tüfekleri Kooperatifi, or Huglu Hunting Firearms Cooperative, is a Turkish manufacturer known for producing high-quality shotguns and hunting firearms. Established in 1962, the cooperative has a rich tradition in shotgun manufacturing, rooted in the Huğlu region. It operates on a 25,000 m² facility, employing around 450 people and comprising 548 cooperative members.

The company offers a diverse range of shotguns, including single barrel, side-by-side double-barrel, over and under, semi-automatic, pump-action, muzzleloader shotguns, and hunter shotguns. Huğlu exports approximately 80% of its production to over 50 countries, including the United States, France, and Norway. The cooperative is recognized as one of the top 10 shotgun manufacturers globally, emphasizing quality and safety through internationally recognized management systems like ISO 9001, ISO 14001, and ISO 45001. Huğlu is committed to craftsmanship and customer satisfaction, making it a trusted brand among hunters, shooters, and firearm collectors worldwide.

HUXWRX Safety Co. is a manufacturer based in Millcreek, Utah, specializing in firearms accessories, particularly suppressors. The company focuses on enhancing user safety and health by reducing toxic emissions during firearm use. Their patented Flow-Through™ technology significantly lowers harmful gases compared to traditional suppressors, ensuring a safer shooting experience without compromising performance.

The product line includes suppressors designed to maintain weapon system efficiency while minimizing toxic gas exposure. HUXWRX Safety Co. serves a diverse customer base, including military units, law enforcement agencies, tactical professionals, and recreational shooters. The company is committed to American manufacturing, producing all its products domestically and emphasizing quality and safety standards. With a dedicated team, HUXWRX Safety Co. continues to support both new innovations and legacy products from OSS Suppressors.

Short Description:
Intruder Stop was inspired by an Elementary School Principal and designed by her engineer husband.  The simple to use, cost effective unit is mounted on the bottom of residential, business or school doors and anchors into the floor in the event of a lockdown situation.  The home version is used as an additional secure point for exterior doors.  The school version allows teachers and staff to lock down a door in less than one second and deploy by foot, thus eliminating the need to bend or deploy a separate device.  Designed and built in North Carolina, this patent pending device is strong and simple to use.  The solid metal construction assures years of ready to use service.  The install requires standard tools and the device can be anchored into any solid floor surface.

Short Description:
Marathon Targets specializes in the design, manufacture, and operation of AI-driven autonomous robotic target systems. Founded in 2010 in Australia and registered in the U.S. in 2016, the company focuses on providing realistic live fire tactical training solutions for military organizations. Their core products include armored, autonomous robotic humanoid targets that simulate human movement, enabling effective training scenarios under live fire conditions.

The company offers innovative solutions like Training-as-a-Service and Zero Infrastructure Range Modernization, which enhance military training methodologies without requiring extensive range infrastructure. Marathon Targets has a global customer base, including the US Marine Corps, US Army, US Navy, US Air Force, Canadian Forces, and several other international military forces. They prioritize collaboration with end users, incorporating customer feedback to continuously improve their systems.

Headquartered in Marrickville, New South Wales, Australia, with a significant presence in Huntsville, Alabama, Marathon Targets operates with a dedicated team and has conducted over 20,000 training events, showcasing their commitment to advancing military training through technology.

Short Description:
Maxim Defense Industries is a defense development company specializing in the design and manufacture of advanced small arms, suppressors, and firearm accessories. Their products cater to military, law enforcement, and commercial markets, focusing on creating tools that are lighter, more reliable, and enhanced through innovative research and development.

The company's product lineup includes high-performance firearms, suppressors, receiver kits, stocks, braces, and various accessories tailored for both professional users and firearms enthusiasts. Notable among their offerings is the M-Kore Technology used in their MSX suppressors, which combines the benefits of monocore silencers with traditional M baffles for exceptional sound suppression and user serviceability. Their suppressor series includes options for various calibers and barrel lengths, designed for heavy use and specific applications.

Maxim Defense is committed to improving existing weapons platforms and developing new solutions for future defense and law enforcement needs, integrating commercially available technologies to enhance performance and reliability. Their customers include military personnel, first responders, law enforcement agencies, and commercial firearm users seeking innovative and high-quality products.

Microtech Knives, Inc. is a leading American knife manufacturer established in 1994 by Anthony Marfione in Vero Beach, Florida. The company specializes in high-performance tactical automatic knives, particularly known for its "Out The Front" (OTF) and double-action models. With its headquarters in Mills River, North Carolina, Microtech operates two manufacturing facilities, ensuring strict quality control and precision engineering in every knife produced.

The core product line includes automatic knives featuring patented opening mechanisms and locking systems, designed for military, law enforcement, and tactical use. Notable models include the U.D.T., HALO, SOCOM, Currahee, and Ultratech. Microtech also collaborates with renowned custom knifemakers to create exclusive designs that combine craftsmanship with factory precision. The company has built a strong reputation among military personnel, law enforcement officers, and knife enthusiasts, recognized for its innovation and quality in the tactical knife market.

Operator XR is a technology company that specializes in immersive virtual reality (VR) training and simulation systems for military and law enforcement applications. Their focus is on enhancing human performance in high-risk situations through realistic, scenario-based training environments that improve decision-making and operational readiness.

The company's flagship product, the OP-2 system, is a portable mission rehearsal and training platform that integrates tactical training with advanced VR technology. It allows personnel to train with their actual service weapons in interactive scenarios, addressing various training needs such as tactical decision-making and mission planning. Operator XR also offers a Scenario Creator Suite, enabling instructors to design customized training environments tailored to the specific requirements of each agency.

Operator XR serves military and law enforcement agencies worldwide, with notable clients including the Texas Department of Public Safety. Their solutions aim to increase training frequency and effectiveness while enhancing safety outcomes in real-world operations.

Short Description:
PepperBall® specializes in developing, manufacturing, and distributing non-lethal self-defense and law enforcement solutions. The company originated from a DARPA program in 1996 and has created a technology platform based on PAVA, a potent pepper powder used in their projectiles. Their core product line features CO2-powered launchers that fire PepperBall® projectiles, which burst on impact to release incapacitating pepper powder, providing a safer alternative to traditional firearms.

PepperBall® serves a diverse customer base, including over 10,000 government and commercial agencies worldwide, such as the Federal Bureau of Prisons and various police departments. They also offer consumer products like the FlashLauncher™, designed for personal protection. Manufacturing takes place in Lake Forest, Illinois, where all materials are produced in-house. The company emphasizes innovation in projectile design and launcher technology to enhance effectiveness while minimizing risks. Additionally, PepperBall® provides extensive training programs led by experienced instructors to ensure safe and effective use of their systems.

Radians is a prominent manufacturer of high-performance Personal Protective Equipment (PPE), established in 1997 and based in Memphis, Tennessee. The company specializes in safety products for various markets, including industrial, construction, utility, sporting goods, law enforcement, and public safety. Radians offers a diverse product line that features safety eyewear, hearing protection, high-visibility apparel (RadWear®), rainwear, hand protection, headgear, cooling products, heated jackets, eyewash stations, and lens cleaning accessories.

Starting with a patented combination of hearing and eyewear protection, Radians has grown into a significant player in the safety industry, focusing on innovation and quality. The company provides both premium and value brands, including licensed lines like DEWALT® and Crossfire®, catering to a wide range of customer needs. Radians is dedicated to customer service and product innovation, supported by ISO 9001:2008 certification and advanced testing facilities. With multiple manufacturing locations in the U.S. and globally, Radians also offers customization options and efficient order processing through its RadLink distributor platform.

RETAY USA is the North American strategy and market development company handling all North American and South American brand and product development for Retay Arms of Konya Turkey.

RETAY USA is a fast growing and dynamic company that embraces the outdoor and hunting culture represented by our products and our advertising. Outdoors people first, we pride ourselves on developing product offerings that satisfy the specific needs of the outdoor and hunting enthusiasts in the Americas. 

Our headquarters is located in Easton, Maryland on the banks of the beautiful Chesapeake Bay in the waterfowl hunting capital of the Mid-Atlantic. The area is an outdoor enthusiasts paradise with world class hunting, fishing and watersports of all kinds and are just a stone's throw in all directions. 

Easton is located about an hour and thirty minutes from our nation's capital Washington DC, and just 45 Minutes From Annapolis and Baltimore, Maryland respectively. Blackwater National Wildlife Refuge and several Atlantic beach destinations are within an hour or two's drive.

RÖHM Clamping is a German company that specializes in the development, design, and manufacturing of precise clamping and gripping devices. Founded in 1909 and headquartered in Sontheim/Brenz, Germany, RÖHM operates additional production sites in Dillingen/Danube and St. Georgen. The company offers a diverse product range, including drill chucks, lathe chucks, live centres, vices, gripping technology, power chucks, cylinders, mandrels, and tool clamping systems, with over 7,000 standard items and many customized solutions.

RÖHM serves various industries such as automotive, railroad technology, watchmaking, medical technology, energy technology, armaments, woodworking, aerospace, and engineering. The company is recognized for its commitment to quality and innovation, producing special clamping devices for clean room environments compliant with ISO 7 standards. With a workforce of around 1,500 employees, RÖHM has established itself as a leading manufacturer of chucking tools globally, known for its sturdy and high-performance products.

Short Description:
Rubberlite, Inc. is a manufacturer and converter specializing in flexible material solutions, including cellular rubber, plastic foams, and custom-engineered polyurethane foams. Founded in 1986, the company has expanded its offerings to include polymer coatings, foam laminations, and flexible composite systems, catering to various industrial and commercial markets.

The company operates in three main areas: Industrial Rubber and Plastic Solutions, Engineered Foam Solutions, and Technical Composites. Rubberlite provides precision-manufactured cellular rubber and plastic products for gasketing, sealing, cushioning, and insulating. Its HyPUR-cel® line of custom-engineered polyurethane foams is designed for high-performance applications across sectors such as footwear, automotive, aerospace, and medical. Additionally, Rubberlite develops advanced lamination and coating technologies to create flexible composite materials.

With nearly 500,000 square feet of manufacturing and warehouse space, Rubberlite focuses on quality, innovation, and customer-specific solutions. The company actively participates in industry events, showcasing its commitment to serving diverse markets and enhancing product performance.

Short Description:
Marlin Firearms is a historic American firearms manufacturer established in 1872 by John Mahlon Marlin in New Haven, Connecticut. The company is well-known for its high-quality lever-action rifles, semi-automatic rifles, pump-action shotguns, and single-shot rifles, boasting a legacy of over 150 years.

Marlin began by producing single-shot pistols and quickly expanded into rifles, gaining prominence with the Model 1881 lever-action rifle. The company has a diverse product lineup, including small-caliber semi-automatic rifles popular for hunting and sport shooting, as well as pump-action shotguns. Marlin's lever-action rifles are particularly noted for their strength, accuracy, and reliability, appealing to hunters, sport shooters, and firearm enthusiasts. The company also has historical significance, having produced military firearms during World War I.

With a reputation for durable and reliable firearms, Marlin Firearms continues to be a leading name in the lever-action rifle market in North America.

Rugged Road, an Atlanta-based small business, is making waves in the outdoor industry. At less than half the weight of the competition with the same great ice retention, our ultralight coolers are unlike anything the market has seen before. Not only are they lightweight, but they're incredibly durable, hold ice for up to 7 days, and float upright (even fully loaded!).

Designed to go everywhere you do, our gear is functional, durable, and sure to be your new go-to.

Beyond a dedication to quality and innovation, Rugged Road is a company with a mission. The business acts as a vessel to give back, leading to the creation of the Rugged Road Foundation. To date, we've broken ground on seven water projects in Western Africa, with plans for many more in the coming months and years.

SIONYX is a photonics company based in Beverly, Massachusetts, that specializes in ultra-low-light CMOS image sensors and digital night vision camera systems. Founded in 2006 by Harvard professors Eric Mazur and James Carey, SIONYX has developed a patented semiconductor process that enhances the sensitivity of silicon photonics, leading to smaller and more cost-effective photonic devices.

The company's core technology, the XQE family of CMOS image sensors, significantly improves light sensing capabilities for various sectors, including commercial, industrial, medical, and defense. SIONYX has a notable partnership with the U.S. Department of Defense, supplying digital night vision cameras for the Integrated Visual Augmentation System (IVAS) program. Their flagship product, the Aurora, is a compact, all-digital night vision camera that provides full-color imaging in ultra-low-light conditions and is popular among outdoor enthusiasts, law enforcement, and search and rescue teams. SIONYX also collaborates with original equipment manufacturers to create customizable sensor and camera modules for specialized applications.

Short Description:
At Spartan Precision Equipment Ltd, we produce rifle and optic support systems that weigh less and do more. Hunting is in each member of our team's DNA, and as such we understand the rigours of our passion wherever they may take us around the world, and bind all of our knowledge and efforts together to ensure our designs never fall short of any requirement for that product's application.

Our flagship product – the Javelin Bipod – is a testament to our dedication to providing quality, practical solutions for all rifle shooting disciplines. Like many of our products since, it was invented with a desire to create a new-age adaptation of a traditional solution that could simply attach and detach as and when needed, that wasn't cumbersome to carry and as practical in the pursuit of tahr and ibex as it is reds and roe deer. 

"For shooters wanting to push the boundaries, gear available on the market just didn't cut it," admits founder Rob (Mr G) Gearing. "In my younger years as a guide, I rapidly fell out of love with having a bipod hanging from my rifle and I used one infrequently. They got in the way and were a pain in my shoulder when carrying my rifle, and my eventual reluctance to carry a one presented me with a few failed hunts. 

"So, applying my background in aviation engines and, in particular, discovery of rare earth magnets when working on the Concord aircraft sculpture, the resulting invention was an ultra-lightweight, stupidly strong bipod that could be on and off the rifle quicker than you could drop the legs on a run-of-the-mill bipod. Exactly what I was after."

As such, the Javelin Bipod was an instant success among rifle shooters all around the world and formed a foundation from which all Spartan products – from entry level to top-end – are forged. Now, over half a decade into production, our fleet of rifle and optic support systems have generated a loyal and growing following that we are ever grateful for.

Spinner North America, LLC specializes in advanced CNC (Computer Numerical Control) machine tools, focusing on efficient and profitable machining of complex parts. Steyr Arms serves a wide clientele, including military forces, law enforcement agencies, professional hunters, sport shooters, and firearms enthusiasts. The company emphasizes its craftsmanship and heritage, aiming to preserve traditional gunmaking while meeting modern demands.

Türkiye'de savunma sanayi alanında meydana gelen gelişmeler Turan'ı da olumlu yönde etkilemiştir. Dünyada hafif silah mühimmatına olan ihtiyacın arttığını ve Türkiye'deki ihtiyacı temin etmeye yönelik girişimlerin de halen tam yeterli olmadığını tespit eden Turan, kendi geleceğinin de bu alanda olması gerektiğine karar vermiştir. Bu maksatla gerekli altyapı yatırımlarını tamamlamaya müteakip 2019 yılında 9×19 mm tabanca mühimmatı Turan Ammunition olarak üretimine de başlamıştır. Turan halihazırda 50 milyon ses fişeği ve 100 milyon 9×19 mm fişeği üretim kapasitesine erişmiştir.

Mermi imalatı ile yurt dışı pazarlara da açılan firmamız üretiminin büyük kısmını Amerika ve Avrupa ülkelerine ihraç etmiştir. Dünya pazarında 7,62 x 39mm ve 5,56 x 45 mm mühimmata olan yüksek talep nedeniyle 2022- 2023 yatırım planında revize yapılmış ve bu ürünlerin imalat ve dolum hatları için gerekli bina, alt yapı ve makine teçhizat yatırımlarına başlanmıştır.

UNISIG Deep Hole Drilling Systems is a U.S.-based manufacturer that specializes in precision deep hole drilling machines, tooling, and automation systems for various industrial applications. Founded in 1981 and operating as a division of Entrust Manufacturing Technologies, Inc., UNISIG engineers and manufactures its products in the USA for a global customer base.

UNISIG serves diverse industries such as aerospace, automotive, defense, energy, and medical. They emphasize technical expertise and customer support, offering tailored training and long-term service to enhance the value of their customers' investments.

Viken Detection is a Massachusetts-based company that specializes in advanced detection technologies aimed at enhancing public safety and security. The company develops and manufactures x-ray imaging and chemical analysis products designed to identify hidden threats such as weapons, narcotics, explosives, and cash. Their solutions are utilized by law enforcement, customs, and border protection agencies to improve security at border crossings, checkpoints, and various properties.

The product portfolio includes handheld x-ray imagers, chemical analyzers, body scanners, vehicle scanners, and elemental analyzers. Notable products like the Nighthawk HBI and Osprey Systems are portable devices designed for high-stakes environments, ensuring precise and reliable detection capabilities. Viken Detection emphasizes innovation and holds numerous patents in detection technology, with a strong focus on research and development led by experts in the field.

The company serves a range of customers, including U.S. Customs and Border Protection, the DEA, and various public safety organizations. Viken Detection is committed to providing effective and affordable detection tools to help prevent drug trafficking, terrorism, and other threats, contributing to a safer world.

Short Description:
Williams Gun Sight's history is nearly a century old and Williams is still helping customers within the firearm industry to this current day.  Developed in 1926 by Harvey Williams in Davison, Michigan.  Harvey realized nearly a century ago firearms had inadequate sights and there was a need by customers for quality after-market sights.  Harvey developed his sights over the decades until they became the industry standard for customers looking to improve their accuracy.

It wasn't until the 1950's Williams branched out providing local customers with gunsmithing and retail services.  Through the years Williams retail became well known locally as the "go to" firearm store because of their superior product knowledge, gunsmithing, and public ranges. In recent years Williams retail store has now grown to 25,000 sq feet including indoor and outdoor ranges while maintaining their experienced gunsmithing department.

Williams Gun Sight has continued to succeed because of this perfect combination between our manufacturing and retail division.  Having a retail store allows our manufacturing division to thrive with product development for our gun sight customers.  Then our local retail customers benefit by having a wide selection of our sight products within our retail store.  Because of these two different divisions totaling over 80 employees Williams Gun Sight will continue to grow for decades to come!

Zenith Firearms, Inc. is an American firearms manufacturer based in Afton, Virginia, specializing in roller-delayed blowback firearms. The company is recognized for its expertise in this area, particularly with its flagship product, the ZF-5, an American-made version of the MP5 submachine gun. Launched in late 2021, the ZF-5 features modern enhancements such as improved serviceability, precise manufacturing tolerances, and a cold hammer-forged barrel.

Originally starting as an import business for Turkish firearms, Zenith has transitioned to domestic manufacturing, operating from a substantial industrial facility. The company employs advanced manufacturing techniques and equipment, ensuring high-quality production standards. Zenith Firearms serves a wide range of customers, including civilian shooters, law enforcement agencies, and distributors, while also providing parts and repair services for aging submachine guns. Their commitment to quality and customer service positions them as a significant player in the firearms industry.

Short Description:
Zistos Corporation designs and manufactures advanced portable visual inspection systems, created to expand perception in mission-critical environments where safety is essential and every second counts. Since 2000, our mission has been clear: creating a safer world by expanding visual awareness for professionals in tactical, industrial, rescue, and security sectors.

Inspired by the events of September 11 and guided by the belief that technology saves lives, our founders developed robust and precise tools that enable rescue teams, military, law enforcement, and industrial technicians to gain visual access to hard-to-reach or potentially dangerous areas, without compromising their own safety.

Our systems include HD pole-mounted cameras, specialized solutions for inspecting confined spaces, collapsed structures, vehicles, tanks, and pipes, as well as thermal imaging technology and secure wireless systems. These tools enable rapid, informed, and safe decision-making in high-risk scenarios, from natural disasters to tactical operations and industrial controls.

Diversity and innovation define our team. Zistos brings together a multitude of nationalities and professional backgrounds, driving creativity and resilience. Every new development and improvement responds to the true needs of those who face danger in the field, with total focus on reliability and ease of use.

Committed to technological advancement, performance excellence, and dedicated customer support, Zistos leads the portable visual inspection sector. Our clients trust us not only for the quality of our products, but also for the certainty we provide in scenarios where seeing the invisible can save lives.

Our purpose: saving lives by expanding visual awareness, helping more people return home safely.﻿

Hexagon Asset Lifecycle Intelligence is a division of Hexagon that provides digital solutions for the design, construction, and operation of industrial facilities. The company focuses on enhancing productivity and sustainability throughout the asset lifecycle by unlocking data and modernizing industrial projects. 

Its product portfolio includes Intergraph Smart® 3D, a 3D design software for plant engineering; Intergraph Smart® Completions, which automates asset information management; and PAS Cyber Integrity, a solution for cybersecurity in industrial operations. The division is set to become a standalone software and SaaS company by early 2026, allowing it to focus on its growth strategy in asset lifecycle intelligence and related fields.

Short Description:
Gun Owners of America (GOA) is a non-profit lobbying organization founded in 1975, dedicated to preserving and defending the Second Amendment rights of gun owners in the United States. Headquartered in Springfield, Virginia, GOA represents over two million gun owners and actively engages with lawmakers at all levels to influence gun-related legislation and policy.

The organization focuses on lobbying and advocacy, spending significant resources to oppose gun control measures and promote pro-gun legislation. GOA also provides legal support through a network of attorneys to defend gun owners' rights in court. Additionally, it operates a Federal Political Action Committee to support candidates who uphold Second Amendment rights. Through its educational arm, the Gun Owners Foundation, GOA conducts seminars and produces public service announcements to raise awareness about gun rights and safety.

Hernon Manufacturing, Inc. is a U.S.-based company founded in 1978 by brothers Harry and Josef Arnon. Headquartered in Sanford, Florida, Hernon specializes in high-performance adhesives, sealants, and precision dispensing and curing equipment. The company has grown significantly from its origins as a basement startup to a global leader in adhesive solutions.

Hernon offers a diverse portfolio of over 5,000 adhesive formulas and various precision dispensing machines, including advanced gantry-style robots and Progressive Cavity Pumps. Their product range also includes UV LED curing lights and thermally conductive pastes. These offerings cater to industries such as aerospace, defense, electronics, and general manufacturing, with a focus on specialized applications like UV curable sealants for oil shaft seals and ammunition.

With a global distribution network spanning over 100 locations and exports to more than 60 countries, Hernon is committed to quality and innovation. The company has received several prestigious awards, including the presidential “E” award for exports, and continues to expand its workforce and production capacity to support ongoing growth.

HighCom Armor is a U.S.-based company that designs, develops, manufactures, and distributes advanced ballistic-resistant body armor and personal protective equipment. Founded in 1997 in San Francisco, California, the company operates a significant manufacturing and distribution facility in Columbus, Ohio, along with R&D and manufacturing operations in Adelaide, Australia. HighCom Armor's mission is to protect military personnel, law enforcement officers, and first responders globally.

The company offers a comprehensive range of products, including hard rifle armor plates, soft body armor vests, ballistic helmets, and ballistic shields. All products are designed and tested to meet or exceed rigorous standards set by organizations like the National Institute of Justice (NIJ) and NATO. HighCom Armor is recognized for its commitment to quality, being the first to receive the BA 9000 certification for body armor manufacturing and maintaining ISO 9001:2015 certification. With a focus on innovation, the company aims to produce thinner, lighter, and stronger body armor solutions while continuing to support the safety of frontline operators.

IMCO Carbide Tool Inc., founded in 1977 and based in Perrysburg, Ohio, is a prominent American manufacturer of advanced cutting tool technologies for metalworking. The company serves a global market with distributors in North America, South America, Europe, and the Pacific Rim. 

IMCO specializes in high-performance cutting tools made from micrograin and ultra-fine micrograin carbide, known for their hardness and heat resistance. Their product range includes end mills, burs, drills, countersinks, roughers/finishers, reamers, routers, and custom-made precision tools. IMCO tools are designed to machine various materials, including aluminum, stainless steel, titanium, and composites, and are utilized in industries such as energy, automotive, medical, and aerospace.

The company focuses on continuous innovation and quality, employing advanced technology and hands-on machining experience to address complex machining challenges. IMCO is dedicated to enhancing productivity and precision in metalworking through ongoing research and development.

Jenoptik AG is a high-technology company based in Jena, Germany, with roots tracing back to the Carl Zeiss optical workshop established in 1846. It became an independent company after German reunification and was officially named Jenoptik AG in 1996, followed by a public listing in 1998.

The company specializes in photonics and systems engineering, offering a wide range of products and services across five main divisions: lasers and materials processing, industrial metrology, traffic solutions, defense and civil systems, and optical systems. Jenoptik develops and manufactures various laser beam sources and components, serving industries such as semiconductor manufacturing, automotive, medical technology, aviation, security, and defense. With a presence in about 80 countries and major production sites in the United States, Switzerland, and France, Jenoptik is committed to research and development and actively participates in international trade fairs to showcase its technologies.

L2 Brands is a designer, manufacturer, and marketer of custom apparel, headwear, and home décor, primarily serving collegiate, resort, and corporate markets. Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Pennsylvania, the company was formed in 2018 through the merger of League Collegiate Outfitters and Legacy Athletic. L2 Brands offers a diverse range of products, including casual apparel like t-shirts, fleece, and spirit blankets, as well as custom-decorated headwear and winter knits, all featuring a vintage-inspired aesthetic.

The company markets its products mainly to collegiate institutions, with licensing agreements covering many four-year colleges. Its customer base includes over 3,000 campus stores, independent retailers, and corporate clients across the United States. Short Description:
Leupold + Stevens, Inc. is a family-owned company based in Portland, Oregon, founded in 1907. Initially a repair shop for survey equipment, it evolved into a manufacturer of high-quality sporting optics and water monitoring instruments. The company is known for its innovative riflescopes, binoculars, and rangefinders, which are designed for hunting, shooting sports, and professional use. Many of their products are made in the USA at their facility in Beaverton, Oregon.

Under the Stevens brand, Leupold + Stevens produces water level recorders and flow meters, catering to environmental agencies, municipalities, and industrial clients. The company has a strong reputation for quality and durability, serving a diverse customer base that includes hunters, professional marksmen, and military personnel. As a fourth-generation family-owned business, Leupold + Stevens emphasizes American manufacturing and continues to be recognized for its commitment to innovation in both optics and hydrological monitoring.

Short Description:
Lexipol is a private company founded in 2003 and headquartered in Frisco, Texas. It specializes in providing risk management solutions for public safety agencies, including law enforcement, fire departments, and local government entities. The company was established by Bruce Praet, Gordon Graham, and Dan Merkle, who aimed to enhance public safety operations through improved policies and training.

Lexipol develops comprehensive policy manuals that are continuously updated to help agencies reduce legal risks and maintain operational consistency. In addition to policy manuals, the company offers online training programs, wellness resources for public safety personnel, and grant services to assist agencies in securing funding. Lexipol also features an electronic policy management platform for efficient policy management and operates digital communities like Police1 and FireRescue1, which serve as valuable resources for public safety professionals. With a mission to create safer communities, Lexipol supports over 8,100 agencies across 35 U.S. states, reaching more than 2 million public safety professionals.

Liberty Ammunition, based in Bradenton, Florida, was founded in 2005 and specializes in high-performance ammunition technology, particularly for self-defense applications. The company is a leader in the ammunition industry, holding over 15 patents, including the notable Liberty 5.56 armor-piercing design, which is widely used in military settings.

The company's product offerings include Civil Defense ammunition, which features high-speed, lead-free rounds designed for effective personal defense. Their Ultra Light ammunition provides lightweight options that enhance carry comfort without compromising performance. Additionally, Liberty Ammunition supplies military and law enforcement with specialized rounds that meet rigorous standards. Their commitment to innovation and quality control is evident, as each bullet undergoes individual inspection. Liberty Ammunition serves a diverse clientele, including law enforcement, military personnel, and civilian shooting enthusiasts, all seeking reliable self-defense solutions.

Primary Weapons Systems (PWS) is a firearms manufacturer based in Boise, Idaho, founded in 2008 by firearm enthusiasts. The company specializes in designing and producing high-quality tactical and sporting rifles, firearm components, and accessories. PWS is recognized for its innovative long-stroke piston system, which enhances reliability and reduces maintenance needs, particularly in high-volume fire situations.

PWS offers a range of products, including the MK1 and MK2 series rifles, muzzle devices like flash suppressors and compensators, and suppressors designed to minimize noise and muzzle blast. The company also produces various firearm components that allow for customization and improved performance. PWS emphasizes rigorous testing of its products to ensure durability and effectiveness across different rifle platforms.

The company serves a diverse customer base, including military and law enforcement agencies, civilian firearm enthusiasts, and gunsmiths. PWS is committed to quality and customer service, supported by a dedicated team focused on compliance, sourcing, and sales.

The company is known for its innovative products, starting with the original "Magpul" device that aids in manipulating rifle magazines. Magpul's product line includes polymer magazines, firearm parts, and accessories compatible with various firearms, such as AR-15, AK-47, and popular shotguns.

The company operates through three main divisions: Magpul Industries, which focuses on firearms accessories; Magpul Professional Training & Simulation (PTS), which produces airsoft-compatible accessories and guns; and Magpul Dynamics, which offers firearms training and instructional videos. Magpul has built a strong reputation for quality and reliability, serving military, law enforcement, and civilian shooting enthusiasts worldwide. With a commitment to innovation and efficiency, Magpul continues to develop products that enhance performance under stress.

Marubeni Citizen-Cincom, Inc. is a joint venture established in 1984 between Marubeni Corporation and Citizen Watch Company. The company is based in Allendale, New Jersey, with additional offices in California, Illinois, and Massachusetts. It specializes in the marketing and servicing of Citizen's CINCOM family of Swiss-type CNC automatic lathes, which are known for their high precision and versatility in complex machining tasks.

The core product line includes CNC automatic lathes with multi-axis capabilities and high spindle speeds, designed for small and complex parts. Marubeni Citizen-Cincom also provides comprehensive marketing, sales, and after-sales services, including operator and technician training programs. The company serves a wide range of industries, such as automotive, medical devices, and electronics, focusing on high-performance machining solutions and customer engagement.

MDT Sporting Goods, also known as Modular Driven Technologies Corp., is a Canadian manufacturer founded in 2009 by Laszlo Klementis. The company specializes in precision rifle chassis systems, magazines, and shooting accessories aimed at enhancing rifle accuracy and ergonomics for tactical and precision shooting.

MDT's flagship product, the TAC21 chassis, was developed with insights from competitive shooters and advanced CNC machining. This product, along with others like the LSS GEN3 chassis, bipods, and scope mounts, allows for customization without compromising rifle performance. The company collaborates closely with shooters worldwide to ensure high standards of functionality and performance in its products.

Operating from Chilliwack, British Columbia, MDT employs approximately 200-500 people and generates an estimated annual revenue of $69.5 million. The company is recognized as a leader in the precision rifle accessories market and is committed to social responsibility, supporting initiatives like Lantern Rescue, which combats human trafficking.

MSA serves various industries, including apparel brands, military, marine, and light industrial sectors, focusing on reliable service and strong customer partnerships.

MYSTERY RANCH is a premium backpack and load-bearing gear company based in Bozeman, Montana, founded in 2000 by Dana Gleason and Renée Sippel-Baker. With a strong foundation in ergonomic backpack design, the company specializes in creating durable, comfortable, and modular backpacks for extreme conditions and professional use. Their innovative designs, such as the patented Futura Yoke™ system, are recognized for effectively distributing weight and enhancing comfort.

The company provides specialized gear for military personnel, firefighters, and outdoor enthusiasts. Their product range includes backpacks for elite military units, firefighting packs developed in collaboration with wildfire crews, and hunting packs designed for backcountry adventures. MYSTERY RANCH also offers urban and commuter packs that incorporate military-grade technology for everyday use. Their commitment to user-driven design ensures that they meet the real-world needs of their diverse customer base, which includes law enforcement agencies and outdoor enthusiasts. In February 2024, MYSTERY RANCH was acquired by YETI Holdings, Inc., while continuing to operate independently from its headquarters.

Short Description:
The National Wild Turkey Federation (NWTF) is a non-profit organization founded in 1973, dedicated to the conservation of wild turkeys and the preservation of hunting heritage in North America. Based in Edgefield, South Carolina, NWTF has a membership of over 250,000 individuals and operates across the United States, Canada, Mexico, and 14 other countries. The organization has played a significant role in increasing the wild turkey population from about 1.3 million in 1973 to nearly 7 million today.

NWTF focuses on various conservation and education initiatives. It has invested over $372 million in habitat conservation, improving more than 22 million acres of wildlife habitat. The organization also supports educational outreach programs like JAKES, Women in the Outdoors, and Wheelin' Sportsmen, which aim to engage diverse groups in outdoor skills and wildlife management. Additionally, NWTF coordinates the Wild Turkey Symposium to facilitate research and collaboration among scientists and biologists, enhancing wild turkey management strategies nationwide.

Short Description:
opto biolabs GmbH is a German company based in Freiburg that specializes in developing and manufacturing customized LED illumination devices for optogenetics research. As a spin-off from the University of Freiburg, the company focuses on providing tailored lighting solutions that enhance experimental capabilities and improve research efficiency in controlling biological processes with light.

Their product lineup includes innovative devices like the optoWELL OPW96, which allows for 96 parallel experiments with precise light delivery. These devices are designed to deliver light with high accuracy, supporting reproducibility and accelerating scientific advancements. The company collaborates with research institutions to integrate their devices into robotic liquid handling systems for fully automated high-throughput screening in optogenetics.

Founded by Dr. Kathrin Brenker, opto biolabs addresses challenges in the field, such as controlling light dosage and ensuring cell viability during illumination. Their mission is to empower researchers by providing smart and customizable lighting solutions that meet demanding research needs. Photonis Defense is a defense technology company based in Lancaster, Pennsylvania, with a history that dates back to 1942. The company specializes in advanced photonics and imaging solutions, focusing on products such as night vision systems, microwave amplifiers, and digital vision technologies. The company designs and manufactures high-performance night vision goggles and monoculars, including the PD-PRO series and Vyper binoculars, known for their durability and advanced imaging capabilities. Photonis Defense serves a diverse range of customers, including the U.S. Department of Defense and various government agencies. Their products are utilized globally, supporting military operations and homeland security missions with superior imaging and electronic warfare capabilities. The company is committed to quality and innovation, ensuring they maintain a technological edge in the defense sector.

Propper International is a prominent manufacturer of clothing and gear tailored for tactical, law enforcement, public safety, and military applications. Established in 1967 by William S. Propper, the company is headquartered in St. Charles, Missouri, and has become one of the largest official suppliers to the U.S. armed forces. Propper has produced over 120 million garments for various military branches, employing over 1,400 people and operating multiple production facilities in locations such as Puerto Rico, the Dominican Republic, and Haiti.

The company offers a wide range of tactical and military apparel, including boots, tops, bottoms, body armor, bags, and accessories. Propper's products are designed to meet the demanding needs of military personnel and public safety professionals, ensuring durability and functionality. With a commitment to quality, Propper has received numerous awards from the Defense Logistics Agency, highlighting its dedication to excellence in defense manufacturing. The company also serves commercial markets through a network of over 3,000 retail and e-commerce channels across the United States.

ReconRobotics, Inc. is a Minnesota-based company founded in 2005 that focuses on the research, development, and manufacturing of ultra-light tactical micro-robot systems. These systems are designed to enhance safety and situational awareness for military, law enforcement, and first responder personnel. The company originated from robotics technology developed at the University of Minnesota's Center for Distributed Robotics.

The core products of ReconRobotics include the Recon Scout® and Throwbot® robot systems. These miniature, mobile reconnaissance robots provide immediate situational awareness and allow users to maintain a greater standoff distance during high-risk operations. With over 7,000 robot systems deployed globally, ReconRobotics serves multiple branches of the United States Armed Forces, international allied forces, and over 800 federal, state, and local law enforcement agencies, including the FBI and ATF. The company markets its products through a distribution network that spans 35 countries.

Salomon is a French sports equipment company founded in 1947 in Annecy, located in the French Alps. Initially starting as a workshop producing ski edges, it has grown into a global leader in outdoor sports gear, particularly in winter sports equipment. The company is now owned by Amer Sports, a Finnish retail conglomerate.

Salomon offers a wide range of outdoor sports equipment and apparel, focusing on innovation and performance. It became the leading ski binding manufacturer by 1972 and has since expanded its product line to include alpine and Nordic skis, boots, hiking and running shoes, snowboards, and inline skates. The brand is well-known in trail running, with popular products like the XA PRO shoe and the XT-6 trail shoe. Salomon emphasizes sustainability and advanced manufacturing, highlighted by its Advanced Shoe Factory 4.0 in France.

The company serves outdoor sports enthusiasts, including skiers, snowboarders, trail runners, and hikers, as well as technical staff and participants in major events like the Olympic and Paralympic Winter Games. Salomon is recognized for its commitment to supporting athletes and adventurers worldwide.

Short Description:
Sonobond Ultrasonics, Inc. is a leading provider of ultrasonic metal welding and textile bonding equipment for industries around the world.  

In 1960, the company—then known as Aeroprojects—invented ultrasonic metal welding and received the first patent ever awarded for this technology:  our exclusive Wedge-Reed System.  During the intervening years, Sonobond has earned an outstanding reputation for its pioneering work and quality engineered products.  Today we manufacture a complete line of bonding and welding equipment for companies in the metals, plastics, and nonwovens/textiles industries.  These include units for applications in aerospace, apparel, appliance, automotive, battery, body armor, electrical, electronic, environmental, filtration, HVAC, photovoltaic, and medical fields.    

Ultrasonic Welding Technology is Environmentally Friendly

Ultrasonic bonding is fast, accurate, economical, and safe for the environment.  

No adhesives, solder, thread, or other consumables are used.  Instead, the process features a specially-designed head that channels high-frequency vibrations to create a rapid, localized buildup of heat in non-ferrous metals, rigid plastics, or synthetic fabrics.  The resulting heat is then used to weld, bond, cut, or slit these materials without heating the surrounding area.  The process is energy-efficient, ultra-reliable and produces strong, high-quality results.  

Sonobond Ultrasonics equipment is available in both stand-alone and modular form.  The modular units are designed for convenient integration into a production line or custom machinery.  All models are easy to operate and require only minimal training.

Short Description:
Sordin is a Swedish company with over 40 years of experience in developing and manufacturing professional hearing protection equipment. Founded in the late 1970s, Sordin specializes in "above the neck" personal protective gear, including earmuffs, protective visors, and safety helmets with integrated hearing protection. The company launched its first passive hearing protector, the Sordin Classic, in 1987, setting a standard for durability and noise attenuation. In 1995, Sordin introduced electronic hearing protectors, enhancing their product range for various professional applications.

Sordin's offerings include passive hearing protectors for industrial and forestry use, electronic hearing protectors that allow for situational awareness, and safety helmets and visors designed for occupational safety. The company also expanded its product line to include in-ear hearing protection through the acquisition of Italian supplier Shothunt in 2022. Sordin serves a diverse customer base across sectors such as manufacturing, mining, construction, military, and emergency services, emphasizing quality, technology, and sustainability in its operations. With production sites in Vikmanshyttan and Värnamo, Sordin produces over one million earmuffs annually and maintains a strong commitment to occupational health and safety.

The State of Montana is the official government entity responsible for governing and administering public services in Montana. It operates through three branches: Legislative, Executive, and Judicial. The Legislative Branch is bicameral, consisting of 50 senators and 100 representatives who create state laws. The Executive Branch includes elected officials such as the Governor and Attorney General, overseeing various departments to implement state policies. The Judicial Branch administers justice through the Supreme Court and other courts.

Montana provides a wide range of public services through its departments and agencies. These services include public education oversight, legal services, regulation of public utilities, and administration of state government operations. The state supports its residents and local governments by delivering essential services, ensuring public safety, and facilitating regulatory compliance. Overall, the State of Montana serves as the comprehensive governing body, dedicated to the welfare and governance of its citizens.

Short Description:
Sydor Optics, Inc. is a family-owned manufacturer of precision optics, established in 1964 by Stefan Sydor. Based in Rochester, New York, the company has evolved from a general optics manufacturer to a specialist in precision flat-surfaced optical components, including parallel and wedged optics. Sydor Optics is known for its high-quality custom optical solutions, with a legacy that includes significant projects like the Mt. Palomar Observatory’s 200-inch telescope mirror.

The company focuses on producing custom flat optical components, such as optical windows and substrates, tailored to meet strict specifications for flatness and surface quality. Sydor Optics serves various industries, including aerospace and defense, semiconductor manufacturing, and medical biosciences, providing optics for applications like the Orion space missions and commercial laser technologies. Under the leadership of Jim Sydor, the company emphasizes craftsmanship, innovation, and customer service while expanding its international presence.

Safariland is an American company founded in 1964 in Sierra Madre, California, initially focused on manufacturing custom gun holsters. Over the years, it has grown into a leading global provider of products and services for law enforcement, military, public safety, and security professionals. The company is known for its innovative duty gear and protective equipment, including advanced holster retention designs and body armor made with Kevlar.

Safariland offers a wide range of products, including holsters, duty gear, ballistic and stab-resistant body armor, less-lethal weapons, marine and aviation safety gear, tactical communication devices, and forensic equipment. The company emphasizes real-world applicability and continuous product improvement through its ambassador program, The CADRE, which includes professionals from various fields. Safariland serves a diverse clientele, including police departments, special operations forces, and security organizations, with a commitment to enhancing operational effectiveness and safety.
