Thunderbird Molding is a family-founded company based in Shelbyville, Indiana, specializing in custom plastic injection molding with over 40 years of experience. They provide a wide range of services, including mold design, prototyping, engineering, production, and assembly, making them a single-source supplier for custom solutions.

The company features high-precision injection molding capabilities with machines ranging from 150 to 950 tons, accommodating both short-run and high-volume production. Thunderbird Molding employs advanced techniques such as two-shot injection molding, insert molding, and over-molding, allowing for diverse product styles and materials. Their engineering team works closely with clients from concept to production, ensuring quality and reliability in their offerings.

Thunderbird Molding serves various industries, including construction and agriculture, and is known for its commitment to on-time delivery and strong customer relationships. With a focus on innovation and sustainability, the company continues to evolve alongside advancements in injection molding technology.

As a woman majority owned company, Tiger Enterprises & Trading, Inc. started operations in Ellington, CT in 1993, under the direction of Mrs. Bonnie Walker, the current Chief Financial Officer and majority owner. Short Description:
As an industry leader in metal sales and service since 1962, The Trident Company is an AS9100 certified stocking distributor of specialty high-performance and corrosion resistant metals that include aluminum, stainless steel, nickel, copper and many other exotic alloys.
Our value-added processing services include boring, turning, cutting, slitting, shearing, and saw operations. Our service-minded employees are committed to providing customer satisfaction by supplying top quality products, excellent craftsmanship and competitive pricing.
The Trident Company was established October 1, 1962 by the original owner who serviced customers out of his garage. The history of "The Trident Company" emblem stems from the original owner's proud affiliation as a United States Naval Academy – Annapolis Graduate.
Today, The Trident Company has grown into a multi-faceted metals service center providing non-ferrous metals nationally from locations in the Texas and Oklahoma. The Trident Team embraces this symbol as a reminder of our long standing history and strong commitment to providing quality and service to our customers.
As an approved ISO:9001 Certified stocking metals distributor, The Trident Company prides themselves on offering superior quality products by utilizing our strong vendor partnerships who also put Quality first.
The Trident Company maintains a very diverse and extensive inventory of specialty high-performance and corrosion resistant metals that include: aluminum, stainless steel, nickel, copper, and many other exotic alloys. We offer these metals in various gauges of sheet and plate, rod and bar, tubing and pipe, and standard structural shapes including beams, angles, channels and more.

Tsugami America, a division of Morris Group, Inc., has been the exclusive North American source for Tsugami Precision CNC machine tools since 1978. Based in Windsor, Connecticut, the company specializes in distributing high-performance CNC lathes, vertical and horizontal machining centers, and multi-tasking machines throughout the U.S., Canada, and Mexico.

The product range includes Swiss-type CNC automatic lathes, opposed gang tool lathes, gang/turret lathes, and multifunction machines designed for manufacturing small, high-precision parts up to 65 mm in diameter. These machines are utilized in various industries, including medical, aerospace, defense, and automotive. Tsugami America also offers application engineering, customer training, and dedicated local service to enhance manufacturing processes. The company focuses on speed, accuracy, and rigidity in its machine tools, supporting advanced automation options for efficient production.

TW Metals LLC is a global specialty metals supplier with a history that dates back to 1907. Formed in 1998 from the merger of Williams & Company and Tubesales, the company operates over 30 locations across North America, Europe, and Asia. As part of O’Neal Industries, TW Metals focuses on providing high-quality specialty metals and innovative supply chain solutions.

The company offers a diverse range of specialty metal products, including tube, pipe, bar, rod, wire, plate, sheet, and aerospace extrusions, available in materials such as stainless steel, aluminum, nickel, titanium, and carbon alloy. TW Metals also provides complete processing services, timely delivery, and expert customer service, along with customized supply chain solutions to help clients meet their production and profitability goals. 

With a primary focus on the aerospace industry, TW Metals serves various sectors, including oil & gas, medical, food service, and government/military. Their specialized business units cater to unique industry needs while ensuring high standards for quality and on-time delivery.

UF PRO is a Slovenian company founded in 1997 by Milena and Armin Wagner, originally known as UNI&FORMA d.o.o. The company specializes in designing and manufacturing high-performance tactical and outdoor clothing systems for professional users, including military personnel, law enforcement officers, and special forces units. UF PRO has built a strong reputation for its innovative and durable tactical apparel, tailored to meet the specific needs of professionals in demanding environments.

The product range includes advanced tactical clothing such as Striker combat pants and jackets, Monsoon waterproof garments, and other specialized apparel designed for extreme conditions. UF PRO emphasizes ergonomic design and high-quality materials to enhance comfort and performance in the field. The company serves a global clientele, including elite military and law enforcement units, with notable customers such as the Slovenian military, Danish police, and various SWAT teams in the United States.

Headquartered in Slovenia, UF PRO also has a subsidiary in Germany and distributes its products internationally through e-commerce and authorized dealers. The company is committed to continuous innovation, supported by strong research and development capabilities.

Veterans Guardian is a veteran-founded company based in Pinehurst, North Carolina, specializing in VA disability claim consulting. Established in 2017 by U.S. Army veterans Scott Greenblatt and Bill Taylor, the company aims to help military veterans achieve the maximum VA disability rating they deserve. With a veteran-first culture, 63% of its staff are veterans or spouses of veterans, reflecting its commitment to serving the veteran community.

The company offers pre-filing consulting services to assist veterans in navigating the VA disability claims process. Their expertise includes optimizing VA disability ratings, preparing necessary documentation, and providing guidance on eligibility for benefits related to military service. Veterans Guardian has created over 300 jobs nationwide and has received multiple awards, including the HIREVets Platinum Award and the Military Friendly Gold Employer designation for 2024.

Short Description:
The company's name ‘ZRODelta' was originally derived from its first quick-detach scope mount, which provided a true return-to-zero mounting solution. ZRO means ‘zero' and Delta means ‘shift, change, or difference', or ‘no difference' for short. I.E. A user could remove a zeroed optic and mount from a firearm, replace it at a later time, and experience no shift or change in the point of impact of the weapon system. The company's name was born: ZRODelta.

The company has expanded far beyond mounts, designing and manufacturing industry-leading weapons, parts, and accessories that define innovation. When we say ZRODelta: The Delta is ZRO, we mean that the difference is ZRO. We are the change within the industry, offering the most modular handgun platform available today, the only semi-automatic precision rifle with a 1/2MOA guarantee, world-class OEM parts production solutions, and best-in-category mounting solutions.

These capabilities, combined with our partnership with the premier precision optics brand US Optics®, has enabled ZRODelta to quickly become the world's leading Creator of Dynamic Weapon Systems.

Short Description:
Hydromat, Inc., based in St. Louis, Missouri, is a prominent manufacturer of precision rotary transfer machines and turnkey machining solutions, established in 1979. The company integrates Swiss precision machine elements with German engineering to provide high-quality metalworking solutions. With a manufacturing facility of about 200,000 square feet and a dedicated team of nearly 200 associates, Hydromat emphasizes craftsmanship and engineering excellence.

The company offers a range of products, including modular rotary transfer machines, multispindle lathes through a partnership with Tornos S.A., and custom turnkey automation systems. Additionally, Hydromat provides barfeeding systems and environmentally friendly part cleaning solutions through its Edge Technologies division. Innovative Mold Inc is located in 12500 31 Mile Rd, Washington, Michigan, United States. 

Innovative Mold is dedicated to meeting the quality expectations of our customer and to the continual operation of a quality system that meets the requirements of the ISO9001:2008 standards. We commit ourselves to a strategy of continuous improvement, on time delivery, and customer satisfaction.

Short Description:
İstanbul Silah ve Savunma Sanayi A.Ş. is a Turkish company founded in 2003 by Erol Kurt. It specializes in the design, manufacture, and export of hunting and sporting firearms, particularly shotguns and rifles. The company operates a modern manufacturing facility in Istanbul, covering approximately 32,000 square meters, with an annual output of around 300,000 rifles. With over 30 years of industry experience, İstanbul Silah emphasizes in-house production of all firearm components to ensure strict quality control.

The product range includes semi-automatic shotguns such as the İmpala, CZ Turka, Mikado, and the patented İmpala Plus. These firearms are designed for durability and ease of maintenance, featuring innovative designs intended for long-term use. İstanbul Silah primarily serves the international civilian market, with a 98% export rate, and collaborates with leading global brands while investing in research and development to enhance the firearms industry in Turkey.

The company is committed to environmental sustainability and social responsibility, implementing practices like recycling, waste management, and the use of alternative energy sources. It also fosters a family culture within the organization, providing education and internship opportunities to the community.

Short Description:
Jacob Grey firearms are engineered, designed, built, and tested in our facility to guarantee the highest quality, superior precision, and accuracy. We have been providing quality firearms for over 11 years now, the owner actually started off building custom 1911s in 2010. In 2012, Jacob Grey opened his aerospace machine shop. Proudly manufacturing OEM parts for some of the most respected names in the aerospace industry.
Using our experience as a gold star supplier for aerospace/defense, we have transformed our brand into firearms that give you the precision, reliability, accuracy, and insurance one needs. If you know the industry, you know they allow no room for mistakes. We must achieve perfection, holding laser tight tolerances. All of our primary firearm components are machined using aluminum billet, machined with the direction of the grain for durability, strength, and tolerance accuracy. Our firearms have a unique precision cut design and fit, unlike a forging or casting like most other manufacturers use. Each Jacob Grey ™ firearm is hand built one by one, inspected, and tested to produce an elevated level of craftsmanship. Your mind can be at ease, as we strongly hold to our lifetime warranty on every firearm. We thrive on providing civilian, law enforcement, military, hunters, and competitive shooters precision and quality firearms that can be relied upon for years to come.

Short Description:
Kali Protectives is a helmet manufacturer founded in 2008 by Brad Waldron, specializing in advanced safety technology for cyclists. The company is known for its innovative use of cone-shaped expanded polystyrene (EPS) foam, which enhances impact absorption by directing forces away from the rider's head, similar to crumple zones in cars. Their patented in-molding process integrates EPS foam directly into the helmet shell, effectively reducing harmful spikes in g-forces during crashes.

Kali Protectives offers a variety of helmets designed for cycling, including mountain biking and gravel riding. Their products feature advanced elements like SuperVents, which provide cooling and structural integrity while minimizing rotational forces. The company emphasizes rigorous engineering and safety testing, collaborating closely with factories and experts to ensure high standards. Kali Protectives is recognized in the cycling community for its commitment to safety and performance, appealing to serious cyclists and outdoor enthusiasts.

Kenetrek designs and manufactures some of the leading hunting and outdoor boots, gaiters, socks and accessories on the market.

At Kenetrek, our true passion lies in outdoor pursuits with good friends, whether that involves chasing trophy bull elk over rugged ridges, backpacking deep into the Bob Marshall Wilderness, or casting dry flies to Madison River Rainbows. L&L Products is a family-owned multinational company founded in 1958 by Bob Ligon and Gene Lane. Starting from humble beginnings, the company has grown into a global leader in applied engineering and materials science, employing over 1,200 people across 15 locations worldwide, including manufacturing facilities in the USA, Europe, China, India, Türkiye, and Brazil.

The company specializes in tailored solutions for static sealing, noise, vibration, and harshness (NVH) reduction, acoustics, structural reinforcement, and composite components. Its products primarily serve the automotive industry, with applications also in aerospace, rail, commercial vehicles, and various industrial sectors. L&L Products emphasizes a customer-centric approach, leveraging expertise in materials science and engineering to develop customized solutions, supported by significant investment in research and development. The company culture reflects the founders' values, focusing on the well-being of employees, customers, suppliers, and local communities.

LaserStar Technologies Corporation, founded in 1957 in Riverside, Rhode Island, specializes in designing, engineering, and manufacturing advanced laser systems. As the only U.S. manufacturer of Nd:YAG micro welding laser systems since the 1990s, it has become a global supplier of laser sources for various applications, including welding, marking, cutting, and deep engraving.

The company offers a wide range of products, such as manual and automated laser welding machines, laser engraving and cutting systems like the FiberCube®XL, and precise laser marking and motion control solutions. LaserStar operates modern facilities in Riverside, Orlando, and Arcadia, and supports its international customer base through partnerships and sales representatives. With a focus on American manufacturing and innovation, LaserStar employs around 90 people and generates approximately $20 million in revenue, continually investing in product development to meet market demands.

LWRC International, LLC is an American firearms manufacturer and defense contractor based in Cambridge, Maryland. Founded in 1999, the company specializes in designing and producing high-performance firearms, particularly focusing on a proprietary short-stroke gas piston operating system for the AR-15/M16/M4 rifle family. This innovative system enhances reliability and simplifies maintenance by reducing heat and carbon fouling.

The company offers a variety of products, including the M6 Series weapons, which feature several variants such as assault rifles, submachine guns, and sniper/assault battle rifles. LWRC also manufactures pistols and suppressors, catering to both individual enthusiasts and professional users. With over 250,000 square feet of manufacturing space and advanced capabilities, LWRC is committed to quality and serves military, law enforcement, and civilian markets.

Short Description:
Train Hard. Stay Safe.

M22 Tactical is a veteran-owned small business near Grand Rapids, Michigan. 

M22 Tactical strives to be a positive force in the firearms community.  We want everyone using firearms to be responsible, focus on training and safety, to be more proficient and ultimately be a positive force in their communities.

Our mission is for every AR-15 owner to have the RedCAT in their training kit.  Our brand identity and tone of voice will always focus on training, safety and responsible gun ownership.  

We created the RedCAT, a patented dry fire training device, to make the AR community safer, more proficient and better prepared.  The RedCAT is proudly manufactured in western Michigan, USA.  We're thrilled to say that our packaging printer and our fulfillment center are also in Michigan.  

Visit redcat22.com for more info on the RedCat and to see our current retailers.   

M22 Tactical will be at SHOT Show 2024 – Booth 41062, First Floor Venetian.  If you'd like to add the RedCat to your product line, we'll be taking orders!  We hope to see you there!

MES, Inc. (Metrics Engineered Supply Chains) is a global manufacturing and supply chain management company founded in 2007 and headquartered in Lewis Center, Ohio. With offices in eight countries, including the U.S., Mexico, Poland, India, and China, MES specializes in sourcing and managing custom-engineered products such as castings, forgings, extrusions, assemblies, and machined parts. The company serves various industries, including automotive, aerospace, defense, and medical.

MES provides comprehensive supply chain solutions, including global sourcing, inventory management, and just-in-time (JIT) delivery, ensuring cost efficiency and high reliability with a 99% on-time delivery rate. Their manufacturing capabilities encompass aluminum die casting, CNC machining, and customization, focusing on specialized and low-quantity components. The company also offers value-added services like heat treatment and surface finishing, supported by a team of engineers who work closely with clients to develop tailored solutions. MES emphasizes maintaining supply chain resiliency and competitive pricing while leveraging technology to enhance communication and quality oversight throughout the product lifecycle.

Short Description:
O.F. Mossberg & Sons, Inc. is America’s oldest family-owned firearms manufacturer, established in March 1919 in New Haven, Connecticut. The company is known for producing reliable and affordable sporting firearms, with a legacy of family leadership that continues today under the great-grandson of the founder.

Mossberg's product line includes a variety of firearms such as shotguns, rifles, and pistols, with a strong emphasis on quality and affordability. The Mossberg 500 series shotguns are particularly popular among hunters, law enforcement, and military personnel. The company also offers .22 rimfire and tactical rifles, as well as firearm-related accessories like scopes. Mossberg has a significant presence in both civilian and professional markets, with a history of government contracts dating back to World War II.

The corporate headquarters is located in North Haven, Connecticut, while most production takes place in Eagle Pass, Texas. O.F. Mossberg & Sons remains committed to providing value and quality to its diverse customer base.

Their products primarily serve professional sectors such as law enforcement, security, and dispatch services. N-ear is recognized for its patented in-ear technology, which provides 360-degree situational awareness, allowing users to stay aware of their environment while enjoying clear audio communication.

Their products are trusted by U.S. and international law enforcement agencies, reflecting a commitment to quality and customer service. N-ear aims to enhance communication clarity and safety in critical operations with their high-quality, discreet, and comfortable in-ear communication devices.

NEMO Arms, Inc. is an American firearms manufacturer based in Nampa, Idaho, founded in 2011. The company specializes in designing, machining, and assembling advanced weapon systems, emphasizing precision and innovation. Originally established in Kalispell, Montana, NEMO Arms has expanded its focus from military and law enforcement weaponry to serve both professional and consumer markets.

NEMO Arms is known for producing the world's first .300 Winchester Magnum cartridge on a Modern Sporting Rifle platform. Their product lineup includes AR-style rifles and pistol caliber carbines, such as the Nemo Arms Omen rifle, which is designed for long-range shooting and tactical applications. The company prioritizes American craftsmanship, with all weapons designed and assembled by skilled workers in Idaho. NEMO Arms also offers services in weapon system integration, research and development, and internal testing, catering to a diverse customer base that includes Special Operations forces, federal law enforcement, competitive shooters, and hunters.

Short Description:
Oberlin Filter Company is an engineering firm founded in 1964, specializing in the design, manufacture, and support of automatic pressure filtration systems. With over 60 years of experience, the company provides reliable and efficient filtration solutions for various industrial applications worldwide.

The company focuses on creating custom automatic filtration equipment, primarily for water and coolant filtration. Their products are utilized in industries such as aerospace, medical, automotive, and surface treatment. Oberlin Filter also supplies filtration media for sectors involving bearings, blades, and gears. Their automatic pressure filters are known for their durability, with some units operating continuously for over 40 years.

Oberlin Filter operates globally, with a significant presence in the UK and Europe through Oberlin Filter Ltd. The company emphasizes collaboration with customers to tailor filtration systems to their specific needs and provides comprehensive support throughout the system's lifecycle. Their manufacturing facilities have expanded to accommodate growth, reflecting their commitment to quality and innovation.

Short Description:
ACTIVATE! Change Drivers is an independent non-profit organization based in South Africa, established in 2012. It focuses on empowering young people aged 18-34 to become active citizens and leaders who drive positive social, economic, and political change. The organization connects over 4,300 young leaders, known as "Activators," through leadership development and civic engagement programs.

The core mission of ACTIVATE! is to provide young South Africans with the tools and training needed to participate actively in democracy and create sustainable change in their communities. The organization offers leadership training, community centers for collaboration, and civic education initiatives to increase youth participation in political processes. ACTIVATE! also hosts national recruitment campaigns and maintains alumni networks to enhance the impact of its youth leadership movement. Through its work, ACTIVATE! aims to listen to youth voices and adapt to changing social contexts, fostering youth-led initiatives that address local needs and promote democratic participation.

They offer a lifetime warranty against manufacturing defects, showcasing their commitment to quality and durability. The company has received numerous industry awards and sponsors athletes who excel in outdoor sports. With a retail store in Seattle and a global distribution network, Outdoor Research aims to create inclusive outdoor experiences for all.

Founded in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania by Derek Peterson and his two business partners, Peterson Cartridge was built with one main goal. That goal is to produce extremely consistent, American-Made brass rifle casings which are designed around, and for, long-distance marksmen.

Unlike most of its competitors, Peterson Cartridge has devoted its entire facility, machinery, and laboratory to producing only brass rifle casings. Specialization is the driving principle behind Peterson Cartridge only producing one component of a multi-component finished product.

In our mind, if you want precision projectiles, purchase them from a company that specializes in projectiles. If you want consistent propellant and primers, purchase them from a company that specializes in propellant and primers. And if you want extremely precise and consistent brass rifle casings, purchase them from us, Peterson Cartridge.

We are a proud member of the Peterson Brothers, Inc. team.

Short Description:
Q30 Innovations is a research and development company dedicated to protecting the brain from traumatic injuries caused by repetitive head impacts, particularly in athletes and military personnel. The company has developed the FDA-cleared Q-Collar, a wearable device that applies gentle pressure to the neck to increase blood volume inside the skull and minimize brain movement during impacts. This innovative approach aims to reduce the risk of injury from sub-concussive impacts that traditional protective gear may not fully address.

The Q-Collar is trusted by over 45,000 athletes, including professionals in contact sports, and is also marketed for military use. Q30 Innovations offers customizable Q-Collar Sleeves in various colors and sizes, allowing users to personalize their protective gear. The company collaborates with leading medical and academic institutions, resulting in more than 25 independent studies published in top medical journals. Headquartered in Westport, Connecticut, Q30 Innovations is expanding its market presence in the United States and Canada, focusing on advanced brain protection technology for athletes and soldiers worldwide.

Short Description:
About Rathbone

Rathbone Precision Metals, a subsidiary of Calvi SpA, was founded in 1905 in Palmer, Massachusetts as a small pinion wire-making manufacturer that served the clock industry in central New England. In 1912 Rathbone moved to its current location in Palmer, MA at 1241 Park Street where we grew to expand around the original brick structure of 1912 that continues to stand today.

Since our inception, we have grown to be the largest and most respected producer of cold rolled and cold drawn metal profiles in North America, primarily serving the power generation, firearms, computer, medical, oil exploration and lawn and garden markets, among a score of others. This has all been made possible by our highly skilled employees, expert engineers, advanced equipment capabilities, faculty for innovation, and close cooperation with our customers, from initial design to the final product.

Rescue Essentials is a U.S.-based company that designs, manufactures, and distributes tactical emergency medical supplies and equipment. Founded in 2007 and headquartered in Leland, North Carolina, the company serves a diverse range of customers, including first responders, law enforcement, military, fire/EMS, and search and rescue professionals. Their mission focuses on providing high-quality products and services that enhance survival outcomes for both trained professionals and everyday heroes.

The company offers a wide selection of emergency medical kits and trauma gear, including Individual First Aid Kits (IFAKs), tactical medical pouches, and custom trauma kits tailored to specific needs. Rescue Essentials excels in custom design, assembly, and contract manufacturing of medical kits, informed by real-world input from clients like the U.S. Border Patrol and NYPD. Their commitment to quality, reliability, and timely delivery ensures that professionals in challenging environments have access to essential medical supplies.

Ring Power Corporation, based in St. Augustine, Florida, is one of the largest authorized Caterpillar dealers in the Southeastern United States. Established in 1961, the company has over 60 years of experience and operates 26 sales locations across North and Central Florida, employing more than 1,600 people. Ring Power emphasizes core values such as safety, integrity, and teamwork, aiming to be a trusted partner for its customers and suppliers.

The company operates through eight main divisions, offering a wide range of services including the sales, leasing, and rental of new and used Caterpillar equipment, as well as equipment servicing and support. Ring Power also features specialized divisions like Ring Power Crane and Entertainment Services, which provide cranes and power equipment rentals for events. Its Cat Rental Store offers a diverse fleet of construction machines with flexible rental terms and 24-hour field support. Ring Power serves various industries, including construction, government, agriculture, and entertainment, ensuring reliable equipment and maintenance support throughout Florida and beyond.

RISE Armament is a firearms manufacturer based in Broken Arrow, Oklahoma, founded in 2013 by engineers and firearms enthusiasts. The company focuses on precision engineering and advanced machining techniques to produce high-performance AR-type rifles and firearm components. 

Their product lineup includes a variety of triggers, such as the RA-140 Super Sporting Trigger and the RA-535 drop-in trigger, known for their crisp performance. RISE Armament also manufactures complete AR-15 and AR-style .308 rifles, recognized for their accuracy and reliability. Additionally, they offer various components and accessories, including barrels, bolt carrier groups, and muzzle devices, all crafted with a commitment to quality and innovation.

RISE Armament serves a diverse customer base, including civilian enthusiasts, competitive shooters, law enforcement, and military personnel. The company is dedicated to continuous improvement and has invested in advanced manufacturing technologies to enhance production efficiency. They also engage in white-label and contract manufacturing, further expanding their presence in the firearms industry.

Born in the Heart of the Wild West

Straight out of Tucson, Arizona, Riton Optics is proud to bring quality and affordability to the optics industry with the greatest focus being you: the customer and end user.

You Will See the Difference

With each and every order we strive to surpass your expectations. From your first look through our Riton High Density glass to your interaction with our customer service team in Tucson, Arizona, we are confident that you will appreciate the quality of our service and products.

You will see the difference in everything we do because we are different, and we developed this company to be exactly that so that you, the consumer, get everything you deserve.

Rochester Precision Optics (RPO) is a leading manufacturer of precision optical products, based in West Henrietta, New York. Established in 2005, RPO is recognized globally for its expertise in night vision applications and offers a wide range of services throughout the product lifecycle, including design, prototyping, fabrication, assembly, and full-rate production.

The company specializes in various manufacturing techniques such as precision glass molding, injection-molded polymer optics, optical diamond turning, and thin film coating. RPO provides comprehensive design and engineering support, with a team of mechanical and optical engineers dedicated to developing lightweight electro-optical products. They serve multiple industries, including industrial, consumer electronics, medical devices, and security, catering to a diverse clientele that includes leading manufacturers and government agencies. RPO emphasizes customer-centric solutions and maintains a commitment to delivering high-quality products on time.

Short Description:
RTP Company is a global manufacturer based in Winona, Minnesota, specializing in custom-engineered thermoplastics. Founded in 1982, the company emerged from the merger of the thermoplastic division of Fiberite and Plastic Trading Company. It is family-operated, led by President and CEO Hugh Miller, which allows for flexibility in creating tailored plastic compounds from over 60 engineering resins and numerous additives.

The company offers a diverse range of thermoplastic products, including pellets for injection molding, sheets for thermoforming, and films made from various materials like TPU, polycarbonate, and PVC. RTP Company focuses on developing custom compounds with specific properties such as color, conductivity, and flame retardancy. It serves multiple industries, including automotive, healthcare, and electronics, and operates more than 20 manufacturing facilities worldwide, ensuring effective service to its global customer base.

Rugged Suppressors is committed to delivering superior products and exceptional customer service, offering an Unconditional Lifetime Warranty to reflect their confidence in product durability. Their diverse clientele includes hunters, tactical operators, and sport shooters who seek reliable and high-performance suppressors.

Short Description:
SCHUBERTH GmbH is a German company that designs and manufactures high-quality safety helmets and protective headgear. Founded in 1922 in Braunschweig, the company is now based in Magdeburg and has over 100 years of experience in helmet production. With around 300 employees, SCHUBERTH produces approximately 1.5 million helmets annually, focusing on innovation in safety, aerodynamics, and comfort.

Short Description:
Toor Knives Inc is a U.S.-based knife manufacturer founded in 2014 by Connor Toor, a former U.S. Marine Corps rifle squad leader. The company specializes in high-quality, hard-use fixed-blade knives that are 100% handmade in the USA. These knives are designed for tactical, sportsman, and everyday carry (EDC) users, reflecting Toor's military experience and insights from fellow servicemen.

The product line includes tactical knives, sportsman knives, and everyday carry knives, all crafted with durable materials for reliability in demanding conditions. Notable offerings include the Mutiny knife, a limited edition collaboration featuring CPM 154 steel blades and 7075 aluminum handles. Toor Knives emphasizes quality with a lifetime guarantee on all blades. The company combines traditional handcrafting with modern manufacturing techniques to ensure precision and scalability, supported by a robust business platform for operational efficiency and global expansion.

Short Description:
Trinidad State College is a public community college in Trinidad, Colorado, established in 1925 as the state's first community college. It operates two campuses: the main campus in Trinidad and a satellite campus in Alamosa. The college is part of the Colorado Community College System and serves around 1,500 students, focusing on affordable and accessible education.

The college offers a diverse range of academic and vocational programs, including fields like Nursing, Welding, Cosmetology, and Cybersecurity. It is known for its unique Gunsmithing School and provides traditional Arts and Sciences courses with transfer agreements to four-year institutions. Trinidad State College emphasizes small class sizes and personalized support, fostering close interactions between students and faculty. With tuition rates significantly lower than those of four-year institutions, it is committed to student success and community enrichment. The college promotes a welcoming environment and is dedicated to diversity, equity, and inclusion.

TSE Industries is a family-owned global manufacturer based in Clearwater, Florida, specializing in polymers, specialty chemicals, plastics, and rubber. Established in 1962, the company has grown from a small distributor to a significant player in the manufacturing of custom-molded, injected, and extruded rubber and plastic products, all produced in the United States.

The product range includes polyurethane elastomers, chain guides, custom rubber extrusions, and various molding and casting products. TSE Industries serves a diverse array of industries, including aerospace and citrus, providing high-performance polymer materials tailored to meet specific needs. With a workforce of around 300 employees, the company generates approximately $81.5 million in revenue, reflecting its strong presence in the chemicals and related products sector.

Tungaloy Corporation is a Japanese company based in Iwaki, Fukushima, that specializes in the production and sales of metal cutting tools and industrial products. Established in 1929, Tungaloy was the first company in Japan to develop cemented carbide, showcasing its long-standing expertise in powder metallurgy and innovative materials.

The company offers a wide range of products, including metal cutting tools like indexable inserts, wear-resistant tools, civil engineering tools, and friction materials. These products cater to various industries such as automobile, construction, aerospace, medical, power generation, and infrastructure. Tungaloy is committed to continuous improvement and innovation, particularly in powder metallurgy and coating technologies, to maintain its leadership in the market.

Tungaloy also emphasizes the development of environmentally friendly tools that support global conservation efforts. With a focus on customer relationships, the company tailors its technologies to meet diverse industrial needs, ensuring high-quality and sustainable solutions.

Short Description:
It happens every day, thousands of times a week. A veteran, a police officer or a civilian opens a box. They find their freshly American made leather holster. The leather softens after a few days and many of them contact the proud staff at Urban Carry simply to thank them for making Concealed Carry so easy and comfortable.

That's what we believe in, that's what we stand for. At Urban Carry we know if something is uncomfortable or difficult we as humans tend to avoid it. We don't want anyone doing that with their safety. We fundamentally believe that the more honest people willing to take a stand against crime and terror the less it will exist. The greater the shepherds the weaker the wolves. We believe in making ways to keep the citizens of America, and the world, safe by helping you keep your safety something simple and comfortable to achieve.

We make sure everything we do honors that belief. From the quality of materials we use, the unique designs
Since its inception in 2014, Urban Carry Holsters has grown rapidly, getting its start exhibiting at local gun shows. Soon, it grew into a thriving national business devoted to remembering its roots of excellent customer service and excellent products to match. Even as we've grown the gun shows have remained a staple as we place real value in meeting our customers, sharing our product with them, and exchanging stories and ideas. As we tell our customers, "Your feedback only helps us to make a great product even better." It is this personal commitment to our customers and our product that extends us beyond our competition.

Urban Carry is thoughtfully constructed from the finest quality saddle-grade leather and saddle-grade nylon stitching. Each of our holsters is hand sewn, individually, to allow a level of attention to detail unparalleled anywhere in our industry. Of course, our holsters are made here in the USA by our team of craftsmen and women. We are the creator, manufacturer, the distributor, and the retailer.

Short Description:
White River Knives are custom quality, American made knife and tool products. White River is family owned with a focus on customer satisfaction. Current products include knives for hunting, fishing, survival, and custom applications.

--Custom Quality matters to us. Which is why we precision grind, hand finish, and leather hone every razor sharp knife we make.

--Customer Satisfaction matters to us. Which is why we guarantee every knife for life. If you are not 100% satisfied with your White River Knife, return it for repair or replacement, free of charge, no questions asked.

--And, American Made matters to us! Every single component – from our steels to the thread in our American made leather sheaths is sourced and produced in the U.S.A.

Michigan's White River in the Manistee National Forest runs through the family property and is the inspiration for the company name. Guide Sensmart, officially known as Wuhan Guide Sensmart Tech Co., Ltd., is a prominent Chinese company focused on developing, manufacturing, and marketing infrared thermal imaging products for commercial use. Established in 2016 as a subsidiary of Guide Infrared Co., Ltd., the company benefits from over 20 years of expertise in infrared technology. With a registered capital of RMB 60 million and a workforce of over 600 employees, approximately 30% of whom are dedicated to research and development, Guide Sensmart operates six major product lines with an annual production capacity of around 1.5 million units.

The company offers a wide range of infrared thermal imaging products, including thermal cameras, thermal imaging modules, thermal scopes, smartphone thermal cameras, and thermographic instruments. Its technology is utilized across various sectors such as security surveillance, law enforcement, firefighting, industrial inspection, and energy diagnostics. Recognized as a leading provider in Asia, Guide Sensmart emphasizes innovation and quality, holding over 50 patents and numerous software copyrights. The company maintains a strong global presence, collaborating with over 300 partners and participating in more than 30 international exhibitions each year.
